WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.560
4,000 essential English words 1. Paul Nation

00:15.560 --> 00:20.360
Copyright 2009. Compass Publishing. All rights reserved.

00:30.000 --> 00:42.280
Unit 1. Wordless. Afraid. When someone is afraid, they feel

00:42.280 --> 00:53.400
fear. The woman was afraid of what she saw. Agree. To agree is to say yes or to think

00:53.400 --> 01:02.480
the same way. The food is very good in that restaurant. I agree with you.

01:02.480 --> 01:10.600
Angry. When someone is angry, they may want to speak loudly or fight. She didn't do her

01:10.600 --> 01:21.960
homework, so her father is angry. Arrive. To arrive is to get to or reach some place.

01:21.960 --> 01:31.400
The bus always arrives at the corner of my street at 4. Attack. To attack is to try

01:31.400 --> 01:36.720
to fight or to hurt. The man with the sword attacked the other

01:36.720 --> 01:49.280
man first. Bottom. The bottom is the lowest part. The bottom of my shoe has a hole in it.

01:49.280 --> 01:58.120
Clever. When someone is clever, they can solve a hard puzzle or problem. The clever boy thought

01:58.120 --> 02:08.520
of a good idea. Cruel. When someone is cruel, they do bad things to hurt others. The cruel

02:08.520 --> 02:18.080
man yelled at his sister. Finally. If something happens finally, it happens after a long time

02:18.080 --> 02:24.440
or at the end. He finally crossed the finish line after five hours of running.

02:24.440 --> 02:34.920
Hide. To hide is to try not to let others see you. The other children will hide while you count

02:34.920 --> 02:46.240
to 100. Hunt. To hunt is to look for or search for an animal to kill. Long ago, people hunted

02:46.240 --> 02:56.560
with bows and arrows. Lot. A lot means a large number or amount of people, animals, things,

02:56.560 --> 03:07.080
etc. There are a lot of apples in the basket. Middle. The middle of something is the center

03:07.160 --> 03:18.160
or halfway point. The Canadian flag has a maple leaf in the middle of it. Moment. A moment is a

03:18.160 --> 03:29.000
second or a very short time. I was only a few moments late for the meeting. Please. When someone

03:29.000 --> 03:38.800
is pleased, they are happy. She was pleased with the phone call she received. Promise. To

03:38.800 --> 03:45.720
promise is to say you will do something for sure. He promised to return my key by tomorrow.

03:45.720 --> 03:56.440
Reply. To reply is to give an answer or say back to someone. She asked him what time his

03:56.440 --> 04:07.320
meeting was. He replied at three. Safe. When a person is safe, they are not in danger. Put on

04:07.320 --> 04:16.320
your seatbelt and the car to be safe. Trick. A trick is something you do to fool another person.

04:16.320 --> 04:27.000
His car trick really surprised us. Well, you use well to say that something was done in a good way.

04:27.000 --> 04:40.360
The couple can dance quite well. The lion and the rabbit. A cruel lion lived in the forest. Every

04:40.360 --> 04:48.400
day he killed and ate a lot of animals. The other animals were afraid the lion would kill them all.

04:48.400 --> 04:56.800
The animals told the lion, let's make a deal. If you promise to eat only one animal each day,

04:56.800 --> 05:05.040
then one of us will come to you every day. Then you don't have to hunt and kill us. The plan

05:05.040 --> 05:12.600
sounded well thought out to the lion, so he agreed. But he also said, if you don't come every day,

05:12.600 --> 05:20.640
I promise to kill all of you the next day. Each day after that, one animal went to the lion so that

05:20.640 --> 05:29.120
the lion could eat it. Then all the other animals were safe. Finally, it was the rabbit's turn to go

05:29.120 --> 05:36.880
to the lion. The rabbit went very slowly that day, so the lion was angry when the rabbit finally

05:36.880 --> 05:46.080
arrived. The lion angrily asked the rabbit, why are you late? I was hiding from another lion in

05:46.080 --> 05:54.920
the forest. That lion said he was the king, so I was afraid. The lion told the rabbit, I am the

05:54.920 --> 06:03.480
only king here. Take me to that other lion and I will kill him. The rabbit replied, I will be

06:03.480 --> 06:10.640
happy to show you where he lives. The rabbit led the lion to an old well in the middle of the forest.

06:10.640 --> 06:18.720
The well was very deep with water at the bottom. The rabbit told the lion, look in there. The lion

06:18.800 --> 06:25.520
lives at the bottom. When the lion looked in the well, he could see his own face in the water.

06:26.320 --> 06:33.600
He thought that was the other lion. Without waiting another moment, the lion jumped into the well to

06:33.600 --> 06:41.120
attack the other lion. He never came out. All of the other animals in the forest were very pleased

06:41.120 --> 06:53.920
with their rabbit's clever trick. Unit two, word list, adventure. An adventure is a fun or

06:53.920 --> 07:04.240
exciting thing that you do. Riding in the rough water was an adventure. Approach. To approach

07:04.240 --> 07:09.120
something means to move close to it. The boy approached his school.

07:11.280 --> 07:16.320
Chemical. A chemical is something that scientists use in chemistry.

07:17.520 --> 07:25.760
The scientist mixed the chemicals. Carefully. Carefully means with great attention,

07:26.320 --> 07:32.880
especially to detail or safety. The baby carefully climbed down the stairs.

07:35.040 --> 07:43.520
Create. To create means to make something new. She created an igloo from blocks of snow.

07:45.840 --> 07:56.160
Evil. Evil describes something or someone bad or cruel, not good. The evil figure scared us all.

07:56.160 --> 08:03.600
Experiment. An experiment is a test that you do to see what will happen.

08:04.800 --> 08:08.080
The student did an experiment in science class.

08:10.240 --> 08:14.800
Kill. To kill someone or something is to make them die.

08:16.000 --> 08:25.600
I killed the fly with the fly swatter. Laboratory. A laboratory is a room where a scientist works.

08:26.880 --> 08:36.080
My mother works in a laboratory. Laugh. Laugh is the sound made when someone is happy or a funny

08:36.080 --> 08:47.280
thing occurs. The sound of their laugh filled the room. Loud. If a sound is loud, it is strong

08:47.280 --> 08:53.520
and very easy to hear. The man's voice was so loud that we all could hear him.

08:54.240 --> 08:59.680
Nervous. When a person is nervous, they think something bad will happen.

09:00.640 --> 09:04.320
The boy became nervous when he heard the news.

09:05.920 --> 09:09.920
Noise. A noise is an unpleasant sound.

09:10.880 --> 09:13.840
The crying baby made a loud noise.

09:15.760 --> 09:21.680
Project. A project is a type of work that you do for a school or a job.

09:22.560 --> 09:28.160
His afternoon work project was to paint the room green.

09:30.480 --> 09:35.120
Scare. To scare someone is to make them feel afraid.

09:36.320 --> 09:39.840
My uncle was scared by what he saw in the room.

09:42.080 --> 09:46.800
Secret. A secret is something that you do not tell other people.

09:47.760 --> 09:50.640
The two boys were sharing a secret.

09:52.800 --> 09:53.280
Shout.

09:54.400 --> 09:56.480
Two shout is to say something loudly.

09:57.600 --> 10:01.760
My boss shouted at me because I was late for work.

10:04.080 --> 10:04.480
Smell.

10:05.680 --> 10:08.960
Two smell something means to use your nose to sense it.

10:10.160 --> 10:12.640
The two friends smell the flower.

10:12.880 --> 10:19.200
Terrible. If something is terrible, it is very bad.

10:20.400 --> 10:23.360
The way he treated his classmate was terrible.

10:25.600 --> 10:31.440
Worse. If something is worse, it is of poorer quality than another thing.

10:32.720 --> 10:35.760
Business was worse this month than last month.

10:35.760 --> 10:40.400
The laboratory.

10:41.680 --> 10:46.080
Mia's father had a laboratory, but she had no idea what was in it.

10:47.040 --> 10:50.240
Her dad always closed and locked the door when he went in.

10:51.440 --> 10:54.000
She knew that he used it to do projects for work.

10:55.120 --> 10:57.440
He never told Mia what these projects were.

10:58.800 --> 11:02.320
One night, Mia approached the door to the laboratory.

11:03.200 --> 11:07.840
She stopped and thought, I wonder what crazy experiment he is doing now.

11:08.640 --> 11:13.360
Suddenly, she heard a loud noise. It sounded like an evil laugh.

11:14.240 --> 11:17.920
The noise scared her, so she walked quickly back to her room.

11:19.040 --> 11:21.840
The next night, her friend Liz came to her house.

11:22.800 --> 11:25.920
When Liz arrived, Mia told her about the night before.

11:26.880 --> 11:29.440
Oh, it was terrible, she said.

11:30.640 --> 11:32.320
Why don't we see what is in there?

11:32.880 --> 11:33.520
Liz asked.

11:34.240 --> 11:36.000
It will be a fun adventure.

11:36.880 --> 11:40.080
Mia felt nervous about going into her father's laboratory,

11:40.640 --> 11:41.520
but she agreed.

11:42.320 --> 11:44.320
As always, the door was locked.

11:45.040 --> 11:48.480
They waited until Mia's father left the laboratory to eat dinner.

11:49.120 --> 11:50.480
He didn't lock the door.

11:51.200 --> 11:52.800
Liz said, let's go.

11:53.760 --> 11:55.120
The laboratory was dark.

11:56.000 --> 11:58.240
The girls walked down the stairs carefully.

11:59.200 --> 12:01.200
Mia smelled strange chemicals.

12:02.000 --> 12:04.480
What terrible thing was her father creating?

12:05.360 --> 12:07.680
Suddenly, they heard an evil laugh.

12:08.720 --> 12:11.600
It was even worse than the one Mia heard the night before.

12:12.640 --> 12:14.800
What if a monster was going to kill them?

12:15.600 --> 12:16.800
Mia had to do something.

12:17.520 --> 12:18.560
She shouted for help.

12:19.360 --> 12:21.920
Mia's father ran into the room and turned on the lights.

12:22.640 --> 12:24.480
Oh no, he said.

12:25.200 --> 12:26.880
You must have learned my secret.

12:27.760 --> 12:30.720
Your monster tried to kill us, Mia said.

12:31.680 --> 12:33.520
Monster, he asked.

12:34.240 --> 12:35.040
You mean this?

12:35.840 --> 12:37.600
He had a pretty doll in his hands.

12:38.400 --> 12:39.360
The doll laughed.

12:39.920 --> 12:42.400
The laugh didn't sound so evil anymore.

12:43.440 --> 12:45.120
I made this for your birthday.

12:46.000 --> 12:49.360
I wanted to give it to you then, but you can have it now.

12:50.000 --> 12:50.880
I hope you like it.

12:52.000 --> 12:52.800
I hope you like it.

12:55.040 --> 12:56.960
Unit 3, word list.

12:58.160 --> 12:58.640
Alien.

12:59.840 --> 13:02.560
An alien is a creature from a different world.

13:03.760 --> 13:05.760
The alien came in peace.

13:08.000 --> 13:08.400
Among.

13:09.760 --> 13:13.280
If you are among certain things, they are all around you.

13:14.480 --> 13:17.760
There was a red apple among the green ones.

13:18.480 --> 13:19.360
A chart.

13:20.320 --> 13:22.720
A chart is a list of information.

13:23.920 --> 13:27.120
We used a chart to see how we had improved.

13:28.960 --> 13:29.920
Cloud.

13:30.640 --> 13:33.680
A cloud is a group of water drops in the sky.

13:34.880 --> 13:37.360
The sky was filled with white clouds.

13:39.840 --> 13:40.480
Comprehend.

13:41.200 --> 13:43.840
To comprehend something is to understand it.

13:44.320 --> 13:47.360
Henry could not comprehend the message.

13:48.800 --> 13:49.600
Describe.

13:50.560 --> 13:55.760
To describe is to say or write what someone or something is like.

13:57.200 --> 14:02.240
They describe their tree as colorful, with gold ribbon and a star.

14:04.640 --> 14:05.120
Ever.

14:06.000 --> 14:08.000
Ever means at any time.

14:09.040 --> 14:13.040
Going skiing last winter was the most fun out of the day.

14:13.840 --> 14:14.800
I've ever had.

14:17.120 --> 14:17.440
Fail.

14:18.720 --> 14:22.080
To fail means you do not succeed in what you try to do.

14:23.440 --> 14:26.240
Since he failed to get the jump, he was sad.

14:28.400 --> 14:28.960
Friendly.

14:30.080 --> 14:33.840
Friendly is behaving in a pleasant, kind way towards someone.

14:34.880 --> 14:37.680
Their friendly animals came up to the girl.

14:38.320 --> 14:39.840
Grade.

14:39.840 --> 14:44.880
A grade is a score or mark given to someone's work.

14:46.080 --> 14:49.280
I managed to get good grains on my report card.

14:51.440 --> 14:52.080
Instead.

14:53.280 --> 14:55.360
Instead means in place of.

14:56.400 --> 14:59.440
The 8th the carrot instead of the ice cream.

15:01.680 --> 15:02.320
Library.

15:03.520 --> 15:06.400
A library is a place where you go to read books.

15:07.680 --> 15:10.720
The library at school is full of books.

15:12.880 --> 15:13.360
Planet.

15:14.480 --> 15:17.280
A planet is a large round thing in space.

15:18.560 --> 15:21.600
Saturn is the planet with the ring around it.

15:23.760 --> 15:24.320
Report.

15:25.440 --> 15:28.080
A report is something students write for school.

15:29.200 --> 15:31.680
Karen had trouble writing her report.

15:33.920 --> 15:34.320
Several.

15:35.280 --> 15:38.080
Several is more than two but not many.

15:39.200 --> 15:41.760
He had to read several books for class.

15:44.080 --> 15:44.480
Solve.

15:45.600 --> 15:48.320
To solve something is to find an answer to it.

15:49.440 --> 15:52.800
All the students could easily solve the math problem.

15:55.040 --> 15:55.600
Suddenly.

15:56.720 --> 16:01.040
If something happens suddenly, it happens quickly and unexpectedly.

16:01.840 --> 16:06.240
I was suddenly surprised by the cake my friends brought me.

16:08.400 --> 16:09.040
Suppose.

16:10.160 --> 16:11.920
To suppose is to guess.

16:13.120 --> 16:15.360
I suppose I should go home now.

16:17.600 --> 16:18.160
Universe.

16:19.280 --> 16:22.960
The universe is the known or supposed objects in space.

16:24.080 --> 16:27.440
The universe is so large that it cannot be measured.

16:27.760 --> 16:28.560
View.

16:29.760 --> 16:33.120
To view is to look at something.

16:34.400 --> 16:37.120
Michael likes to view himself in the mirror.

16:40.640 --> 16:41.360
The report.

16:42.560 --> 16:47.680
Lee sat among the books at the library and thought about his group project.

16:48.480 --> 16:52.880
They had to turn it in soon but he hadn't even started his part.

16:53.840 --> 16:55.920
Jack and Claire were in his group.

16:56.560 --> 16:58.160
They had worked hard.

16:58.160 --> 17:02.960
They were also very smart and Lee didn't want them to get a bad grade.

17:03.840 --> 17:05.440
Jack did the report.

17:05.440 --> 17:10.880
He wrote a lot of very good sentences and described things with great adjectives.

17:11.600 --> 17:14.560
Claire drew a nice map of the stars.

17:14.560 --> 17:17.840
Now Lee needed to do his part of the project.

17:18.560 --> 17:22.560
Well, I suppose I need to start my model, Lee thought.

17:23.280 --> 17:26.080
Making a model of a planet was really hard.

17:26.880 --> 17:32.000
Lee tried to read several books but he couldn't comprehend any of the charts.

17:32.720 --> 17:36.400
We're going to fail because of me, Lee said.

17:37.120 --> 17:39.760
He put his head down on the table and said,

17:40.400 --> 17:44.640
I wish I could see a planet instead of having to read about it.

17:45.440 --> 17:47.840
Suddenly there was a bright light.

17:48.720 --> 17:52.160
Lee was pulled from his chair, threw the roof

17:52.160 --> 17:54.160
and right into a strange ship.

17:54.960 --> 17:56.240
Hello, kid.

17:56.240 --> 17:57.600
Said an alien.

17:57.600 --> 17:59.040
Did you ask for help?

17:59.760 --> 18:03.360
Lee told the friendly alien all about his project.

18:04.000 --> 18:07.200
The alien agreed to help Lee solve his problem.

18:07.920 --> 18:11.440
First, we'll fly through space to view the universe.

18:11.440 --> 18:14.720
Then I can help you make a model of my planet.

18:15.520 --> 18:18.320
Soon they were going through the clouds.

18:18.320 --> 18:20.000
They passed the moon.

18:20.000 --> 18:21.360
Then they viewed Mars.

18:22.000 --> 18:24.320
Lee was very excited.

18:24.320 --> 18:28.800
Instead of a bad grade, his group would have the best project ever.

18:29.520 --> 18:31.520
It's time to go home.

18:31.520 --> 18:33.200
The alien finally said.

18:33.840 --> 18:38.240
On the way back, he helped Lee make a model of the planet Mars.

18:39.040 --> 18:40.800
Soon they were on Earth.

18:41.600 --> 18:43.360
Thanks, Lee said.

18:43.360 --> 18:45.040
My model will be awesome.

18:45.840 --> 18:49.600
Then he took his model and said goodbye to his new friend.

18:52.160 --> 18:55.600
Unit 4, word list.

18:56.800 --> 18:57.520
Appropriate.

18:58.640 --> 19:01.760
When a thing is appropriate, it is right or normal.

19:02.880 --> 19:06.560
It's appropriate to wear a suit when you go to the office.

19:08.880 --> 19:09.440
Avoid.

19:10.640 --> 19:13.360
To avoid something is to stay away from it.

19:14.480 --> 19:16.960
Avoid the broken bottle on the floor.

19:17.840 --> 19:19.360
Behave.

19:19.360 --> 19:24.960
To behave is to act in a particular way, especially to be good.

19:24.960 --> 19:29.360
She always behaves well when her father is around.

19:32.000 --> 19:32.560
Calm.

19:32.560 --> 19:37.040
When someone is calm, they do not get excited or upset.

19:37.040 --> 19:41.440
A nice, warm bath makes me feel so calm.

19:43.440 --> 19:43.840
Concern.

19:43.840 --> 19:44.160
Concern.

19:44.320 --> 19:44.880
Concern.

19:46.080 --> 19:48.000
Concern is a feeling of worry.

19:49.040 --> 19:52.800
I was filled with concern after reading the newspaper.

19:54.960 --> 19:55.520
Content.

19:56.720 --> 19:59.760
To be content is to be happy and not want more.

20:00.960 --> 20:04.480
The baby looked very content sitting on the floor.

20:06.640 --> 20:07.200
Expect.

20:08.400 --> 20:11.680
If you expect something to happen, you believe it will happen.

20:12.640 --> 20:15.920
I expect the boss to be here very soon.

20:18.160 --> 20:18.800
Frequently.

20:20.000 --> 20:22.720
When something happens frequently, it happens often.

20:23.920 --> 20:28.320
We meet frequently, either at the beginning or ending of the week.

20:30.480 --> 20:30.880
Habit.

20:32.000 --> 20:34.080
A habit is a thing that you do often.

20:35.360 --> 20:38.320
Smoking is a bad habit that can kill you.

20:39.040 --> 20:40.480
Instructional.

20:40.480 --> 20:41.120
Instruct.

20:42.240 --> 20:43.760
To instruct is to teach.

20:45.120 --> 20:48.320
My teacher instructs us in several subjects.

20:50.480 --> 20:50.960
Issue.

20:52.080 --> 20:54.080
An issue is an important topic.

20:55.200 --> 20:58.880
The men spoke about issues that were important to the people.

21:01.120 --> 21:01.440
None.

21:02.800 --> 21:05.520
None means not any of someone or something.

21:06.480 --> 21:08.320
He spent all his money.

21:08.720 --> 21:10.000
There is none left.

21:12.160 --> 21:12.640
Patient.

21:13.760 --> 21:18.080
If a person is patient, they don't become angry or upset easily.

21:19.200 --> 21:22.880
I had to be patient and wait until five o'clock to leave.

21:25.120 --> 21:25.680
Positive.

21:26.720 --> 21:28.880
If something is positive, it is good.

21:30.160 --> 21:34.320
She has a positive future ahead of her after finishing college.

21:36.480 --> 21:36.960
Punish.

21:38.080 --> 21:42.880
To punish means to make someone suffer for breaking the rules or laws.

21:44.000 --> 21:47.360
To punish me, my teacher had me stand in the corner.

21:49.520 --> 21:50.160
Represent.

21:51.200 --> 21:55.360
To represent is to speak or act for a person or group.

21:56.560 --> 21:59.120
My lawyer will represent me in court.

22:01.360 --> 22:01.760
Shake.

22:02.720 --> 22:06.640
To shake is to move back and forth or up and down quickly.

22:07.760 --> 22:11.200
When people shake hands, it usually means they agree.

22:13.520 --> 22:14.000
Spread.

22:15.200 --> 22:18.160
To spread is to move quickly to more places.

22:19.280 --> 22:21.760
I like to spread butter on my toast.

22:23.920 --> 22:24.320
Stroll.

22:25.520 --> 22:28.720
To stroll means to walk slowly and calmly.

22:29.680 --> 22:32.480
My dog and I stroll through the park today.

22:34.720 --> 22:35.200
Village.

22:36.320 --> 22:38.480
A village is a very small town.

22:39.680 --> 22:42.560
There are only a few houses in my village.

22:46.080 --> 22:47.120
The dog's bell.

22:48.480 --> 22:50.560
John's dog was a bad dog.

22:51.280 --> 22:52.720
He bit people frequently.

22:53.680 --> 22:55.600
John had great concern about this.

22:56.320 --> 22:59.200
It was not an appropriate way for a dog to behave.

22:59.920 --> 23:03.600
His friends in the village always expected the dog to bite them.

23:04.560 --> 23:07.440
The news about John's dog spread through the village.

23:08.160 --> 23:10.560
None of the people wanted to go to John's house.

23:11.440 --> 23:15.280
John tried to instruct the dog to behave, but it never worked.

23:16.000 --> 23:19.440
He tried to be patient and teach the dog to be calm.

23:20.320 --> 23:21.680
That also didn't work.

23:22.560 --> 23:24.480
John didn't want to punish the dog.

23:25.440 --> 23:27.680
How will I stop my dog's bad habit?

23:28.480 --> 23:29.360
John asked himself.

23:30.560 --> 23:33.040
John's friend came to talk to him about the issue.

23:34.000 --> 23:36.320
During their important meeting, his friend said,

23:37.040 --> 23:39.760
the people in the village asked me to represent them.

23:40.640 --> 23:42.560
We want your dog to stop this habit.

23:43.280 --> 23:45.520
Why don't you put a bell around the dog's neck?

23:46.400 --> 23:49.280
This way, we would hear your dog coming down the street.

23:50.160 --> 23:52.000
John thought this was a great idea.

23:52.880 --> 23:54.880
Now people could stay away from the dog.

23:55.440 --> 23:58.080
It would not be able to bite anyone anymore.

23:59.120 --> 24:00.640
The dog liked the bell too.

24:01.600 --> 24:03.600
People looked at him when they heard his bell.

24:04.560 --> 24:06.240
This made the dog very content.

24:06.960 --> 24:09.360
He liked the song the bell played when he walked.

24:10.320 --> 24:14.320
One day, John's dog strolled through the village and met some other dogs.

24:15.040 --> 24:17.200
He expected them to want a bell like his.

24:18.000 --> 24:19.280
But they laughed at his bell.

24:20.160 --> 24:22.160
They said the bell made people avoid him.

24:22.960 --> 24:24.320
John's dog shook his head.

24:25.440 --> 24:28.240
No, they look at me because they like the bell.

24:28.960 --> 24:30.000
The other dog said,

24:30.800 --> 24:33.280
you have the wrong idea of what makes you popular.

24:34.160 --> 24:35.440
Of course they like your bell.

24:36.240 --> 24:38.640
It tells them where you are so they can avoid you.

24:39.440 --> 24:41.200
You aren't able to bite them anymore.

24:42.240 --> 24:46.960
You see, being popular isn't something positive when it's for the wrong reason.

24:50.080 --> 24:54.560
Unit 5, word list, aware.

24:55.920 --> 24:58.640
If you are aware of something, you know about it.

24:59.680 --> 25:02.240
I was not aware of the ringing phone.

25:04.560 --> 25:09.200
Badly, badly means in a severe or harmful way.

25:10.480 --> 25:13.200
Be heard as armed badly playing with friends.

25:13.200 --> 25:19.440
Be long. If something belongs to you, you own it.

25:20.560 --> 25:22.560
The blue suit belongs to Paul.

25:24.720 --> 25:28.720
Continue. To continue, something is to keep doing it.

25:29.840 --> 25:33.680
She stood under her umbrella as the rain continued to fall.

25:35.920 --> 25:39.360
Error. An error is something you do wrong.

25:40.320 --> 25:44.640
I made an error on my report, so my boss was angry.

25:46.800 --> 25:51.520
Experience. An experience is something you have seen or done.

25:52.800 --> 25:55.360
Raw climbing was a fun experience.

25:57.520 --> 26:01.440
Field. A field is a big area of land.

26:02.720 --> 26:05.120
The field of flowers looks so pretty.

26:05.760 --> 26:11.760
Hurt. To hurt is to do something that makes you feel pain.

26:13.040 --> 26:15.600
She hurt her leg falling down the stairs.

26:17.760 --> 26:22.800
Judgment. Judgment is the ability to form opinions or decisions.

26:24.080 --> 26:27.280
It's good judgment to recycle your aluminum cans.

26:29.600 --> 26:34.320
Likely. If something likely happens, it will probably happen.

26:35.440 --> 26:38.880
I will likely stay at home and watch TV tonight.

26:41.120 --> 26:46.560
Normal. If something is normal, it is not strange nor surprising to you.

26:47.680 --> 26:50.400
It is normal for me to bathe every night.

26:52.640 --> 26:57.040
Rare. If something is rare, you do not see it very often.

26:58.160 --> 27:00.640
It is rare for him to miss his fight.

27:00.640 --> 27:06.000
Relax. To relax is to rest.

27:07.200 --> 27:09.600
The frog relaxed in the warm sun.

27:11.840 --> 27:16.000
Request. To request something is to ask for it.

27:17.200 --> 27:21.200
The little girl requested a special gift from Santa Claus.

27:23.360 --> 27:29.200
Reside. To reside means to live somewhere permanently or for a long time.

27:30.160 --> 27:34.880
My brother and his family reside in a lovely house on the beach.

27:37.040 --> 27:41.680
Result. A result is something that happens because of something else.

27:42.800 --> 27:47.120
As a result of all the rain, the man had to climb on the roof.

27:49.360 --> 27:53.920
Roll. To roll is to move by turning over and over.

27:55.120 --> 27:58.320
You must roll the ball into the pins when you ball.

28:00.160 --> 28:06.160
Sense. Sense is used to talk about a past event still happening now.

28:07.360 --> 28:10.800
Since 1992, he has been driving back car.

28:12.960 --> 28:16.800
Visible. If something is visible, it can be seen.

28:18.080 --> 28:21.200
The moon and stars were visible in the night sky.

28:22.560 --> 28:26.640
Wild. If something is wild, it is found in nature.

28:27.440 --> 28:32.320
You should be careful around a fox because it is a wild animal.

28:35.760 --> 28:37.760
The jackal and the sun child.

28:38.880 --> 28:42.640
A jackal is a wild dog with a big black back.

28:43.360 --> 28:48.640
It resides in the desert. But how did the jackal get his black back?

28:49.520 --> 28:51.040
This was how it happened.

28:52.000 --> 28:56.800
One day, the jackal saw a girl. She was sitting upon a rock.

28:57.360 --> 29:02.640
She was not a normal child. She was a rare and beautiful sun child.

29:03.280 --> 29:08.800
She was bright and warm like the sun. The child saw the jackal and smiled.

29:09.680 --> 29:15.120
She said, jackal, I have been relaxing on this rock for too long.

29:15.600 --> 29:23.840
I must get home soon, but I am slow and you are fast. You will likely get me home more quickly.

29:24.800 --> 29:30.800
Then she requested, will you carry me home? If you do, I'll give you a gift.

29:31.360 --> 29:35.520
This necklace belongs to me, but I will give it to you.

29:36.320 --> 29:41.440
The wild jackal agreed. So the sun child sat on the dog's back.

29:42.080 --> 29:45.600
They started to walk, but soon the jackal felt ill.

29:46.160 --> 29:52.160
The sun child was very hot on his back. The heat was hurting his back very badly.

29:53.040 --> 29:56.960
I made a terrible error in judgment, he thought.

29:57.840 --> 30:01.920
He shouldn't have agreed to carry her, so he asked her to get off.

30:02.640 --> 30:07.200
But she did not. The jackal's back continued to get harder and harder.

30:07.840 --> 30:11.680
He had to get away from the sun child, so he made a plan.

30:12.480 --> 30:18.800
First, he ran as fast as he could. He hoped the sun child would fall off, but she did not.

30:19.440 --> 30:25.360
So when the sun child was looking at the sky, not aware of the jackal's next plan,

30:25.360 --> 30:31.440
he jumped into a field of flowers. As a result, the child rolled off his back.

30:31.440 --> 30:37.440
The jackal ran away, but the sun child left a mark on the jackal's back,

30:37.440 --> 30:42.960
a visible black mark. Ever since his experience with the sun child,

30:42.960 --> 30:45.440
the jackal has had a black back.

30:49.440 --> 30:56.400
Unit 6, word list, advantage. An advantage is something that helps you.

30:57.600 --> 31:01.040
Being tall is an advantage to a basketball player.

31:02.320 --> 31:06.800
Cause. Do cause is to make something happen.

31:07.840 --> 31:10.080
The cold weather caused her to get sick.

31:12.240 --> 31:17.520
Choice. A choice is the act or possibility of picking something.

31:18.720 --> 31:21.520
I had my choice of five doors to open.

31:23.680 --> 31:28.320
Community. A community is a group of people who live together.

31:29.120 --> 31:32.880
The kids from my community usually play together.

31:35.200 --> 31:38.880
Dead. To be dead is to not be alive.

31:40.000 --> 31:43.040
A dead person is usually buried in the ground.

31:45.280 --> 31:50.560
Distance. The distance between two things is how far it is between them.

31:51.840 --> 31:58.160
The distance between the earth and the moon is 384,400 kilometers.

31:59.280 --> 32:04.560
Escape. To escape is to run away from something bad.

32:05.840 --> 32:08.800
The butterfly could not escape from the cage.

32:10.960 --> 32:14.800
Face. If you face a problem, you deal with it.

32:15.920 --> 32:20.640
My sister and I have to find a better way to face our differences.

32:22.800 --> 32:27.920
Follow. To follow means to go behind someone and go where they go.

32:29.120 --> 32:31.600
The little boy followed his mother home.

32:33.760 --> 32:37.200
Fright. Fright is the feeling of being scared.

32:38.400 --> 32:40.000
She was filled with fright.

32:42.240 --> 32:46.640
Ghost. A ghost is the spirit of a dead person.

32:47.920 --> 32:50.320
Many people are afraid of ghosts.

32:52.560 --> 32:56.560
Individual. An individual is one person.

32:57.520 --> 33:01.120
Only one individual could win the bicycle race.

33:03.280 --> 33:07.680
Pet. A pet is an animal that lives with people.

33:08.800 --> 33:12.240
Out of all my pets, the dog is my favorite.

33:14.400 --> 33:18.240
Reach. To reach means to arrive at a place.

33:19.360 --> 33:22.320
I was happy to finally reach my destination.

33:23.040 --> 33:27.680
Return. To return is to go back to a place.

33:28.480 --> 33:32.480
I was happy to return home to my mom after school.

33:34.480 --> 33:38.400
Survive. To survive is to stay alive.

33:39.440 --> 33:42.160
My dog survived her fall into the water.

33:44.160 --> 33:48.160
Upset. To be upset is to be unhappy about something.

33:49.040 --> 33:52.480
She was upset because she broke her toy.

33:54.080 --> 33:58.880
Voice. A voice is the sound a person makes when they talk or sing.

34:00.080 --> 34:04.080
He used a microphone so everyone could hear his voice.

34:05.920 --> 34:09.680
Weather. The weather is the condition of the air.

34:10.320 --> 34:12.880
Hot. Rainy. Windy. Etc.

34:14.080 --> 34:17.120
The weather can be sunny. Rainy.

34:18.240 --> 34:19.040
Or cold.

34:21.200 --> 34:27.120
Wise. To be wise is to use experience and intelligence to make good choices.

34:28.400 --> 34:32.080
Many people believe that owls are very wise animals.

34:35.600 --> 34:40.560
The Friendly Ghost. A nice woman lived by a large river.

34:41.520 --> 34:45.680
She loved children. She wanted to help them in any way.

34:46.640 --> 34:50.880
She loved her community. And everyone in the community loved her.

34:51.840 --> 34:55.520
She lived a very long time and became very wise.

34:56.480 --> 34:58.880
When she died, she became a ghost.

34:59.680 --> 35:03.360
She was dead, but every night she returned to her community.

35:04.240 --> 35:07.520
She wanted to help children and not to cause them fright.

35:08.240 --> 35:09.840
But she had a scary voice.

35:10.720 --> 35:14.160
Children were afraid of her. But the ghost was a good one.

35:15.040 --> 35:16.720
She only scared them to help them.

35:17.840 --> 35:21.520
One night, some children and a dog were playing by the river.

35:22.720 --> 35:26.400
They were having fun with their pet. But they were far from home.

35:27.520 --> 35:31.440
Then the weather became bad. It rained and rained.

35:32.400 --> 35:35.520
The river was rising. It was very dark.

35:36.320 --> 35:40.320
The children knew they were lost. They needed to go north,

35:40.320 --> 35:42.480
but they didn't know which direction it was.

35:43.440 --> 35:46.800
When the moon came out, they saw a ghost by the river.

35:47.760 --> 35:50.160
The ghost said, go away.

35:51.600 --> 35:55.520
The children felt great fright. They knew it was a ghost.

35:56.320 --> 36:00.880
Then the ghost moved closer. She yelled again, go away.

36:02.320 --> 36:06.320
The children became very upset. Some of them began to cry.

36:07.280 --> 36:10.400
The children knew they had a choice. They could escape,

36:10.960 --> 36:14.160
or they could stay and face this scary individual in the dark.

36:15.040 --> 36:17.280
The children ran a long distance away.

36:18.400 --> 36:20.080
The ghost followed them all the way.

36:21.120 --> 36:22.720
Finally, the children reached home.

36:23.600 --> 36:24.960
The ghost was very happy.

36:26.000 --> 36:30.080
Soon the river rose higher and higher. It was very dangerous.

36:31.040 --> 36:33.120
The ghost had helped the children survive.

36:34.000 --> 36:36.000
She had saved them from the rising water.

36:36.640 --> 36:38.880
She also used her power to lead them home.

36:39.760 --> 36:44.800
Sometimes, meeting a ghost has advantages. A ghost can save your life.

36:48.880 --> 36:52.640
Unit 7, word list. Allow.

36:53.840 --> 36:56.640
To allow something to happen means to let it happen.

36:57.920 --> 37:00.800
Having a ticket will allow you to enter the show.

37:03.040 --> 37:03.520
Announce.

37:04.560 --> 37:06.480
To announce something is to make it known.

37:07.440 --> 37:11.200
He announced to everyone his new idea for the company.

37:13.280 --> 37:13.840
Beside.

37:14.960 --> 37:18.240
When someone or something is beside you, they are next to you.

37:19.280 --> 37:21.520
The two brothers stood beside each other.

37:23.680 --> 37:24.160
Challenge.

37:25.280 --> 37:27.680
A challenge is something difficult to complete.

37:28.800 --> 37:31.840
It was a challenge to climb to the top of the mountain.

37:32.080 --> 37:32.880
To claim.

37:34.080 --> 37:38.240
To claim means to say that something is true.

37:39.440 --> 37:42.880
He claimed to know why the country's laws were weak.

37:44.960 --> 37:45.520
Condition.

37:46.720 --> 37:50.400
The condition of someone or something is the state that they are in.

37:51.600 --> 37:54.240
The patient's condition was very good.

37:56.320 --> 37:56.960
Contribute.

37:58.000 --> 38:01.760
To contribute to something means to do something to make it successful.

38:02.800 --> 38:06.400
We decided to contribute money to the new hospital.

38:08.480 --> 38:08.960
Difference.

38:10.080 --> 38:13.360
A difference is a way that something is not like other things.

38:14.480 --> 38:18.560
The biggest difference between the birds is the color of their feathers.

38:20.720 --> 38:21.200
Divide.

38:22.320 --> 38:25.040
To divide something is to make it into smaller parts.

38:26.160 --> 38:27.680
We divided the pizza.

38:29.760 --> 38:30.320
Expert.

38:31.280 --> 38:34.560
An expert is someone who is very good at doing something.

38:35.680 --> 38:38.080
The wizard was an expert at magic.

38:40.240 --> 38:40.720
Famous.

38:41.760 --> 38:45.360
If someone or something is famous, they are known to many people.

38:46.480 --> 38:49.520
The Eiffel Tower in Paris is very famous.

38:51.760 --> 38:52.160
Force.

38:53.280 --> 38:55.680
Force is a person's strength or power.

38:56.640 --> 39:00.160
He used all his force to try and open the door.

39:02.400 --> 39:02.800
Harm.

39:03.920 --> 39:07.520
Harm is hurt or problems caused to someone or something.

39:08.640 --> 39:12.560
A hot iron can cause great harm if you are not careful.

39:14.800 --> 39:15.120
Lay.

39:16.320 --> 39:20.400
To lay means to put or place in a horizontal or flat position.

39:21.600 --> 39:23.680
Don't lay your socks on the floor.

39:25.840 --> 39:26.240
Peace.

39:27.440 --> 39:29.040
Peace is a time without war.

39:30.240 --> 39:32.720
A white dove is a symbol for peace.

39:34.880 --> 39:35.360
Prince.

39:36.400 --> 39:38.240
A prince is the son of a king.

39:39.440 --> 39:41.760
The prince and the princess were married.

39:43.920 --> 39:44.480
Protect.

39:45.520 --> 39:48.400
To protect someone is to stop them from getting hurt.

39:49.680 --> 39:51.920
Firemen protect us from fires.

39:54.160 --> 39:54.560
Sense.

39:55.760 --> 39:58.880
To send something is to know about it without being told.

40:00.000 --> 40:02.160
I could sense that he was watching me.

40:04.400 --> 40:04.800
Sudden.

40:05.920 --> 40:08.640
When something is sudden, it happens very quickly.

40:09.760 --> 40:12.160
He felt a sudden pain in his chest.

40:14.320 --> 40:14.880
Therefore.

40:16.080 --> 40:18.240
Therefore means, for this reason.

40:19.440 --> 40:22.960
He is fat, therefore he will go on a diet.

40:26.480 --> 40:27.600
The best prince.

40:28.720 --> 40:31.120
King Minos was very sick.

40:31.120 --> 40:33.040
His condition was getting worse.

40:33.600 --> 40:35.360
He had three sons.

40:35.360 --> 40:36.400
He loved them all.

40:36.960 --> 40:39.440
He had to announce who would become king.

40:40.240 --> 40:43.520
Two of the princes stood waiting outside the king's room.

40:44.240 --> 40:47.360
Theseus was the oldest and strongest.

40:47.360 --> 40:49.600
He thought his father would make him king.

40:50.400 --> 40:53.360
Pilius, the second son, thought differently.

40:53.920 --> 40:56.240
He was an expert with weapons.

40:56.240 --> 40:58.160
He thought the king would choose him.

40:58.880 --> 41:01.760
When I'm king, Theseus told Pilius.

41:01.760 --> 41:04.880
I'll let you contribute to the defense of our country.

41:05.600 --> 41:06.880
You can lead the army.

41:07.520 --> 41:09.120
Pilius became angry.

41:09.920 --> 41:13.440
Father knows I'm famous for my sword skills.

41:13.440 --> 41:14.640
He'll make me king.

41:15.360 --> 41:17.440
You, Theseus yelled.

41:17.440 --> 41:18.560
He won't choose you.

41:19.280 --> 41:21.040
The kingdom is mine.

41:21.040 --> 41:22.080
Pilius claimed.

41:22.640 --> 41:24.640
Father will give it to me.

41:24.640 --> 41:27.040
Or I'll use force to take it.

41:27.600 --> 41:30.880
Theseus made a sudden move to take out his sword.

41:30.880 --> 41:32.480
Then Pilius did the same.

41:33.520 --> 41:37.200
Beating me will be a challenge, Theseus said.

41:37.200 --> 41:38.480
Fight me now.

41:38.480 --> 41:40.080
The winner gets the kingdom.

41:40.720 --> 41:42.320
Pilius agreed.

41:42.320 --> 41:45.200
King Minos could hear his sons fighting.

41:45.200 --> 41:48.000
The youngest son, Jason, stood beside him.

41:48.640 --> 41:50.480
He sensed his father's sadness.

41:51.200 --> 41:54.080
The king laid his hand flat on Jason's arm.

41:54.800 --> 41:56.880
Your brothers fight too much.

41:56.880 --> 41:58.240
The king told him.

41:58.240 --> 42:01.040
I must protect my kingdom from all harm.

42:01.760 --> 42:03.760
They'll divide it between them.

42:03.760 --> 42:05.680
The people won't know what to do.

42:06.320 --> 42:07.200
They'll be war.

42:07.760 --> 42:10.320
I can't allow either of them to be king.

42:11.120 --> 42:13.600
Therefore, I'm making you king.

42:14.400 --> 42:16.880
Your kindness has always made you special.

42:17.600 --> 42:20.320
It's the difference between you and your brothers.

42:20.960 --> 42:22.640
You can bring peace.

42:22.640 --> 42:23.360
They can't.

42:24.240 --> 42:25.840
Then the king died.

42:25.840 --> 42:29.280
Theseus and Pilius heard that their youngest brother was king.

42:29.920 --> 42:31.440
They were surprised.

42:31.440 --> 42:33.600
They realized that their fighting was wrong.

42:34.160 --> 42:36.880
It had kept them from saying goodbye to their father.

42:37.520 --> 42:39.600
They agreed to have Jason as their king.

42:40.400 --> 42:42.080
He was the best choice.

42:46.080 --> 42:46.720
Unidate.

42:47.280 --> 42:47.920
Wordless.

42:48.960 --> 42:49.520
Accept.

42:50.560 --> 42:53.280
To accept something that is offered is to take it.

42:54.240 --> 42:56.800
I accepted the girl's very nice gift.

42:58.880 --> 42:59.440
Arrange.

43:00.640 --> 43:03.280
To arrange things is to put them in the right place.

43:04.400 --> 43:07.760
Please arrange the bowling bins in order so we can play.

43:09.920 --> 43:10.480
Attend.

43:11.600 --> 43:13.680
To attend something is to go to it.

43:14.800 --> 43:17.520
My sister and I attend the same school.

43:18.160 --> 43:19.680
Balance.

43:19.680 --> 43:23.840
To balance something is to keep it from falling.

43:25.040 --> 43:27.920
We saw an elephant balance itself on a ball.

43:30.160 --> 43:30.800
Contrast.

43:31.840 --> 43:35.040
A contrast is the sharp difference between two things.

43:36.160 --> 43:39.520
The contrast between my parents is very noticeable.

43:41.600 --> 43:42.240
Encourage.

43:43.280 --> 43:46.320
To encourage someone is to make them want to do something.

43:47.520 --> 43:50.640
My football coach will encourage us when we are losing.

43:52.720 --> 43:53.280
Familiar.

43:54.480 --> 43:58.720
If someone or something is familiar to you, you know them well.

44:00.000 --> 44:02.800
The two friends were very familiar with each other.

44:04.960 --> 44:05.360
Grab.

44:06.560 --> 44:10.560
To grab is to take hold of someone or something suddenly.

44:11.680 --> 44:13.440
I grabbed a pair from the tree.

44:14.240 --> 44:15.200
Hang.

44:15.760 --> 44:20.240
To hang something is to keep it above the ground.

44:21.440 --> 44:25.360
I drew a picture of my family and my mother hung it on the wall.

44:27.520 --> 44:27.920
Huge.

44:29.040 --> 44:31.520
If something is huge, it is very big.

44:32.640 --> 44:35.360
At work, my father drives a huge chalk.

44:37.600 --> 44:38.240
Necessary.

44:39.360 --> 44:42.160
If something is necessary, you must do it.

44:43.120 --> 44:47.520
It is necessary to have a passport when you travel to a foreign country.

44:49.600 --> 44:50.080
Pattern.

44:51.200 --> 44:54.800
A pattern is a way in which something is done or organized.

44:55.920 --> 44:59.920
My pattern of brushing my teeth is the same as most people's.

45:02.080 --> 45:02.720
Propose.

45:03.840 --> 45:06.480
To propose something is to say that it should be done.

45:07.760 --> 45:11.920
Santa Claus proposed that I try to be a good boy all year.

45:12.640 --> 45:13.600
Purpose.

45:14.240 --> 45:18.240
A purpose is the reason that you do something.

45:19.440 --> 45:22.480
The purpose of exercising is to get into shape.

45:24.640 --> 45:25.120
Release.

45:26.240 --> 45:28.640
To release something is to stop holding it.

45:29.760 --> 45:31.840
She released the bird from her hands.

45:34.080 --> 45:34.640
Require.

45:35.760 --> 45:39.360
To require something is to say that it is necessary.

45:40.240 --> 45:43.680
We require teachers to have a university degree.

45:46.000 --> 45:46.400
Single.

45:47.520 --> 45:50.160
If something is single, then there is only one.

45:51.360 --> 45:53.600
I have a single key in my hand.

45:55.760 --> 45:56.320
Success.

45:57.520 --> 46:00.640
Success is doing something well that you choose to do.

46:01.920 --> 46:04.480
My daughter was a big success at school.

46:05.120 --> 46:06.240
Terror.

46:06.560 --> 46:10.160
To tear something means to pull it apart.

46:11.280 --> 46:13.120
It is easy to tear paper.

46:15.280 --> 46:15.680
Theory.

46:16.800 --> 46:19.520
A theory is an idea about how something works.

46:20.720 --> 46:24.400
We talked about Einstein's theory of relativity in class.

46:27.840 --> 46:30.000
How the sun and the moon were made.

46:30.800 --> 46:34.800
Do you ever wonder where the moon and the sun came from?

46:35.760 --> 46:38.160
The Inuit people of Alaska have a theory.

46:39.280 --> 46:41.520
They tell a story about a beautiful girl.

46:42.480 --> 46:43.600
She was very nice.

46:44.480 --> 46:47.840
In contrast, her brother was a mean little boy.

46:48.800 --> 46:50.560
One day he proposed something.

46:51.520 --> 46:54.080
We should go to a party, he said.

46:54.880 --> 46:55.840
The girl accepted.

46:56.480 --> 46:58.800
First it was necessary for her to prepare.

46:59.600 --> 47:02.080
She arranged her hair and put on nice clothes.

47:02.960 --> 47:04.560
This required a lot of time.

47:05.520 --> 47:08.800
But the girl worked hard and soon she had success.

47:09.600 --> 47:10.720
She looked perfect.

47:11.840 --> 47:13.360
They attended the party together.

47:14.320 --> 47:15.680
The girl was having fun.

47:16.560 --> 47:18.320
Later she walked into the bathroom.

47:19.280 --> 47:21.200
Suddenly the lights were turned off.

47:22.000 --> 47:24.800
Someone grabbed her hair and tore her clothes.

47:25.680 --> 47:26.960
She ran out of the bathroom.

47:27.760 --> 47:29.520
She wanted to know who did this to her.

47:30.480 --> 47:31.680
Then she had an idea.

47:32.480 --> 47:33.680
She fixed her hair again.

47:34.640 --> 47:36.400
This time it was even more beautiful.

47:37.280 --> 47:39.520
She even balanced beautiful jewels in it.

47:40.480 --> 47:43.040
She wanted to encourage the person to grab it again.

47:44.240 --> 47:45.840
She put black dirt in her hair.

47:46.800 --> 47:48.960
The purpose of this was to catch the person.

47:49.920 --> 47:52.960
She went to the bathroom again and it was the same pattern.

47:53.600 --> 47:56.240
The lights went off and someone grabbed her hair.

47:57.040 --> 47:59.280
When he released it, his hand was black.

48:00.240 --> 48:01.680
The girl returned to the party.

48:02.640 --> 48:05.440
She knew there was only a single person with a black hand.

48:06.160 --> 48:09.120
When she saw that person, he was very familiar.

48:09.760 --> 48:10.800
It was her brother.

48:11.760 --> 48:12.960
He ran into the woods.

48:13.520 --> 48:14.720
The girl ran after him.

48:15.360 --> 48:17.680
They both carried fire so they could see in the dark.

48:18.480 --> 48:19.840
The smoke went into the air.

48:20.640 --> 48:22.000
As they ran they grew.

48:22.880 --> 48:23.920
They became huge.

48:24.720 --> 48:26.000
Then they went into space.

48:26.960 --> 48:29.680
When the girl's fire went out, she hung in the sky.

48:30.480 --> 48:31.440
She became the moon.

48:32.080 --> 48:33.440
And her brother became the sun.

48:34.400 --> 48:35.760
They chase each other forever.

48:39.840 --> 48:40.560
Unit 9.

48:41.280 --> 48:41.840
Wordlessed.

48:43.040 --> 48:43.600
Against.

48:44.720 --> 48:48.480
To be against something is to be touching it or opposed to it.

48:49.680 --> 48:51.680
They both leaned against the wall.

48:53.920 --> 48:54.320
Beach.

48:55.280 --> 48:58.480
The beach is a sandy or rocky place by the ocean.

48:59.520 --> 49:02.720
The little girl built a sand castle on the beach.

49:04.880 --> 49:05.440
Damage.

49:06.480 --> 49:08.320
To damage something is to break it.

49:09.360 --> 49:11.680
The car was damaged in the accident.

49:13.840 --> 49:14.400
Discover.

49:15.520 --> 49:18.160
To discover something is to find it for the first time.

49:19.280 --> 49:22.240
I discovered some new information in this book.

49:24.480 --> 49:24.960
Emotion.

49:26.160 --> 49:27.680
An emotion is how you feel.

49:28.880 --> 49:32.000
Anger is a common emotion that we all feel.

49:34.240 --> 49:34.640
Fix.

49:35.760 --> 49:37.760
To fix something is to make it work.

49:38.880 --> 49:42.560
My dad has many tools to help him fix broken things.

49:44.800 --> 49:45.200
Frank.

49:46.240 --> 49:48.640
If you are Frank, you are being very honest.

49:49.840 --> 49:52.800
The teacher had a frank discussion with their students.

49:54.960 --> 49:55.760
Identify.

49:56.800 --> 49:59.360
To identify something is to be able to name it.

50:00.480 --> 50:03.280
I use the file to identify his name.

50:05.520 --> 50:06.000
Island.

50:07.040 --> 50:09.360
An island is land in the middle of water.

50:10.560 --> 50:12.640
Japan is a group of islands.

50:14.800 --> 50:15.200
Ocean.

50:16.400 --> 50:19.600
The ocean is all of the salt water that surrounds land.

50:20.800 --> 50:23.040
The ocean can make powerful waves.

50:25.200 --> 50:25.760
Perhaps.

50:26.960 --> 50:29.680
Perhaps is used when you say that something could happen.

50:30.880 --> 50:33.440
Perhaps I will eat an apple for lunch.

50:35.600 --> 50:36.080
Pleasant.

50:37.200 --> 50:39.360
If something is pleasant, you enjoy it.

50:40.480 --> 50:43.360
The character had a pleasant look on its face.

50:45.600 --> 50:46.000
Prevent.

50:47.200 --> 50:49.600
To prevent something is to stop it from happening.

50:50.720 --> 50:53.760
The handcuffs prevented me from moving my hands.

50:55.120 --> 50:56.400
Rock.

50:57.440 --> 50:59.280
A rock is a hard thing in the dirt.

51:00.400 --> 51:02.800
I stacked rocks on top of one another.

51:05.040 --> 51:05.440
Save.

51:06.560 --> 51:09.040
To save something is to keep it from being hurt.

51:10.160 --> 51:12.160
I want to help save the world.

51:14.320 --> 51:14.720
Step.

51:15.840 --> 51:17.360
To step is to walk.

51:18.560 --> 51:20.320
Be careful where you step.

51:21.040 --> 51:21.520
Step.

51:22.560 --> 51:22.880
Still.

51:24.240 --> 51:27.440
Still is used when you say that a situation keeps going on.

51:28.640 --> 51:31.200
They are still waiting in line to get tickets.

51:33.440 --> 51:33.840
Taste.

51:34.960 --> 51:37.600
A taste is the flavor something makes in your mouth.

51:38.800 --> 51:40.720
The taste of the fruit was sweet.

51:42.880 --> 51:43.280
Throw.

51:44.480 --> 51:48.160
To throw something is to use your hand to make it go through the air.

51:49.120 --> 51:52.240
The pitcher can throw the baseball very fast.

51:54.480 --> 51:54.880
Wave.

51:56.000 --> 51:59.600
A wave is a line of water that moves higher than the rest of the water.

52:00.640 --> 52:03.760
The water was filled with large blue waves.

52:07.360 --> 52:08.240
The starfish.

52:09.520 --> 52:12.320
Last summer I took a trip to an island.

52:12.880 --> 52:14.320
I had a lot of fun.

52:14.800 --> 52:18.160
I sat and watched the waves and listened to the ocean.

52:18.800 --> 52:20.720
I learned to identify birds.

52:21.280 --> 52:25.760
I discovered pretty things and enjoyed the taste of new foods.

52:25.760 --> 52:27.440
It was a very nice time.

52:28.240 --> 52:31.200
One evening I took a pleasant walk by the ocean.

52:31.920 --> 52:35.760
When the waves came in many starfish fell on the beach.

52:36.400 --> 52:40.080
Some starfish went back into the water and they were safe.

52:40.800 --> 52:43.520
But other starfish were still on the sand.

52:44.160 --> 52:46.880
They would die if they did not get into the water.

52:47.600 --> 52:50.240
There were many starfish on the beach that night.

52:50.720 --> 52:54.480
It made me sad but I knew I could not fix the problem.

52:54.960 --> 52:58.320
I stepped very carefully so I did not damage them.

52:59.040 --> 53:00.880
Then I saw little girl.

53:01.520 --> 53:03.840
She was also sad about the starfish.

53:04.560 --> 53:07.280
She wanted to prevent all of them from dying.

53:08.000 --> 53:10.320
She asked me if I could perhaps help her.

53:11.120 --> 53:14.480
To be frank I don't think we can do anything I said.

53:15.200 --> 53:17.040
The little girl started to cry.

53:17.600 --> 53:20.560
She sat back against a rock and thought for a while.

53:21.520 --> 53:23.680
Finally the emotion was gone.

53:24.160 --> 53:25.920
She stopped crying and stood up.

53:27.120 --> 53:30.240
Then she picked up a starfish and threw it into the water.

53:31.040 --> 53:32.080
What are you doing?

53:32.080 --> 53:35.120
I asked her but she did not answer me.

53:35.120 --> 53:37.920
She just threw as many starfish as she could.

53:38.480 --> 53:40.560
You cannot save all of them.

53:40.560 --> 53:41.120
I said.

53:41.680 --> 53:43.040
She stopped to look at me.

53:43.760 --> 53:45.840
No I cannot save them all.

53:45.840 --> 53:46.560
She replied.

53:47.040 --> 53:49.680
Then she picked up a very big starfish and said

53:50.240 --> 53:51.680
but I can save this one.

53:52.400 --> 53:57.520
And then she smiled and threw the starfish as far as she could into the ocean.

54:01.520 --> 54:02.160
Unit 10.

54:02.800 --> 54:03.440
Word list.

54:04.720 --> 54:05.280
Benefit

54:06.240 --> 54:07.920
A benefit is a good thing.

54:09.200 --> 54:12.240
Being able to fly is a good benefit to burns.

54:14.480 --> 54:14.880
Certain.

54:16.080 --> 54:18.880
If you are certain about something you know it is true.

54:20.080 --> 54:22.640
I am certain that seaburs have stripes.

54:24.800 --> 54:25.200
Chance.

54:26.400 --> 54:28.720
A chance is an opportunity to do something.

54:29.920 --> 54:33.520
I had a chance to see the Roman Colosseum last summer.

54:35.600 --> 54:36.080
Effect.

54:37.200 --> 54:39.760
An effect is a change made by something else.

54:40.880 --> 54:43.440
The medicine had a good effect on the boy.

54:45.680 --> 54:46.240
Essential.

54:47.280 --> 54:50.480
If something is essential it is very important and necessary.

54:51.520 --> 54:54.720
It is essential to have oxygen when you scuba dive.

54:56.960 --> 54:57.280
Far.

54:58.320 --> 55:00.640
If something is far it is not close.

55:01.280 --> 55:05.520
It is far going from the east coast to the west coast of America.

55:07.680 --> 55:08.160
Focus.

55:09.280 --> 55:12.800
To focus on something is to think about it and pay attention to it.

55:14.000 --> 55:17.440
My mom always helps me to focus on my school work.

55:19.520 --> 55:20.000
Function.

55:21.200 --> 55:23.280
The function of something is what it does.

55:24.480 --> 55:28.240
The function of a flashlight is to help you see in the dark.

55:28.880 --> 55:29.840
Grass.

55:30.800 --> 55:33.760
Grass is the green leaves that cover the ground.

55:34.400 --> 55:36.720
The grass looks so soft and green.

55:38.640 --> 55:39.440
Guard.

55:40.400 --> 55:42.640
To guard something is to take care of it.

55:43.600 --> 55:46.640
The police officer will guard us from any harm.

55:48.480 --> 55:49.040
Image.

55:50.240 --> 55:52.480
The image of something is a picture of it.

55:53.440 --> 55:56.240
The image of her eye was very clear.

55:59.200 --> 55:59.840
Immediate.

56:00.880 --> 56:03.200
If something is immediate it happens quickly.

56:04.320 --> 56:07.520
An immediate response came from the pizza place.

56:09.680 --> 56:10.240
Primary.

56:11.280 --> 56:14.240
If something is primary it is the most important thing.

56:15.440 --> 56:17.840
His primary thoughts are about money.

56:20.000 --> 56:20.400
Proud.

56:21.520 --> 56:24.720
If someone feels proud they are happy about what they have done.

56:25.520 --> 56:28.960
She is proud of the picture she drew of her house.

56:31.120 --> 56:31.600
Remain.

56:32.800 --> 56:34.800
To remain somewhere is to stay there.

56:36.000 --> 56:39.040
My sister had to remain home since she was sick.

56:41.200 --> 56:41.600
Rest.

56:42.720 --> 56:46.720
To rest is to stop being active while the body gets back at strength.

56:47.760 --> 56:50.080
I rested on the couch after work.

56:52.240 --> 56:52.720
Separate.

56:53.360 --> 56:56.320
If two things are separate they are not together.

56:57.520 --> 57:01.440
New York and Los Angeles are in two separate parts of America.

57:03.680 --> 57:04.080
Sight.

57:05.200 --> 57:06.480
A sight is a place.

57:07.680 --> 57:10.080
We found the perfect sight for our picnic.

57:12.240 --> 57:12.640
Tail.

57:13.840 --> 57:16.000
A tail is a part of an animal's body.

57:16.480 --> 57:18.320
Sticking out from its rear or back.

57:19.520 --> 57:22.240
Our dog wags its tail when it's happy.

57:23.520 --> 57:24.800
Trouble.

57:26.000 --> 57:28.080
Trouble is a problem or a difficulty.

57:29.200 --> 57:31.440
I have trouble working with my boss.

57:34.960 --> 57:36.080
The first peacock.

57:37.280 --> 57:39.200
Argos lived in ancient Greece.

57:40.000 --> 57:42.080
He was a husband and a proud father.

57:42.800 --> 57:44.960
He worked hard and did well at his job.

57:45.920 --> 57:47.840
But one thing about him wasn't normal.

57:48.800 --> 57:50.480
He was born with 100 eyes.

57:51.440 --> 57:54.400
Having many eyes was usually a benefit to him.

57:55.360 --> 57:57.280
He had a chance to see many things.

57:58.400 --> 58:02.800
Also, since he had so many eyes, he was very good at guarding things.

58:03.440 --> 58:06.560
While sleeping, he only rested a few eyes at a time.

58:07.440 --> 58:08.480
The others stayed awake.

58:09.200 --> 58:11.600
He worked for Hera, a great goddess.

58:12.240 --> 58:15.040
His primary function was to guard a special cow.

58:15.600 --> 58:17.520
The cow was very important to Hera.

58:18.160 --> 58:19.360
It was her favorite pet.

58:20.000 --> 58:23.120
The most essential part of his job was to keep the cow alone.

58:23.760 --> 58:28.160
It had to be kept separate from all the other cows and far away from people.

58:29.200 --> 58:31.040
This was an easy job for Argos.

58:32.000 --> 58:33.760
The cow just ate grass all day.

58:34.720 --> 58:36.560
But the god Zeus wanted the cow.

58:37.440 --> 58:39.280
He wanted to take it away from Hera.

58:40.240 --> 58:40.960
He had a plan.

58:42.160 --> 58:43.920
He found a great music player.

58:45.120 --> 58:47.840
He asked the man to play a beautiful song for Argos.

58:48.800 --> 58:51.200
Zeus was certain Argos would go to sleep.

58:52.400 --> 58:54.240
The song had an immediate effect.

58:54.960 --> 58:56.800
Argos couldn't focus on his job.

58:57.760 --> 58:58.640
He fell asleep.

58:59.760 --> 59:01.920
Zeus saw this and he took the cow.

59:02.800 --> 59:04.960
Hera was very angry with Argos.

59:05.840 --> 59:07.360
She turned him into a peacock.

59:08.240 --> 59:10.160
She put his many eyes on his tail.

59:11.360 --> 59:12.720
Argos was very sad.

59:13.920 --> 59:16.400
Zeus saw how much trouble he had caused Argos.

59:17.040 --> 59:18.640
He made another plan.

59:19.440 --> 59:21.520
He turned Argos into a group of stars.

59:22.560 --> 59:24.960
He wanted Argos to remain in the sky forever.

59:26.000 --> 59:28.720
Even today, Argos' image remains there.

59:29.280 --> 59:31.520
Above the site where all his problems began.

59:32.400 --> 59:34.160
We can still see him in the night sky.

59:38.240 --> 59:38.960
Unit 11.

59:39.680 --> 59:40.240
Wordlessed.

59:41.360 --> 59:41.920
Anymore.

59:43.120 --> 59:44.800
Anymore means any longer.

59:45.760 --> 59:48.240
Her old pants don't fit her anymore.

59:50.320 --> 59:50.880
A sleep.

59:51.920 --> 59:54.240
When a person is asleep, they are not awake.

59:55.440 --> 59:57.760
The baby has been asleep for hours.

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:00.480
Berry.

01:00:01.600 --> 01:00:05.600
A berry is a small round fruit that grows on certain plants and trees.

01:00:06.800 --> 01:00:08.480
The berry looked delicious.

01:00:10.720 --> 01:00:11.200
Collect.

01:00:12.160 --> 01:00:15.600
To collect things is to group them together all in one place.

01:00:16.720 --> 01:00:19.200
I collected shells when I was younger.

01:00:21.360 --> 01:00:21.840
Compete.

01:00:23.040 --> 01:00:25.680
To compete is to try to be better than someone.

01:00:26.800 --> 01:00:29.440
He will compete with very good athletes.

01:00:31.600 --> 01:00:32.320
Conversation.

01:00:33.440 --> 01:00:35.680
A conversation is a talk between people.

01:00:36.880 --> 01:00:40.000
There were two conversations going on at once.

01:00:42.160 --> 01:00:42.720
Creature.

01:00:43.840 --> 01:00:45.600
A creature is any living thing.

01:00:46.800 --> 01:00:50.880
The creature we saw today was either a dolphin or a porpoise.

01:00:53.040 --> 01:00:53.520
Decision.

01:00:54.720 --> 01:00:56.240
A decision is a choice.

01:00:57.440 --> 01:00:59.040
Be made the wrong decision.

01:01:01.200 --> 01:01:01.600
Either.

01:01:02.800 --> 01:01:07.360
Either is used with ore to say there are two or more possibilities.

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:12.480
You can choose to be either white or black when you play chess.

01:01:14.640 --> 01:01:15.120
Forest.

01:01:16.240 --> 01:01:19.200
A forest is a place with lots of trees and animals.

01:01:20.320 --> 01:01:22.560
I love to go walking in the forest.

01:01:24.720 --> 01:01:25.200
Ground.

01:01:26.320 --> 01:01:29.040
The ground is the top part of the earth that we walk on.

01:01:30.240 --> 01:01:33.520
The ground under our feet was dry and brown.

01:01:34.160 --> 01:01:35.680
Introduce.

01:01:35.680 --> 01:01:40.480
To introduce someone or something is to say who they are.

01:01:41.680 --> 01:01:45.120
I introduced myself to our newest coworker today.

01:01:47.360 --> 01:01:47.760
Mary.

01:01:48.960 --> 01:01:51.760
To marry is to legally become husband and wife.

01:01:52.880 --> 01:01:56.000
Rose and Henry were married and they lived happily.

01:01:58.080 --> 01:01:58.560
Prepare.

01:01:59.680 --> 01:02:01.760
To prepare is to get ready for something.

01:02:02.400 --> 01:02:05.040
I prepared my speech to the class.

01:02:07.360 --> 01:02:07.760
Sail.

01:02:08.880 --> 01:02:11.360
To sail is to move a boat on the water.

01:02:12.480 --> 01:02:14.880
I love to sail my boat on the lake.

01:02:17.120 --> 01:02:17.600
Serious.

01:02:18.720 --> 01:02:21.920
When something is serious, it is bad or unsafe.

01:02:23.040 --> 01:02:25.200
The accident was very serious.

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:26.960
Spend.

01:02:27.600 --> 01:02:33.040
To spend is to use time doing something or being somewhere.

01:02:34.160 --> 01:02:36.560
I like to spend my free time fishing.

01:02:38.880 --> 01:02:39.360
Strange.

01:02:40.480 --> 01:02:42.800
When something is strange, it is not normal.

01:02:44.000 --> 01:02:48.160
Joe had a strange look on his face after he saw what happened.

01:02:50.400 --> 01:02:50.720
Truth.

01:02:51.840 --> 01:02:54.480
The truth is a fact or something that is right.

01:02:55.520 --> 01:02:59.040
He was telling the truth about seeing a large green snake.

01:03:01.200 --> 01:03:01.520
Wake.

01:03:02.640 --> 01:03:04.880
To wake is to not be sleeping anymore.

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:09.360
He is always full of energy when he wakes in the morning.

01:03:12.800 --> 01:03:14.720
Princess Rose and the creature.

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:18.880
There was once a beautiful princess named Rose.

01:03:19.440 --> 01:03:23.840
Her mother, the queen, however, was not as beautiful as the princess.

01:03:24.480 --> 01:03:29.360
The queen felt bad that she was not the most beautiful woman in the kingdom anymore.

01:03:30.080 --> 01:03:32.480
She was tired of competing with her daughter.

01:03:33.360 --> 01:03:34.720
She made a decision.

01:03:35.440 --> 01:03:37.520
She prepared a drink for the princess.

01:03:38.160 --> 01:03:40.880
After the princess drank it, she fell asleep.

01:03:41.680 --> 01:03:44.080
Then the queen took the princess to the forest.

01:03:44.640 --> 01:03:46.480
She left the princess there.

01:03:46.480 --> 01:03:48.560
It was a very serious thing to do.

01:03:49.200 --> 01:03:53.600
Either she will be killed by animals or she will get lost in the forest.

01:03:54.080 --> 01:03:57.040
The queen thought the princess had a dream.

01:03:57.040 --> 01:04:00.880
She dreamed about a man with brown hair and brown eyes.

01:04:00.880 --> 01:04:02.960
It was the man she would went.

01:04:02.960 --> 01:04:04.640
The princess woke up.

01:04:04.640 --> 01:04:07.680
She saw a strange creature on the ground.

01:04:07.680 --> 01:04:10.880
It looked like a man, but he was hairy and green.

01:04:11.680 --> 01:04:14.640
He had horns on his head and a pig's nose.

01:04:15.280 --> 01:04:16.240
The creature said,

01:04:17.040 --> 01:04:18.800
Did I scare you?

01:04:18.800 --> 01:04:20.080
I hope not.

01:04:20.080 --> 01:04:22.080
Let me introduce myself.

01:04:22.080 --> 01:04:23.440
I am Henry.

01:04:23.520 --> 01:04:25.120
I am not scared.

01:04:25.120 --> 01:04:28.480
To tell you the truth, I think you are cute.

01:04:28.480 --> 01:04:29.520
Said Rose.

01:04:29.520 --> 01:04:32.400
Rose and Henry spent the day together.

01:04:32.400 --> 01:04:36.240
They collected berries, caught fish and had lunch.

01:04:36.240 --> 01:04:40.000
They had a very good day filled with nice conversations.

01:04:41.120 --> 01:04:43.840
Rose, I have to go home.

01:04:43.840 --> 01:04:47.120
Said Henry, my ship will sail home soon.

01:04:47.120 --> 01:04:50.160
I can't leave you here in the forest alone.

01:04:50.160 --> 01:04:51.440
Will you come with me?

01:04:52.160 --> 01:04:53.600
Rose was very happy.

01:04:54.240 --> 01:04:57.040
She gave Henry a kiss right on his pig nose.

01:04:57.680 --> 01:05:00.880
As soon as she kissed Henry, he began to change.

01:05:01.600 --> 01:05:04.480
His pig nose turned into a man's nose.

01:05:04.480 --> 01:05:06.960
His horns and green hair went away.

01:05:07.680 --> 01:05:11.360
Standing in front of her was the man Rose had dreamt about.

01:05:11.920 --> 01:05:15.360
Rose and Henry were married and they lived happily.

01:05:15.920 --> 01:05:22.240
Unit 12, word list, alone.

01:05:22.240 --> 01:05:25.920
If someone is alone, they are not with another person.

01:05:25.920 --> 01:05:28.720
The boy wanted to be alone to think.

01:05:30.720 --> 01:05:31.760
Apartment.

01:05:31.760 --> 01:05:35.920
An apartment is a set of rooms in a building where people live.

01:05:35.920 --> 01:05:39.200
She has a nice apartment in the city.

01:05:39.840 --> 01:05:40.720
Article.

01:05:40.720 --> 01:05:44.480
An article is a story in a newspaper or magazine.

01:05:45.680 --> 01:05:49.120
Did you read the article in the newspaper about the soccer game?

01:05:50.640 --> 01:05:52.080
Artist.

01:05:52.720 --> 01:05:56.960
An artist is a person who paints, draws or makes sculptures.

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:00.960
He went to Paris to become an artist.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:03.040
Attitude.

01:06:04.000 --> 01:06:05.120
Someone's attitude.

01:06:05.120 --> 01:06:06.400
Someone's attitude.

01:06:06.400 --> 01:06:07.040
Attitude.

01:06:08.160 --> 01:06:10.960
Someone's attitude is the way they feel and think.

01:06:12.160 --> 01:06:14.080
John has a bad attitude.

01:06:14.080 --> 01:06:15.440
He's always angry.

01:06:17.520 --> 01:06:18.000
Compare.

01:06:19.200 --> 01:06:23.200
To compare means to say how two things are the same and different.

01:06:24.320 --> 01:06:28.640
If you compare cats and dogs, you'll see that they're both good pets.

01:06:30.800 --> 01:06:31.200
Judge.

01:06:32.240 --> 01:06:34.960
To judge something is to say if it is good or bad.

01:06:35.600 --> 01:06:39.680
The boy was going to judge how his mother's turkey tasted.

01:06:41.840 --> 01:06:42.400
Magazine.

01:06:43.600 --> 01:06:47.840
A magazine is a regular publication with news, stories and articles.

01:06:48.960 --> 01:06:51.120
She likes to read fashion magazines.

01:06:53.280 --> 01:06:53.840
Material.

01:06:54.880 --> 01:06:57.040
A material is what is used to make something.

01:06:58.320 --> 01:07:01.280
Brick is a good material for building houses.

01:07:01.600 --> 01:07:02.400
A meal.

01:07:03.600 --> 01:07:09.360
A meal is a time when food is eaten, like breakfast, lunch or dinner.

01:07:10.560 --> 01:07:14.640
Breakfast is my favorite meal because I enjoy breakfast foods.

01:07:16.880 --> 01:07:17.280
Method.

01:07:18.320 --> 01:07:20.160
A method is the way to do something.

01:07:21.360 --> 01:07:26.160
One method to remember things is to tie a string around your finger.

01:07:28.320 --> 01:07:28.720
Neighbor.

01:07:29.520 --> 01:07:31.840
A neighbor is a person who lives near you.

01:07:32.880 --> 01:07:35.760
I like my neighbor because he's very friendly.

01:07:37.840 --> 01:07:38.560
Professional.

01:07:39.680 --> 01:07:43.760
If something is professional, it deals with work that uses special skills.

01:07:44.880 --> 01:07:48.480
If you want to be a pilot, you must have professional training.

01:07:50.720 --> 01:07:51.120
Profit.

01:07:52.240 --> 01:07:55.040
A profit is the extra money you make when you sell something.

01:07:56.000 --> 01:07:59.520
I made a small profit from selling my old clothes.

01:08:01.600 --> 01:08:02.160
Quality.

01:08:03.200 --> 01:08:05.200
The quality of something is how good it is.

01:08:06.320 --> 01:08:09.120
The quality of his car is very good.

01:08:11.280 --> 01:08:11.600
Shape.

01:08:12.640 --> 01:08:15.680
A shape is a simple form like a square or circle.

01:08:16.720 --> 01:08:18.960
The triangle is my favorite shape.

01:08:21.120 --> 01:08:21.520
Space.

01:08:22.640 --> 01:08:24.400
A space is an empty area.

01:08:25.520 --> 01:08:28.560
I don't have much space for things in my small house.

01:08:30.800 --> 01:08:31.200
Stare.

01:08:32.400 --> 01:08:35.360
Stairs are the things that are used to go up in a building.

01:08:36.480 --> 01:08:38.880
You can take the stairs to the second floor.

01:08:41.200 --> 01:08:41.600
Symbol.

01:08:42.800 --> 01:08:45.360
A symbol is a thing that stands for something else.

01:08:46.480 --> 01:08:49.840
This symbol tells us that we cannot smoke in this area.

01:08:50.480 --> 01:08:56.480
Then, if someone or something is thin, they are not fat.

01:08:57.680 --> 01:09:00.480
The man was thin because he didn't eat much.

01:09:04.080 --> 01:09:05.360
The crazy artist.

01:09:06.720 --> 01:09:09.440
Friendofer was the best artist in the world.

01:09:10.240 --> 01:09:11.280
Everyone loved him.

01:09:12.080 --> 01:09:14.560
The quality of his paintings was very high.

01:09:15.360 --> 01:09:17.600
He always used the best materials.

01:09:18.480 --> 01:09:20.560
He made a big profit from his paintings.

01:09:21.200 --> 01:09:23.680
He had delicious meals with his rich neighbors.

01:09:24.320 --> 01:09:25.600
He taught art classes.

01:09:26.320 --> 01:09:27.120
Life was good.

01:09:28.160 --> 01:09:29.760
Then his attitude changed.

01:09:30.400 --> 01:09:32.480
He stopped selling paintings and teaching.

01:09:33.200 --> 01:09:34.800
He tried a new method of painting.

01:09:35.840 --> 01:09:38.000
He stayed alone in his apartment all day.

01:09:38.720 --> 01:09:41.680
He worked all day and all night, rarely eating.

01:09:42.560 --> 01:09:44.480
Soon, Friendofer became very thin.

01:09:45.360 --> 01:09:48.240
But he kept working on the same paintings for many years.

01:09:49.200 --> 01:09:50.560
He worked as hard as he could.

01:09:51.520 --> 01:09:53.520
Finally, he finished the painting.

01:09:54.240 --> 01:09:57.120
He was very happy and invited other artists to see it.

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:00.080
I want your professional opinion, he said.

01:10:00.880 --> 01:10:04.000
He wanted them to judge it and compare it to other paintings.

01:10:04.800 --> 01:10:08.640
Everyone was very excited as they went up the stairs to his apartment.

01:10:09.360 --> 01:10:11.520
Friendofer was excited to show his painting.

01:10:12.080 --> 01:10:13.840
And the artists were excited to see it.

01:10:14.720 --> 01:10:16.560
They'll love it, he thought.

01:10:17.520 --> 01:10:18.960
But they did not.

01:10:19.920 --> 01:10:21.680
They were surprised by his painting.

01:10:22.560 --> 01:10:24.080
There was no white anywhere.

01:10:24.960 --> 01:10:28.000
Friendofer filled the whole painting with lines and colors.

01:10:28.960 --> 01:10:30.960
There was no space for a normal picture.

01:10:31.680 --> 01:10:33.280
It was full of strange shapes.

01:10:34.160 --> 01:10:36.000
It looked bad to the other artists.

01:10:36.960 --> 01:10:39.520
He used symbols and they didn't understand them.

01:10:40.480 --> 01:10:41.680
They thought it was terrible.

01:10:42.640 --> 01:10:44.400
Why did you paint this strange picture?

01:10:44.960 --> 01:10:45.600
Someone asked.

01:10:46.240 --> 01:10:47.760
They didn't understand its beauty.

01:10:48.720 --> 01:10:52.080
But after some time, many people began to like his painting.

01:10:52.720 --> 01:10:54.880
People wrote articles about it in magazines.

01:10:55.680 --> 01:10:56.960
They said it was his best work.

01:10:57.680 --> 01:10:59.120
They loved his strange symbols.

01:11:00.000 --> 01:11:01.360
They loved his strange colors.

01:11:02.000 --> 01:11:05.840
Friendofer's painting reminded everyone that just because something was new,

01:11:06.400 --> 01:11:07.600
didn't mean that it was bad.

01:11:08.160 --> 01:11:12.160
He also helped them to realize that sometimes it takes people a little time

01:11:12.160 --> 01:11:13.760
to understand great things.

01:11:17.680 --> 01:11:18.560
Unit 13.

01:11:19.200 --> 01:11:19.840
Word List

01:11:21.040 --> 01:11:21.520
Blood

