Blood is the red liquid in your body.

01:11:25.680 --> 01:11:28.640
I cut my finger and got blood on my shirt.

01:11:30.880 --> 01:11:31.200
Burn

01:11:32.400 --> 01:11:34.640
To burn something is to set it on fire.

01:11:34.640 --> 01:11:37.840
I burn some wood in the campfire.

01:11:40.080 --> 01:11:40.400
Cell

01:11:41.600 --> 01:11:44.640
A cell is a small room where a person is locked in.

01:11:45.840 --> 01:11:47.840
The jail cell was very small.

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:50.560
Contain

01:11:51.760 --> 01:11:53.920
To contain something is to have it inside.

01:11:55.120 --> 01:11:57.040
The mailbox contained a letter.

01:11:59.120 --> 01:11:59.680
Correct

01:12:00.720 --> 01:12:02.320
To be correct is to be right.

01:12:03.280 --> 01:12:06.080
All of my answers on the test were correct.

01:12:08.240 --> 01:12:08.640
Crop

01:12:09.760 --> 01:12:12.000
A crop is food that a farmer grows.

01:12:13.280 --> 01:12:15.760
Weed is a crop that is made into bread.

01:12:18.000 --> 01:12:18.480
Demand

01:12:19.680 --> 01:12:22.560
To demand something is to say strongly that you want it.

01:12:23.600 --> 01:12:26.160
The workers demanded to be paid more money.

01:12:28.320 --> 01:12:28.720
Equal

01:12:29.840 --> 01:12:31.520
To be equal is to be the same.

01:12:32.880 --> 01:12:35.040
Both students are equal in age.

01:12:37.280 --> 01:12:37.600
Feed

01:12:38.800 --> 01:12:40.240
To feed is to give food.

01:12:41.520 --> 01:12:44.240
Mother feeds my baby brother every day.

01:12:46.400 --> 01:12:46.720
Hole

01:12:47.920 --> 01:12:49.680
A hole is an opening in something.

01:12:50.880 --> 01:12:54.000
The man was going to jump into the hole in the eyes.

01:12:56.240 --> 01:12:56.800
Increase

01:12:57.920 --> 01:13:00.640
To increase something is to make it larger or more.

01:13:01.600 --> 01:13:04.960
They've increased the price of gas by 15 cents.

01:13:07.200 --> 01:13:07.680
Lord

01:13:08.880 --> 01:13:12.000
Long ago a Lord was a man in charge of a town.

01:13:13.200 --> 01:13:15.520
The Lord of the town was not kind.

01:13:17.680 --> 01:13:18.000
Oh

01:13:19.120 --> 01:13:23.520
To owe is to have to pay or give back something received from another.

01:13:24.560 --> 01:13:27.600
I owed him $20 so I paid him back.

01:13:28.240 --> 01:13:30.240
Position

01:13:31.440 --> 01:13:33.600
A position is the way something is placed.

01:13:34.720 --> 01:13:36.720
How can you sit in that position?

01:13:38.960 --> 01:13:39.360
Raise

01:13:40.480 --> 01:13:42.240
To raise something is to lift it up.

01:13:43.360 --> 01:13:46.320
We had to work together to raise the last piece.

01:13:48.560 --> 01:13:49.200
Responsible

01:13:50.320 --> 01:13:53.360
If a person is responsible they do the right things.

01:13:54.400 --> 01:13:57.040
I tried to be responsible and save money.

01:13:58.480 --> 01:13:59.600
Site

01:14:00.640 --> 01:14:02.800
A site is something interesting to see.

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:06.240
I saw the pyramids of Egypt.

01:14:06.240 --> 01:14:07.040
What a site.

01:14:09.280 --> 01:14:09.680
Spot

01:14:10.800 --> 01:14:13.040
A spot is a place where something happens.

01:14:14.240 --> 01:14:16.720
The kitchen is a good spot to eat meals.

01:14:18.880 --> 01:14:19.360
Structure

01:14:20.480 --> 01:14:21.840
A structure is a building.

01:14:22.960 --> 01:14:26.080
They just built a beautiful new structure downtown.

01:14:28.240 --> 01:14:28.640
Whole

01:14:29.760 --> 01:14:31.360
Whole means all of something.

01:14:32.400 --> 01:14:35.440
I ate the whole pie. We don't have any more.

01:14:38.960 --> 01:14:40.560
The farmer and the cats.

01:14:41.680 --> 01:14:46.160
Arthur was a responsible farmer and Maria was a nice lady.

01:14:47.120 --> 01:14:48.160
But they were poor.

01:14:48.720 --> 01:14:51.200
They owed the town lord money for their land.

01:14:51.840 --> 01:14:53.840
One summer their farm burned.

01:14:54.320 --> 01:14:58.080
One structure caught fire and most of the animals ran away.

01:14:58.960 --> 01:15:00.320
Only the cats stained.

01:15:00.880 --> 01:15:05.280
So Arthur and Maria had to bring in their crops without an animal's help.

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:08.640
On a fall day the lord demanded his money.

01:15:09.360 --> 01:15:13.200
Arthur asked if the lord could wait until he brought in his crops.

01:15:13.920 --> 01:15:15.600
The lord was angry.

01:15:15.600 --> 01:15:18.160
He raised his hands high and yelled,

01:15:18.240 --> 01:15:20.400
Pay me by the end of the week.

01:15:20.400 --> 01:15:23.600
If you don't I will increase the money you have to pay.

01:15:24.320 --> 01:15:26.640
I might put you in a jail cell.

01:15:27.280 --> 01:15:31.040
So Arthur and Maria worked until there was blood on their hands.

01:15:31.760 --> 01:15:34.640
They finished four lines of corn and went to bed.

01:15:35.280 --> 01:15:37.920
But the next morning eight lines were finished.

01:15:38.640 --> 01:15:41.520
Maria didn't we stop in this spot here?

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:42.880
Arthur asked.

01:15:43.440 --> 01:15:47.680
Yes that is correct and the tools were in a different position too.

01:15:48.320 --> 01:15:49.120
Maria said.

01:15:49.840 --> 01:15:52.160
They were surprised and happy.

01:15:52.160 --> 01:15:55.280
That day they worked hard and finished five lines.

01:15:55.920 --> 01:15:58.400
But in the morning ten lines were done.

01:15:59.040 --> 01:16:01.120
Each day they did a lot of work.

01:16:01.680 --> 01:16:05.040
Each night someone else did an equal amount of work.

01:16:05.760 --> 01:16:08.080
In a week the whole field was finished.

01:16:08.720 --> 01:16:12.000
Tomorrow I will sell the crops and pay the lord.

01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:12.720
Arthur said.

01:16:13.360 --> 01:16:15.440
But that morning the crops were gone.

01:16:16.160 --> 01:16:18.720
A bag was in the middle of the field.

01:16:18.720 --> 01:16:19.760
It contained money.

01:16:20.400 --> 01:16:23.040
Maria let's see who has helped us work.

01:16:23.760 --> 01:16:26.800
Through a hole in the wall they saw a funny sight.

01:16:27.520 --> 01:16:30.400
The cats were dancing in the field and eating corn.

01:16:31.200 --> 01:16:33.120
Now Arthur knew what had happened.

01:16:33.840 --> 01:16:35.840
The cats had worked at night.

01:16:35.840 --> 01:16:40.880
After that Arthur was very nice to his cats and fed them lots of corn.

01:16:41.360 --> 01:16:48.560
Unit 14, word list, coach.

01:16:49.760 --> 01:16:52.080
A coach is a person who teaches sports.

01:16:53.280 --> 01:16:56.000
My coach gets very excited during games.

01:16:58.080 --> 01:16:58.560
Control.

01:16:59.760 --> 01:17:02.400
To control something is to make it do what you want.

01:17:03.440 --> 01:17:06.400
To control the tv just push the buttons.

01:17:06.400 --> 01:17:09.120
Description.

01:17:10.320 --> 01:17:13.520
A description of someone or something says what they are like.

01:17:14.640 --> 01:17:18.480
I gave a description of the man with the gun and hat to the police.

01:17:20.720 --> 01:17:21.200
Direct.

01:17:22.320 --> 01:17:25.520
If something is direct it goes straight between two places.

01:17:26.640 --> 01:17:29.600
The green path is a direct route to my house.

01:17:31.760 --> 01:17:32.240
Exam.

01:17:33.440 --> 01:17:34.800
An exam is a test.

01:17:35.760 --> 01:17:39.120
I did some practice questions for the math exam on the board.

01:17:41.280 --> 01:17:41.840
Example.

01:17:42.960 --> 01:17:46.080
An example of something is a thing that is typical of it.

01:17:47.360 --> 01:17:49.840
Cola is an example of a soft drink.

01:17:52.080 --> 01:17:52.400
Limit.

01:17:53.600 --> 01:17:57.360
A limit is the largest or smallest amount of something that you allow.

01:17:58.640 --> 01:18:01.840
My mother put a limit on how much I could use the phone.

01:18:02.560 --> 01:18:03.440
Local.

01:18:04.480 --> 01:18:07.120
If something is local it is nearby.

01:18:08.320 --> 01:18:12.160
The local market in my neighborhood sells all the food we need.

01:18:14.240 --> 01:18:15.040
Magical.

01:18:16.000 --> 01:18:20.000
Magical describes a quality that makes someone or something special.

01:18:21.040 --> 01:18:24.560
The fireworks made the night sky look so magical.

01:18:26.560 --> 01:18:27.040
Male.

01:18:28.080 --> 01:18:30.880
Male is letters and other things sent to people.

01:18:32.800 --> 01:18:36.800
I get a lot of mail because I have friends all over the world.

01:18:39.040 --> 01:18:39.440
Novel.

01:18:40.560 --> 01:18:42.640
A novel is a book that tells a story.

01:18:43.760 --> 01:18:46.560
He wrote a great novel about ancient China.

01:18:48.640 --> 01:18:49.200
Outline.

01:18:50.320 --> 01:18:53.440
An outline is the plan for a story or essay.

01:18:54.720 --> 01:18:57.680
Before I wrote my essay I made an outline.

01:18:59.840 --> 01:19:00.240
Poet.

01:19:00.880 --> 01:19:03.760
A poet is a person who writes poems.

01:19:04.880 --> 01:19:07.680
William Shakespeare was one of the greatest poets.

01:19:09.760 --> 01:19:10.160
Print.

01:19:11.200 --> 01:19:13.440
To print something is to put it onto paper.

01:19:14.640 --> 01:19:17.360
Make sure that you print your name clearly.

01:19:19.600 --> 01:19:19.920
Scene.

01:19:21.120 --> 01:19:23.840
A scene is one part of a book or movie.

01:19:24.880 --> 01:19:28.480
A movie is made up of many short pieces or scenes.

01:19:30.720 --> 01:19:31.040
Sheet.

01:19:32.240 --> 01:19:34.720
A sheet is a thin flat piece of paper.

01:19:35.840 --> 01:19:39.600
I only needed a single sheet of paper to do my homework.

01:19:41.760 --> 01:19:42.160
Silly.

01:19:43.280 --> 01:19:46.800
If someone or something is silly they show a lack of thought.

01:19:47.920 --> 01:19:51.120
I made a silly mistake of dropping mom's vase.

01:19:53.360 --> 01:19:53.760
Store.

01:19:54.880 --> 01:19:57.200
A store is a place where you can buy things.

01:19:58.160 --> 01:20:01.040
I picked up a few things at the grocery store.

01:20:03.200 --> 01:20:03.680
Suffer.

01:20:04.720 --> 01:20:06.480
To suffer is to feel pain.

01:20:07.600 --> 01:20:09.840
Her headache made her suffer all day.

01:20:12.000 --> 01:20:12.720
Technology.

01:20:13.840 --> 01:20:16.720
Technology is new things made by using science.

01:20:17.760 --> 01:20:20.880
He loves technology such as laptop computers.

01:20:24.400 --> 01:20:25.520
A magical book.

01:20:26.320 --> 01:20:28.080
Sarah loved to read.

01:20:29.120 --> 01:20:30.800
She read novels and poems.

01:20:31.520 --> 01:20:34.160
She loved the beautiful descriptions and phrases.

01:20:34.880 --> 01:20:37.600
She loved reading work from poets and novelists.

01:20:38.720 --> 01:20:40.960
She didn't like video games or technology.

01:20:41.920 --> 01:20:43.440
She was on the basketball team.

01:20:44.000 --> 01:20:45.440
But she didn't like sports.

01:20:46.160 --> 01:20:48.080
Her parents made her play basketball.

01:20:48.720 --> 01:20:51.520
In fact, Sarah's parents made her do many things.

01:20:52.080 --> 01:20:53.920
But she didn't want to do those things.

01:20:54.880 --> 01:20:56.960
She just wanted to sit and read all day.

01:20:57.920 --> 01:21:00.400
One day a small book came in the mail.

01:21:01.120 --> 01:21:02.000
It was for Sarah.

01:21:02.880 --> 01:21:04.320
The book looked very special.

01:21:05.120 --> 01:21:06.880
It was printed on sheets of gold.

01:21:07.680 --> 01:21:08.800
Sarah began to read.

01:21:09.520 --> 01:21:11.360
The outline of the story was simple.

01:21:12.160 --> 01:21:13.760
It was about a magical place.

01:21:14.960 --> 01:21:16.560
Strange things happened there.

01:21:17.520 --> 01:21:20.800
One example from the book was about a boy who could control people.

01:21:21.360 --> 01:21:24.560
In one scene, he made his friends tell funny jokes.

01:21:25.520 --> 01:21:26.640
Sarah loved the book.

01:21:27.280 --> 01:21:28.400
She read it all the time.

01:21:29.200 --> 01:21:30.800
Then something strange happened.

01:21:31.520 --> 01:21:33.680
The book gave Sarah a special power.

01:21:34.720 --> 01:21:36.400
She could control other people.

01:21:37.360 --> 01:21:38.960
She was like the boy in the book.

01:21:39.840 --> 01:21:43.200
During one exam, she made her friend tell silly jokes.

01:21:44.000 --> 01:21:45.200
Her friend got in trouble.

01:21:46.000 --> 01:21:49.120
After school, Sarah did not make a direct trip home.

01:21:49.920 --> 01:21:52.240
On the way, she went to the local store.

01:21:52.880 --> 01:21:54.720
She wanted to play more tricks on people.

01:21:55.440 --> 01:21:56.640
She caused problems.

01:21:57.360 --> 01:21:58.640
She made people fall down.

01:21:59.600 --> 01:22:00.800
She laughed and had fun.

01:22:01.840 --> 01:22:04.160
Finally, she laughed and started to walk home.

01:22:05.280 --> 01:22:06.320
Then she saw something.

01:22:06.960 --> 01:22:09.840
Her basketball coach was about to walk in front of a bus.

01:22:10.560 --> 01:22:11.760
He was looking the other way.

01:22:12.800 --> 01:22:13.760
She had to stop him.

01:22:14.560 --> 01:22:15.680
She used her power.

01:22:16.560 --> 01:22:17.360
She controlled him.

01:22:18.320 --> 01:22:19.680
She made him stop walking.

01:22:20.720 --> 01:22:22.160
Sarah learned something that day.

01:22:22.880 --> 01:22:25.360
It was better to help people than make them suffer.

01:22:26.320 --> 01:22:28.720
So she put a limit on how she used her power.

01:22:29.600 --> 01:22:32.160
She did not want to do bad things with it anymore.

01:22:33.040 --> 01:22:34.800
She only wanted to do good.

01:22:38.880 --> 01:22:39.680
Unit 15.

01:22:40.320 --> 01:22:40.880
Word list

01:22:42.080 --> 01:22:42.640
A cross

01:22:43.760 --> 01:22:46.560
To go across something is to go to the other side of it.

01:22:47.600 --> 01:22:50.400
He walked across the board to the other side.

01:22:52.560 --> 01:22:53.040
Breathe.

01:22:54.160 --> 01:22:57.680
To breathe means to let air go in and out of your body.

01:22:58.880 --> 01:23:02.080
We need strong healthy lungs to help us breathe well.

01:23:04.240 --> 01:23:05.040
Characteristic

01:23:06.080 --> 01:23:09.920
A characteristic is something that shows what a person or a thing is like.

01:23:11.120 --> 01:23:14.480
One characteristic of tigers is their black stripes.

01:23:15.040 --> 01:23:17.040
Consume

01:23:18.240 --> 01:23:20.960
To consume something means to eat or drink it.

01:23:22.160 --> 01:23:24.560
Jack consumed a whole plate of spaghetti.

01:23:26.640 --> 01:23:27.120
Excite

01:23:28.240 --> 01:23:31.280
To excite someone means to make them happy and interested.

01:23:32.240 --> 01:23:34.960
I heard about the school dance on Friday.

01:23:34.960 --> 01:23:36.000
This excited me.

01:23:38.240 --> 01:23:38.800
Extreme

01:23:40.000 --> 01:23:44.000
If something is extreme, it is in a large amount or degree.

01:23:45.200 --> 01:23:48.720
His workout was so extreme that he was sweating heavily.

01:23:50.800 --> 01:23:51.200
Fear

01:23:52.160 --> 01:23:54.240
Fear is the feeling of being afraid.

01:23:55.280 --> 01:23:57.600
I have a great fear of skateboarding.

01:23:59.680 --> 01:24:00.160
Fortunate

01:24:01.280 --> 01:24:03.200
If you are fortunate, you are lucky.

01:24:04.240 --> 01:24:06.160
I was fortunate to get a seat.

01:24:08.240 --> 01:24:08.640
Happen

01:24:09.760 --> 01:24:12.880
If someone happens to do something, they do it by chance.

01:24:13.840 --> 01:24:16.960
I happen to meet some new friends at school today.

01:24:19.120 --> 01:24:19.520
Length

01:24:20.560 --> 01:24:24.240
The length of something is how long it is from one end to the other.

01:24:25.440 --> 01:24:27.840
The length of the floor is 3 meters.

01:24:30.000 --> 01:24:30.480
Mistake

01:24:31.520 --> 01:24:33.520
A mistake is something you do wrong.

01:24:34.640 --> 01:24:37.840
My boss always yells at me when I make a mistake.

01:24:40.000 --> 01:24:40.560
Observe

01:24:41.520 --> 01:24:43.760
To observe something is to watch it.

01:24:44.880 --> 01:24:48.000
Ryan observed the sun rising over the mountains.

01:24:50.160 --> 01:24:50.880
Opportunity

01:24:52.000 --> 01:24:54.560
An opportunity is a chance to do something.

01:24:55.680 --> 01:24:58.880
I had an opportunity to take pictures in the jungle.

01:25:01.040 --> 01:25:01.440
Prize

01:25:02.720 --> 01:25:06.000
A prize is something of value that is given to the winner.

01:25:06.960 --> 01:25:10.800
I won a prize for getting the best grade on my science test.

01:25:13.040 --> 01:25:13.360
Race

01:25:14.560 --> 01:25:17.600
A race is a contest to see who is the fastest.

01:25:18.720 --> 01:25:22.080
Paul is a fast runner, so he easily won the race.

01:25:24.320 --> 01:25:24.800
Realize

01:25:25.920 --> 01:25:28.240
To realize is to suddenly understand.

01:25:29.360 --> 01:25:33.200
After I left my house, I realized that I left the light on.

01:25:33.200 --> 01:25:35.920
Respond

01:25:37.120 --> 01:25:40.480
To respond is to give an answer to what someone else said.

01:25:41.600 --> 01:25:44.880
When the teacher asked the question, we all responded.

01:25:47.040 --> 01:25:47.440
Risk

01:25:48.560 --> 01:25:51.040
A risk is a chance of something bad happening.

01:25:52.240 --> 01:25:54.800
I took a risk and climbed the snowy mountain.

01:25:57.040 --> 01:25:57.520
Wonder

01:25:58.640 --> 01:26:02.080
To wonder is to ask yourself questions or have a need to know.

01:26:03.280 --> 01:26:06.560
The young mother wondered if she'd have a boy or a girl.

01:26:08.800 --> 01:26:09.120
Yet

01:26:10.320 --> 01:26:13.440
Yet is used to say something has not happened up to now.

01:26:14.560 --> 01:26:17.120
We can't go out yet. We're still eating.

01:26:20.720 --> 01:26:21.760
The big race

01:26:23.040 --> 01:26:25.920
A dog saw a group of animals across the road.

01:26:26.480 --> 01:26:28.000
We walked over to meet them.

01:26:28.720 --> 01:26:30.720
What are you doing? He asked them.

01:26:31.520 --> 01:26:36.800
I just sold them tickets to a race between the rabbit and the turtle, the duck responded.

01:26:37.600 --> 01:26:39.440
This news excited the dog.

01:26:40.240 --> 01:26:42.880
He felt fortunate that he happened to be there.

01:26:43.440 --> 01:26:46.720
I don't have anything to do today, the dog said.

01:26:46.720 --> 01:26:48.400
I want to buy a ticket too.

01:26:49.200 --> 01:26:52.080
The dog sat down to observe the race.

01:26:52.080 --> 01:26:54.000
The race would be extreme.

01:26:54.000 --> 01:26:56.320
It would be many kilometers in length.

01:26:56.880 --> 01:27:00.240
The rabbit and the turtle stood next to each other.

01:27:00.320 --> 01:27:02.240
They waited for the race to start.

01:27:02.880 --> 01:27:06.720
The dog wondered why the turtle agreed to run against the rabbit.

01:27:07.520 --> 01:27:10.640
Being fast was not a characteristic of turtles.

01:27:11.280 --> 01:27:13.360
The rabbit was going to win easily.

01:27:14.000 --> 01:27:15.760
Suddenly the race began.

01:27:16.320 --> 01:27:18.560
The rabbit ran extremely quickly.

01:27:19.120 --> 01:27:20.720
The turtle walked slowly.

01:27:21.360 --> 01:27:23.600
After a minute the rabbit looked back.

01:27:24.080 --> 01:27:29.680
He saw that the turtle was far behind him and was breathing quickly because he was so tired.

01:27:30.320 --> 01:27:32.720
The rabbit smiled and slowed to a walk.

01:27:33.360 --> 01:27:35.520
A minute later the rabbit said,

01:27:35.520 --> 01:27:37.920
I'm winning so I'll take a rest.

01:27:37.920 --> 01:27:40.240
He sat and began to consume some grass.

01:27:40.800 --> 01:27:42.880
Then he let his eyes close.

01:27:42.880 --> 01:27:44.640
He wasn't the winner yet,

01:27:44.640 --> 01:27:47.600
but there was no risk of him losing the race.

01:27:48.160 --> 01:27:49.200
He went to sleep.

01:27:49.760 --> 01:27:52.400
Hours later a loud sound woke him.

01:27:52.960 --> 01:27:56.160
All of the animals were yelling and looking at the field.

01:27:56.800 --> 01:27:58.880
He felt fear for the first time.

01:27:59.440 --> 01:28:01.760
The turtle was almost at the finish line.

01:28:02.480 --> 01:28:05.280
Now the rabbit realized his mistake,

01:28:05.280 --> 01:28:06.560
but the race was over.

01:28:07.040 --> 01:28:11.200
He gave the turtle an opportunity to win and the turtle took it.

01:28:11.840 --> 01:28:14.320
The duck handed the turtle his prize.

01:28:14.320 --> 01:28:17.120
It was the happiest day of the turtle's life.

01:28:17.840 --> 01:28:20.160
The dog was happy for the turtle.

01:28:20.160 --> 01:28:22.720
He isn't fast, the dog thought,

01:28:22.720 --> 01:28:25.520
but he tried his best and did something great.

01:28:29.520 --> 01:28:33.600
Unit 16, word list, academy.

01:28:34.720 --> 01:28:36.960
An academy is a special type of school.

01:28:38.240 --> 01:28:41.680
There are many courses taught at the academy that I go to.

01:28:43.840 --> 01:28:47.920
Ancient, if something is ancient, it is very old.

01:28:49.120 --> 01:28:51.600
I want to see the ancient buildings in Rome.

01:28:53.920 --> 01:28:57.440
Board, a board is a flat piece of wood.

01:28:58.400 --> 01:29:01.120
The sign was made of a few wooden barns.

01:29:03.360 --> 01:29:07.120
Century, a century is 100 years.

01:29:08.240 --> 01:29:12.080
Our company is celebrating a century of business in London.

01:29:14.240 --> 01:29:20.320
Clue, a clue is a fact or object that helps solve a mystery or crime.

01:29:21.360 --> 01:29:24.240
The detective found some clues on the sidewalk.

01:29:24.880 --> 01:29:30.080
Concert, a concert is an event where you listen to people play music.

01:29:31.360 --> 01:29:33.520
I enjoyed the concert last night.

01:29:33.520 --> 01:29:35.040
The band was very good.

01:29:37.440 --> 01:29:42.640
County, a county is the largest political division of a state in the US.

01:29:43.840 --> 01:29:47.040
He wanted to represent the citizens of his county.

01:29:49.440 --> 01:29:53.680
Dictionary, a dictionary is a book that tells us

01:29:54.320 --> 01:29:55.280
what words mean.

01:29:56.480 --> 01:29:59.200
I use the dictionary to learn new words.

01:30:01.360 --> 01:30:04.720
Exist, to exist is to be real.

01:30:05.920 --> 01:30:08.800
Do you really think that unicorns ever existed?

01:30:10.960 --> 01:30:16.960
Flat, flat describes something that is level and smooth with no curved parts.

01:30:18.160 --> 01:30:22.160
My parents bought a new flat screen TV over the weekend.

01:30:24.480 --> 01:30:27.840
Gentlemen, a gentleman is a nice man.

01:30:29.040 --> 01:30:32.000
My grandfather is a kind and helpful gentleman.

01:30:34.160 --> 01:30:39.280
Hidden, hidden means to be not easily noticed or too hard to find.

01:30:40.480 --> 01:30:43.840
The hidden camera recorded everything in the parking lot.

01:30:46.000 --> 01:30:51.440
Maybe, maybe is used to show that something is possible or may be true.

01:30:52.400 --> 01:30:56.640
If I focus hard enough, maybe I can come up with the right answer.

01:30:58.720 --> 01:31:02.400
Officer, an officer is a leader in the army.

01:31:03.520 --> 01:31:06.400
The soldiers follow the orders of the officer.

01:31:08.480 --> 01:31:13.280
Original, if something is original, it is the first one of that thing.

01:31:14.560 --> 01:31:17.520
This is the original painting of the Mona Lisa.

01:31:17.520 --> 01:31:25.120
Pound, to pound something, is to hit it many times with a lot of force.

01:31:26.240 --> 01:31:28.240
He pounded the nail with the hammer.

01:31:30.480 --> 01:31:35.040
Process, a process is the steps to take to do something.

01:31:36.240 --> 01:31:38.480
Making a cake is a long process.

01:31:40.720 --> 01:31:45.760
Publish, to publish a book is to get it printed and ready to sell.

01:31:46.720 --> 01:31:49.760
That company publishes daily newspapers.

01:31:51.920 --> 01:31:57.520
Theatre, a theatre is a building where you watch plays, shows and movies.

01:31:58.640 --> 01:32:00.880
We went to the theatre to see a play.

01:32:03.200 --> 01:32:06.640
Wealth, wealth is a large amount of money.

01:32:07.840 --> 01:32:11.360
One of the most important things to some people is wealth.

01:32:11.360 --> 01:32:16.400
Atoms, Counties, Gold

01:32:17.600 --> 01:32:22.480
Atoms Academy was a good school. Boys lived there and took classes.

01:32:23.680 --> 01:32:25.120
Tom worked hard all week.

01:32:26.080 --> 01:32:28.960
On a spring Saturday, he wanted to do something fun.

01:32:29.840 --> 01:32:32.240
He asked his friend Jeff to go to the movie theatre.

01:32:33.280 --> 01:32:36.480
Sorry, Jeff answered. I'm going to a concert.

01:32:37.200 --> 01:32:39.280
So Tom asked Joe to go to the movies.

01:32:40.160 --> 01:32:41.840
But Joe's soccer team had a game.

01:32:42.800 --> 01:32:45.680
Next, Tom went down the hall to Brad's room.

01:32:46.640 --> 01:32:49.120
Brad was reading a very large old book.

01:32:50.240 --> 01:32:51.920
Hi Brad, Tom said.

01:32:52.560 --> 01:32:55.360
Are you reading a dictionary? It looks ancient.

01:32:56.240 --> 01:32:59.680
No, this is called the Wealth of Adams County.

01:33:00.480 --> 01:33:02.720
It's about hidden gold in Adams County.

01:33:03.680 --> 01:33:05.200
It's more than a century old.

01:33:06.000 --> 01:33:07.760
It was published in 1870.

01:33:08.720 --> 01:33:11.280
Look, it even has the original cover on it.

01:33:12.240 --> 01:33:14.320
Tom asked, where did you get it?

01:33:15.280 --> 01:33:16.640
It's from my dad's friend.

01:33:17.200 --> 01:33:19.840
He is a nice gentleman, an officer in the army.

01:33:20.480 --> 01:33:24.880
Answered Brad, the gold doesn't really exist, does it?

01:33:25.520 --> 01:33:26.160
Tom asked.

01:33:26.880 --> 01:33:30.720
I don't know, but maybe there are clues to it in this book.

01:33:31.440 --> 01:33:32.160
Let's find it.

01:33:33.040 --> 01:33:34.720
Looking for gold sounded like fun.

01:33:35.680 --> 01:33:38.640
The first clue was to find a flat tree underground.

01:33:39.600 --> 01:33:42.000
It must be in the forest, Tom said.

01:33:42.800 --> 01:33:46.720
Brad said, the flat tree could be a board under the dirt.

01:33:47.520 --> 01:33:48.720
It could cover the gold.

01:33:49.520 --> 01:33:51.760
Tom and Brad dug in the dirt all morning.

01:33:52.640 --> 01:33:54.960
The process of looking for gold made them hungry.

01:33:55.840 --> 01:33:57.280
They were ready to stop for lunch.

01:33:58.160 --> 01:33:59.760
But then Brad hit something hard.

01:34:00.560 --> 01:34:01.440
It was a board.

01:34:02.400 --> 01:34:04.480
Brad pounded on the board until it broke.

01:34:05.280 --> 01:34:06.800
There was a small hole under it.

01:34:08.000 --> 01:34:10.480
Look, he held up a gold coin.

01:34:11.440 --> 01:34:13.360
Tom saw a piece of paper in the hole.

01:34:14.160 --> 01:34:15.360
Brad, there's more.

01:34:16.080 --> 01:34:17.760
It's a map to the rest of the gold.

01:34:18.720 --> 01:34:19.520
Brad smiled.

01:34:20.160 --> 01:34:20.720
Let's go.

01:34:21.760 --> 01:34:24.320
And they hurried to find the wealth of Adams County.

01:34:28.320 --> 01:34:29.200
Unit 17.

01:34:30.000 --> 01:34:30.640
Word list.

01:34:31.840 --> 01:34:32.480
Appreciate.

01:34:33.520 --> 01:34:36.720
To appreciate something is to understand its good qualities.

01:34:37.840 --> 01:34:40.240
I can appreciate the lovely scenery.

01:34:42.400 --> 01:34:42.960
Available.

01:34:44.000 --> 01:34:46.480
If something is available, it means you can get it.

01:34:47.680 --> 01:34:50.080
There were many seats available in the room.

01:34:52.320 --> 01:34:52.720
Beat.

01:34:53.920 --> 01:34:56.560
To beat someone means to do better than they do.

01:34:57.520 --> 01:35:00.160
I managed to beat everyone in the race.

01:35:02.320 --> 01:35:02.720
Bright.

01:35:03.760 --> 01:35:06.320
If something is bright, it shows a lot of light.

01:35:07.440 --> 01:35:10.400
The bright light from the explosion hurt my eyes.

01:35:12.640 --> 01:35:13.280
Celebrate.

01:35:14.320 --> 01:35:17.840
To celebrate is to do something to show that an event is special.

01:35:18.960 --> 01:35:21.840
We all celebrate it when we heard the great news.

01:35:24.000 --> 01:35:24.560
Determine.

01:35:25.440 --> 01:35:28.320
To determine means to choose or make a decision.

01:35:29.360 --> 01:35:32.400
He tried to determine which one to eat first.

01:35:34.640 --> 01:35:35.200
Disappear.

01:35:36.320 --> 01:35:39.680
To disappear means to go away or not be seen.

01:35:40.880 --> 01:35:44.000
The top of the building is disappearing in the clouds.

01:35:46.160 --> 01:35:46.560
Else.

01:35:47.680 --> 01:35:51.040
If you talk about something else, you talk about something different.

01:35:52.160 --> 01:35:54.240
I wanted a bike for my birthday.

01:35:54.640 --> 01:35:56.080
But I got something else.

01:35:58.320 --> 01:35:58.640
Fair.

01:35:59.920 --> 01:36:03.840
Fair describes treating someone in a way that is reasonable or right.

01:36:04.960 --> 01:36:07.600
He sold me his car for a fair price.

01:36:09.840 --> 01:36:10.160
Flow.

01:36:11.440 --> 01:36:15.040
To flow is to move easily and continuously in one direction.

01:36:16.160 --> 01:36:19.280
The water flowed over the rocks and into the lake.

01:36:21.440 --> 01:36:21.920
Forward.

01:36:22.880 --> 01:36:26.080
If you move forward, you move in the direction in front of you.

01:36:27.280 --> 01:36:30.640
When he saw his mother, the baby crawled forward to her.

01:36:32.800 --> 01:36:33.200
Hill.

01:36:34.400 --> 01:36:36.400
A hill is a round area of land.

01:36:37.280 --> 01:36:38.960
It is higher than the land around it.

01:36:40.080 --> 01:36:42.720
The sun was rising above the green hills.

01:36:44.960 --> 01:36:45.280
Level.

01:36:46.480 --> 01:36:49.120
A level is a point on a scale that measures something.

01:36:50.080 --> 01:36:52.320
Please check the level of the temperature.

01:36:54.480 --> 01:36:54.880
Loan.

01:36:56.000 --> 01:37:00.400
If someone or something is loan, they are the only one of that kind.

01:37:01.520 --> 01:37:03.760
A lone man walked along the street.

01:37:05.840 --> 01:37:06.240
Puddle.

01:37:07.360 --> 01:37:09.760
A puddle is a pool of liquid on the ground.

01:37:10.880 --> 01:37:13.440
When the ice melted, it formed a puddle.

01:37:15.600 --> 01:37:16.240
Response.

01:37:17.120 --> 01:37:19.600
A response is the answer to a question.

01:37:20.720 --> 01:37:24.240
He asked if I was sad. My response was no.

01:37:26.560 --> 01:37:26.960
Season.

01:37:28.080 --> 01:37:29.760
A season is a time of the year.

01:37:30.400 --> 01:37:32.960
Spring, summer, fall, or winter.

01:37:34.160 --> 01:37:37.760
Fall is a warm season while winter is very cold.

01:37:39.920 --> 01:37:40.480
Solution.

01:37:41.600 --> 01:37:43.920
A solution is a way to solve a problem.

01:37:44.880 --> 01:37:48.000
There are many problems. We need solutions.

01:37:50.240 --> 01:37:50.640
Waste.

01:37:51.680 --> 01:37:54.640
To waste means to carelessly use something all up.

01:37:55.760 --> 01:37:58.320
Turn off the water so you don't waste it.

01:38:00.480 --> 01:38:00.880
Weather.

01:38:02.000 --> 01:38:05.120
You use weather when you must choose between two things.

01:38:06.160 --> 01:38:09.120
I could not decide whether to go left or right.

01:38:09.120 --> 01:38:14.080
The race for water.

01:38:15.360 --> 01:38:17.680
There was a town next to a river.

01:38:18.320 --> 01:38:22.320
The people there had a lot of water, but they wasted it.

01:38:23.280 --> 01:38:25.120
That made the sky angry.

01:38:25.680 --> 01:38:29.920
It said, if you waste water, I will take it away from you.

01:38:30.560 --> 01:38:32.080
But the people didn't listen.

01:38:32.800 --> 01:38:37.360
When the season changed from spring to summer, the clouds disappeared.

01:38:38.000 --> 01:38:41.200
The bright sun was hot and made the river dry.

01:38:41.840 --> 01:38:43.760
There was no water available.

01:38:44.560 --> 01:38:47.280
People asked, when will the rain fall?

01:38:48.160 --> 01:38:52.320
The sky's response was, you don't appreciate water.

01:38:52.320 --> 01:38:55.760
You waste it and now I will never make rain again.

01:38:56.560 --> 01:38:59.520
A boy determined that this wasn't fair.

01:38:59.520 --> 01:39:01.200
He thought of a solution.

01:39:01.200 --> 01:39:03.040
He asked the sky to raise him.

01:39:03.680 --> 01:39:09.200
He said, if I get to the top of that hill, before your rain can form puddles,

01:39:09.200 --> 01:39:10.720
you must fill our river.

01:39:11.360 --> 01:39:12.880
The sky laughed.

01:39:12.880 --> 01:39:15.200
Little boy, I am the sky.

01:39:15.200 --> 01:39:17.520
I am above everything else.

01:39:17.520 --> 01:39:18.800
You cannot beat me.

01:39:19.760 --> 01:39:21.520
But the boy knew he would win.

01:39:22.240 --> 01:39:25.440
When the race began, the boy ran forward.

01:39:25.440 --> 01:39:29.760
The sky started raining on the hill, but puddles did not form there.

01:39:30.240 --> 01:39:33.280
When it rained on the hill, the water went down.

01:39:34.000 --> 01:39:35.920
The sky kept raining.

01:39:35.920 --> 01:39:38.160
The water flowed down into the river.

01:39:38.800 --> 01:39:42.640
When the boy reached the top of the hill, the river was full.

01:39:43.200 --> 01:39:45.520
The people began to celebrate.

01:39:45.520 --> 01:39:49.120
It was the highest level the river had ever been at before.

01:39:49.920 --> 01:39:51.920
The sky was angry.

01:39:51.920 --> 01:39:53.680
A boy can't beat me.

01:39:53.680 --> 01:39:55.600
I won't fill your river.

01:39:55.600 --> 01:39:58.560
It said, now the boy laughed.

01:39:58.640 --> 01:40:01.920
It doesn't matter whether you want to fill it or not.

01:40:01.920 --> 01:40:04.480
He said, you already did.

01:40:04.480 --> 01:40:06.400
The sky looked at the full river.

01:40:07.040 --> 01:40:09.200
You tricked me, it said.

01:40:09.200 --> 01:40:12.560
It asked the people, do you appreciate water now?

01:40:13.360 --> 01:40:16.800
Yes, they said, we won't waste it.

01:40:16.800 --> 01:40:21.520
That is how a lone boy saved his town and won the race for water.

01:40:22.080 --> 01:40:29.120
Unid 18, word list, argue.

01:40:30.240 --> 01:40:34.240
To argue is to angrily speak to someone because you do not agree.

01:40:35.360 --> 01:40:37.600
We argued about where to go for dinner.

01:40:39.680 --> 01:40:40.320
Communicate.

01:40:41.360 --> 01:40:45.840
To communicate is to give information by talking, writing, etc.

01:40:46.880 --> 01:40:49.920
I communicated with Paul about his new ideas.

01:40:52.080 --> 01:40:52.480
Crowd.

01:40:53.600 --> 01:40:55.520
A crowd is a large group of people.

01:40:56.640 --> 01:41:00.240
A large crowd had gathered on the street to see the accident.

01:41:02.400 --> 01:41:02.880
Depend.

01:41:04.000 --> 01:41:06.720
To depend on someone or something is to need them.

01:41:07.760 --> 01:41:10.720
Children depend on their parents for many things.

01:41:12.880 --> 01:41:13.280
Dish.

01:41:14.480 --> 01:41:15.760
A dish is a plate.

01:41:16.880 --> 01:41:19.520
She put a clean white dish on the table.

01:41:21.600 --> 01:41:22.000
Empty.

01:41:23.200 --> 01:41:25.920
If something is empty, it does not have anything in it.

01:41:27.040 --> 01:41:31.840
My gas tank was almost empty, so I couldn't drive my car very long.

01:41:34.000 --> 01:41:34.560
Exact.

01:41:35.680 --> 01:41:38.480
If something is exact, it is just the right amount.

01:41:39.600 --> 01:41:42.800
Please use the exact amount of sugar for the cake.

01:41:44.960 --> 01:41:45.360
Fresh.

01:41:46.400 --> 01:41:48.320
If something is fresh, it is new.

01:41:49.200 --> 01:41:52.800
I just bought these oranges. They are very fresh.

01:41:55.040 --> 01:41:55.520
Gather.

01:41:56.560 --> 01:42:00.320
To gather is to collect several things, usually from different places.

01:42:01.440 --> 01:42:03.840
Sam gathered some flowers for his mother.

01:42:05.920 --> 01:42:06.480
Indicate.

01:42:07.600 --> 01:42:11.680
To indicate means to show, point, or make something clear.

01:42:12.800 --> 01:42:16.560
He pointed to his eyes to indicate where he had heard himself.

01:42:18.720 --> 01:42:19.120
Item.

01:42:20.240 --> 01:42:22.560
An item is a thing that you buy or sell.

01:42:23.760 --> 01:42:26.720
I have many items for school in my bag.

01:42:28.880 --> 01:42:29.360
Offer.

01:42:30.480 --> 01:42:33.200
To offer is to present someone with something.

01:42:34.240 --> 01:42:36.720
He offered me the keys to his car.

01:42:38.880 --> 01:42:39.280
Price.

01:42:40.400 --> 01:42:42.640
The price of something is how much it costs.

01:42:43.840 --> 01:42:45.840
What is the price of this item?

01:42:46.480 --> 01:42:47.440
Product.

01:42:48.400 --> 01:42:51.200
A product is something that is made.

01:42:52.400 --> 01:42:55.600
My sister has many beauty products in her room.

01:42:57.840 --> 01:42:58.320
Property.

01:42:59.440 --> 01:43:01.280
Property is something that someone owns.

01:43:02.480 --> 01:43:04.240
The house is now my property.

01:43:06.400 --> 01:43:06.880
Purchase.

01:43:08.000 --> 01:43:09.840
To purchase something is to buy it.

01:43:10.880 --> 01:43:13.040
I recently purchased a new car.

01:43:13.760 --> 01:43:18.160
To recommend something is to say that someone should do it.

01:43:19.200 --> 01:43:22.960
My doctor recommended that I get some exercise.

01:43:24.960 --> 01:43:25.440
Select.

01:43:26.160 --> 01:43:28.240
To select something is to choose it.

01:43:29.200 --> 01:43:32.560
I hope that I selected the right answers on the test.

01:43:35.200 --> 01:43:35.600
A tool.

01:43:36.400 --> 01:43:38.640
A tool is something that helps you do a task.

01:43:38.640 --> 01:43:41.520
We used a tool to fix the window.

01:43:42.720 --> 01:43:43.280
Treat.

01:43:43.920 --> 01:43:47.120
To treat is to act in a certain way towards someone.

01:43:48.160 --> 01:43:51.040
The cats treated the mouse very nicely.

01:43:52.560 --> 01:43:54.560
The little red chicken.

01:43:55.760 --> 01:43:59.440
A little red chicken had a store in a small town.

01:44:00.800 --> 01:44:03.360
She sold many different items to people in the town.

01:44:04.560 --> 01:44:06.480
The parents had a store in a small town.

01:44:06.800 --> 01:44:07.360
People in the town.

01:44:08.320 --> 01:44:09.840
The people loved her products.

01:44:10.720 --> 01:44:13.200
One day, a cat came to her property.

01:44:13.920 --> 01:44:17.440
He saw the sign that indicated where the chicken store was located.

01:44:18.000 --> 01:44:19.440
He wanted to purchase bread.

01:44:20.160 --> 01:44:22.160
But the chicken store was almost empty.

01:44:22.800 --> 01:44:24.320
She had only a bag of wheat.

01:44:25.520 --> 01:44:27.360
You can use the wheat to make bread.

01:44:28.000 --> 01:44:28.800
The chicken said,

01:44:29.600 --> 01:44:31.600
No, I don't want to work.

01:44:32.160 --> 01:44:34.800
The cat said, I just want to buy bread.

01:44:35.760 --> 01:44:38.160
The cat became angry and left the store.

01:44:39.360 --> 01:44:42.640
Later, the little red chicken saw the cat in a crowd.

01:44:43.680 --> 01:44:46.320
I will help you make the bread, she said.

01:44:47.120 --> 01:44:48.640
But the cat treated her badly.

01:44:49.440 --> 01:44:51.200
He did not even communicate with her.

01:44:52.080 --> 01:44:53.760
He did not want to do any work.

01:44:54.400 --> 01:44:56.320
So the chicken decided to make the bread.

01:44:57.360 --> 01:45:00.400
She selected the exact amount of wheat to make fresh bread.

01:45:01.600 --> 01:45:04.400
She used a stone to pound the wheat to get it ready.

01:45:05.440 --> 01:45:07.120
Soon, her bread was ready.

01:45:08.080 --> 01:45:10.480
The cat came and saw the bread on a dish.

01:45:11.280 --> 01:45:12.880
Give me some of your bread.

01:45:13.440 --> 01:45:17.200
He said, No, said the little red chicken.

01:45:17.760 --> 01:45:19.440
You did not help me make the bread.

01:45:20.000 --> 01:45:21.760
So you shall not have any to eat.

01:45:22.480 --> 01:45:23.920
The cat argued with the chicken.

01:45:24.640 --> 01:45:26.160
He tried to offer a price for it.

01:45:26.800 --> 01:45:29.440
But the little red chicken did not want to sell her bread.

01:45:30.320 --> 01:45:32.960
Don't depend on others to do work for you.

01:45:33.600 --> 01:45:34.720
Said the little red chicken.

01:45:35.760 --> 01:45:37.360
Then how will I get bread?

01:45:38.160 --> 01:45:38.880
The cat asked.

01:45:39.520 --> 01:45:41.040
I recommend doing some work.

01:45:41.760 --> 01:45:42.880
Said the little red chicken.

01:45:43.440 --> 01:45:45.440
Use a tool to plant your own wheat.

01:45:46.000 --> 01:45:49.360
When it grows big, you can gather it and make your own bread.

01:45:50.000 --> 01:45:53.200
You need to learn to do work for what you want.

01:45:57.280 --> 01:45:59.440
Unit 19, word list.

01:46:00.400 --> 01:46:01.120
Alive.

01:46:02.160 --> 01:46:05.520
If someone or something is alive, they are not dead.

01:46:06.640 --> 01:46:11.040
My grandparents are still alive even though they are over 90.

01:46:13.280 --> 01:46:13.600
Bone.

01:46:14.800 --> 01:46:16.880
A bone is a hard part of the body.

01:46:18.000 --> 01:46:20.720
I brought home a nice bone for my dog.

01:46:22.960 --> 01:46:23.360
Bother.

01:46:24.400 --> 01:46:26.960
To bother is to make the effort to do something.

01:46:27.920 --> 01:46:30.720
No one bothered to wash the dishes today.

01:46:32.880 --> 01:46:33.360
Captain.

01:46:34.400 --> 01:46:37.520
A captain is the person who leads a ship or airplane.

01:46:38.640 --> 01:46:41.440
The captain sailed his ship to Australia.

01:46:43.600 --> 01:46:44.160
Conclusion.

01:46:45.280 --> 01:46:47.760
The conclusion of something is the final part of it.

01:46:48.880 --> 01:46:53.200
At the conclusion of the race, the spectators cheered for the winner.

01:46:55.360 --> 01:46:55.760
Doubt.

01:46:57.040 --> 01:46:59.040
Doubt is a feeling of not being sure.

01:47:00.160 --> 01:47:02.640
I have doubt that the story is true.

01:47:04.880 --> 01:47:05.440
Explore.

01:47:06.560 --> 01:47:08.640
To explore is to look for new places.

01:47:09.840 --> 01:47:13.200
He wants to explore the world and see new things.

01:47:15.360 --> 01:47:15.760
Foreign.

01:47:16.880 --> 01:47:19.680
If something is foreign, it is from a different country.

01:47:20.880 --> 01:47:23.920
Mexican food is a popular foreign food.

01:47:24.560 --> 01:47:26.320
I am glad you came to my party.

01:47:27.520 --> 01:47:32.720
However, however, means despite or not being influenced by something.

01:47:34.800 --> 01:47:35.360
She is a great cook.

01:47:35.920 --> 01:47:39.840
However, she never had professional lessons.

01:47:41.040 --> 01:47:41.680
Injustice.

01:47:42.800 --> 01:47:45.840
Injustice is a lack of fairness or justice.

01:47:48.000 --> 01:47:48.480
Putty.

01:47:49.840 --> 01:47:52.400
Injustice is a lack of fairness or justice.

01:47:53.040 --> 01:47:57.520
Putting an innocent person in jail is an act of injustice.

01:47:59.760 --> 01:48:00.480
International.

01:48:01.520 --> 01:48:05.040
If something is international, it involves more than one country.

01:48:06.240 --> 01:48:10.160
The United Nations is a powerful international organization.

01:48:12.480 --> 01:48:12.880
Lawyer.

01:48:13.920 --> 01:48:17.120
A lawyer works with the law and represents people in court.

01:48:18.240 --> 01:48:22.240
The lawyer left the courthouse after the judge made her decision.

01:48:23.040 --> 01:48:24.960
Mention.

01:48:26.160 --> 01:48:28.400
To mention something is to talk about it.

01:48:29.440 --> 01:48:32.880
The doctors mentioned the problems that the patient was having.

01:48:35.040 --> 01:48:35.600
Policy.

01:48:36.640 --> 01:48:38.160
A policy is a rule.

01:48:39.280 --> 01:48:42.960
He told us that his policy was to put customers first.

01:48:45.120 --> 01:48:45.600
Social.

01:48:46.720 --> 01:48:50.320
If something is social, it is about many people in a community.

01:48:50.960 --> 01:48:55.440
People should come together and fix the world's social problems.

01:48:57.680 --> 01:48:58.160
Speech.

01:48:59.280 --> 01:49:01.600
A speech is something said to a group of people.

01:49:02.720 --> 01:49:04.720
She gave a speech to the class.

01:49:06.960 --> 01:49:07.360
Staff.

01:49:08.480 --> 01:49:11.600
A staff is a group of people working together in a company.

01:49:12.720 --> 01:49:16.640
My dad has a staff of four people to help him at the office.

01:49:16.640 --> 01:49:17.280
This.

01:49:18.880 --> 01:49:19.280
Toward.

01:49:20.480 --> 01:49:23.120
If you go toward something, you go closer to it.

01:49:24.320 --> 01:49:27.360
Santa walked toward my house with a special tree.

01:49:29.680 --> 01:49:30.000
Wood.

01:49:31.280 --> 01:49:33.200
Wood is the thing that trees are made of.

01:49:34.320 --> 01:49:36.880
I put the pieces of wood in a pile.

01:49:40.480 --> 01:49:41.200
Shipwrecked.

01:49:42.400 --> 01:49:44.080
Simon Yates was a lawyer.

01:49:44.720 --> 01:49:46.000
He helped many people.

01:49:46.640 --> 01:49:49.040
However, he was not a nice man.

01:49:49.760 --> 01:49:52.560
His policy was to help only rich people.

01:49:53.360 --> 01:49:55.920
He didn't bother about social injustice.

01:49:56.720 --> 01:50:00.720
He made a lot of money, but many people didn't like him.

01:50:01.440 --> 01:50:04.240
Even people on his staff didn't like him.

01:50:04.800 --> 01:50:07.200
They wanted bad things to happen to him.

01:50:07.920 --> 01:50:11.200
In fact, they were glad when he got into trouble.

01:50:12.000 --> 01:50:14.160
Simon had a very bad day.

01:50:14.640 --> 01:50:17.440
He did many things wrong and lost his job.

01:50:18.080 --> 01:50:20.160
Soon, he didn't have any money.

01:50:20.960 --> 01:50:24.560
His wife, Mrs. Yates, began to have doubts about him.

01:50:25.280 --> 01:50:27.840
Simon wanted to start a new life.

01:50:27.840 --> 01:50:29.520
He planned to leave the country.

01:50:30.240 --> 01:50:33.040
He mentioned his plan to the captain of a ship.

01:50:33.680 --> 01:50:35.920
The captain was exploring the world.

01:50:36.800 --> 01:50:40.000
The captain felt bad for Simon and said,

01:50:40.000 --> 01:50:42.560
I will take you to foreign countries.

01:50:42.560 --> 01:50:44.160
They left the next day.

01:50:45.200 --> 01:50:48.480
Near the conclusion of their international trip,

01:50:48.480 --> 01:50:49.840
the weather turned bad.

01:50:50.400 --> 01:50:55.040
A wave pushed Simon off the boat, but he was alive.

01:50:55.040 --> 01:50:56.800
He swam toward an island.

01:50:57.360 --> 01:50:59.600
After a long time, he got there.

01:51:00.400 --> 01:51:02.080
At first, he was upset.

01:51:02.880 --> 01:51:04.480
He was lost and alone.

01:51:05.360 --> 01:51:07.760
I'll never go home again, he thought.

01:51:08.640 --> 01:51:11.840
He had a lot of problems, but he survived.

01:51:12.640 --> 01:51:14.400
He built a house in a tree.

01:51:15.040 --> 01:51:16.880
He lived on a diet of fish.

01:51:17.680 --> 01:51:19.840
He made tools from wood and bones.

01:51:20.560 --> 01:51:22.800
He made a cup to drink rainwater.

01:51:23.600 --> 01:51:26.960
Slowly, he learned to be happy on the island.

01:51:26.960 --> 01:51:28.320
He swam every day.

01:51:28.880 --> 01:51:33.440
He had trouble sometimes, but he always found a way to fix the problem.

01:51:34.240 --> 01:51:36.240
Life was simple, he liked it.

01:51:36.960 --> 01:51:40.480
Finally, people on a ship saw Simon on the island.

01:51:41.040 --> 01:51:42.560
They wanted to take him home.

01:51:43.280 --> 01:51:45.040
But Simon was happy.

01:51:45.040 --> 01:51:47.520
He gave them a long speech about life.

01:51:48.080 --> 01:51:49.520
He said he wanted to stay.

01:51:50.160 --> 01:51:53.600
He liked his new simple life more than his old life.

01:51:57.760 --> 01:51:59.600
Unit 20, word list.

01:52:00.800 --> 01:52:01.360
