If something is worth an amount of money, it costs that amount.

01:55:32.480 --> 01:55:34.800
Our house is worth a lot of money.

01:55:38.320 --> 01:55:39.840
The Seven Cities of Gold

01:55:41.120 --> 01:55:46.720
Many years ago, a Spanish officer named Coronado heard the story of seven great cities.

01:55:47.360 --> 01:55:50.640
The walls of these cities are made of gold, his friends told him.

01:55:51.200 --> 01:55:55.280
The people eat meat from golden plates and dress in nice clothes,

01:55:55.280 --> 01:55:56.320
they said.

01:55:56.320 --> 01:55:58.960
They called these cities the Seven Cities of Gold.

01:55:59.680 --> 01:56:00.720
Were the cities real?

01:56:01.280 --> 01:56:03.600
Coronado never considered asking his friends.

01:56:04.240 --> 01:56:05.600
Coronado thought to himself,

01:56:06.160 --> 01:56:08.880
the things in these cities must be worth a lot of money.

01:56:09.680 --> 01:56:11.920
So he went to find the Seven Cities of Gold.

01:56:12.480 --> 01:56:16.080
He took along 300 men, many horses, and extra food.

01:56:16.720 --> 01:56:18.000
They headed west.

01:56:18.000 --> 01:56:20.800
Coronado wanted to achieve his gold very badly.

01:56:21.600 --> 01:56:23.920
Coronado and his men rode for many days.

01:56:24.640 --> 01:56:25.840
Then they saw some cities.

01:56:26.640 --> 01:56:31.920
We found the Seven Cities of Gold, his men yelled, but Coronado wasn't happy.

01:56:32.480 --> 01:56:33.760
He had a different opinion.

01:56:34.480 --> 01:56:37.360
These can't be the Seven Cities of Gold, he said.

01:56:38.080 --> 01:56:39.680
Look, they're made of dirt.

01:56:40.240 --> 01:56:41.200
Coronado was right.

01:56:41.840 --> 01:56:43.600
The cities weren't bright and golden.

01:56:44.240 --> 01:56:45.440
They were dirty and brown.

01:56:46.000 --> 01:56:48.320
The people didn't eat meat from golden plates.

01:56:49.040 --> 01:56:51.120
They ate vegetables from regular bowls.

01:56:51.920 --> 01:56:53.600
They wore the most basic clothes.

01:56:54.240 --> 01:56:56.880
Coronado regarded the cities as ugly places.

01:56:57.760 --> 01:57:00.720
What happened to the cities of gold, he thought?

01:57:00.720 --> 01:57:01.920
Did someone destroy them?

01:57:02.480 --> 01:57:03.360
Was there a war?

01:57:04.000 --> 01:57:06.240
Did someone already come and take the gold?

01:57:06.960 --> 01:57:10.960
That night, the people of the cities entertained Coronado and his men

01:57:10.960 --> 01:57:11.920
and served them food.

01:57:12.480 --> 01:57:14.240
They advised Coronado to go home.

01:57:15.120 --> 01:57:17.360
There is no gold here, they told him.

01:57:17.840 --> 01:57:18.960
Coronado was angry.

01:57:19.840 --> 01:57:21.200
Did his friends lie to him?

01:57:22.160 --> 01:57:23.280
He left the next morning.

01:57:24.080 --> 01:57:26.080
He looked back at the cities one more time.

01:57:27.040 --> 01:57:29.120
The sun reflected light on the dirt houses.

01:57:30.000 --> 01:57:31.920
Coronado thought he saw a bit of gold.

01:57:32.800 --> 01:57:34.320
Were his friends right after all?

01:57:35.440 --> 01:57:38.400
No, he told himself, it's just the sun.

01:57:39.280 --> 01:57:40.800
Then he turned away and went home.

01:57:44.880 --> 01:57:48.720
Unit 21, word list, appear.

01:57:49.840 --> 01:57:51.360
To appear is to seem.

01:57:52.320 --> 01:57:55.440
She appeared to be sad, she was crying.

01:57:57.680 --> 01:57:58.000
Base.

01:57:59.200 --> 01:58:01.120
The base is the bottom of something.

01:58:02.320 --> 01:58:04.960
The base of the table has three legs.

01:58:07.120 --> 01:58:07.520
Brain.

01:58:08.720 --> 01:58:11.600
The brain is the organ in your head that lets you think.

01:58:12.640 --> 01:58:15.360
You must use your brain to solve the problem.

01:58:17.520 --> 01:58:18.000
Career.

01:58:18.960 --> 01:58:22.480
A career is a job that you do for a large part of your life.

01:58:23.520 --> 01:58:27.120
He was in the hospitality business for most of his career.

01:58:29.280 --> 01:58:29.680
Clerk.

01:58:30.720 --> 01:58:32.240
A clerk is a type of worker.

01:58:33.040 --> 01:58:34.960
Clerks in a store help customers.

01:58:36.000 --> 01:58:38.880
The clerk added up her bill for the groceries.

01:58:41.040 --> 01:58:41.440
Effort.

01:58:42.640 --> 01:58:45.280
Effort is hard work or an attempt to do something.

01:58:46.080 --> 01:58:49.680
He always puts a lot of effort into his studies.

01:58:51.840 --> 01:58:52.320
Enter.

01:58:53.360 --> 01:58:55.360
To enter a place is to go into it.

01:58:56.480 --> 01:58:59.680
Two guards greeted me as I entered the front door.

01:59:01.840 --> 01:59:02.400
Excellent.

01:59:03.520 --> 01:59:06.000
When something is excellent, it is very good.

01:59:07.120 --> 01:59:10.160
I got an excellent scar on my school test.

01:59:12.240 --> 01:59:12.640
Hero.

01:59:13.600 --> 01:59:16.880
A hero is a brave person who does things to help others.

01:59:17.920 --> 01:59:22.640
To children, the man in the blue and red costume was a real hero.

01:59:24.720 --> 01:59:25.120
Hurry.

01:59:26.240 --> 01:59:28.160
To hurry is to do something quickly.

01:59:29.360 --> 01:59:31.360
I hurried home on my bike.

01:59:33.440 --> 01:59:34.080
Inform.

01:59:35.200 --> 01:59:37.920
To inform someone is to tell them about something.

01:59:39.040 --> 01:59:41.920
I called an informter about my idea.

01:59:43.440 --> 01:59:44.640
Later.

01:59:45.840 --> 01:59:49.680
Later means after the present, expected or usual time.

01:59:50.880 --> 01:59:55.200
She missed the train, so she'll arrive a little later than expected.

01:59:57.360 --> 01:59:57.760
Leave.

01:59:58.960 --> 02:00:02.080
To leave means to go away from someone or something.

02:00:03.200 --> 02:00:06.320
He packed his bag and was ready to leave for home.

02:00:08.560 --> 02:00:09.040
Locate.

02:00:10.160 --> 02:00:12.000
To locate something is to find it.

02:00:13.120 --> 02:00:15.760
I could not locate my keys in the house.

02:00:17.920 --> 02:00:18.320
Nurse.

02:00:19.440 --> 02:00:22.400
A nurse is a person who helps sick people in the hospital.

02:00:23.520 --> 02:00:25.440
A nurse helped me get better.

02:00:27.600 --> 02:00:28.160
Operation.

02:00:29.280 --> 02:00:33.440
An operation is when a doctor replaces or removes something in the body.

02:00:34.640 --> 02:00:37.360
The operation on my arm was a success.

02:00:39.600 --> 02:00:39.920
Pain.

02:00:40.880 --> 02:00:43.360
Pain is the feeling that you have when you are hurt.

02:00:44.560 --> 02:00:46.560
His head was full of pain.

02:00:48.800 --> 02:00:49.440
Refuse.

02:00:50.560 --> 02:00:52.560
To refuse something is to say no to it.

02:00:53.680 --> 02:00:56.000
The dog refused to play with the cat.

02:00:58.240 --> 02:00:58.560
Though.

02:00:59.840 --> 02:01:03.600
Though is used when the second idea makes the first seem surprising.

02:01:04.880 --> 02:01:07.680
Though he was overweight, he liked to be active.

02:01:10.000 --> 02:01:10.400
Various.

02:01:11.520 --> 02:01:14.160
If something is various, there are many types of it.

02:01:15.280 --> 02:01:17.600
She owned shoes of various styles.

02:01:21.120 --> 02:01:21.600
Katie.

02:01:22.800 --> 02:01:26.400
I first met eight-year-old Katie on a rainy afternoon.

02:01:27.040 --> 02:01:28.960
I was a nurse at a hospital.

02:01:29.760 --> 02:01:32.560
The clerk at the desk told me about Katie.

02:01:33.200 --> 02:01:36.160
She was there because she felt a lot of pain.

02:01:36.720 --> 02:01:40.240
The doctor is located a problem at the base of her brain.

02:01:41.040 --> 02:01:44.400
I knew she was special even before she got better.

02:01:45.040 --> 02:01:47.600
I'll always remember Katie as a hero.

02:01:48.240 --> 02:01:51.520
When I entered Katie's room, she was not in her bed.

02:01:52.160 --> 02:01:55.360
She was in a chair next to Tommy, a little boy.

02:01:56.080 --> 02:02:00.560
Though Katie did not feel well, she was playing with Tommy and his toys.

02:02:01.280 --> 02:02:04.800
It took a lot of effort for her just to sit in the chair.

02:02:05.360 --> 02:02:08.320
But she played with Tommy because it made him happy.

02:02:09.280 --> 02:02:13.200
Katie was always smiling and never appeared to be in pain.

02:02:14.160 --> 02:02:16.320
She refused to just lie in bed.

02:02:17.440 --> 02:02:20.000
One day, I found her painting a picture.

02:02:20.880 --> 02:02:24.080
Later, she gave it to one of the older patients.

02:02:25.040 --> 02:02:29.760
Another day, she went outside to get flowers for another sick little girl.

02:02:30.560 --> 02:02:32.240
Katie made everyone smile.

02:02:33.200 --> 02:02:36.560
The doctors hurried to fix the problem in Katie's brain.

02:02:37.280 --> 02:02:39.280
The operation was successful.

02:02:39.840 --> 02:02:43.280
The doctors informed the hospital staff of the good news.

02:02:44.080 --> 02:02:45.120
Katie was fine.

02:02:45.680 --> 02:02:47.360
She soon felt excellent.

02:02:47.920 --> 02:02:52.080
She got better and was able to leave the hospital a month later.

02:02:53.040 --> 02:02:55.680
I have had a long career as a nurse.

02:02:56.320 --> 02:02:57.920
I have met many patients.

02:02:58.640 --> 02:03:01.920
However, I have never met another girl like Katie.

02:03:02.560 --> 02:03:06.160
Even after she got well, she still came to the hospital.

02:03:06.960 --> 02:03:09.840
She played various games with the young patients.

02:03:10.480 --> 02:03:13.040
She read many books to the older patients.

02:03:13.600 --> 02:03:16.640
Katie's kind heart helped her get better so quickly.

02:03:17.360 --> 02:03:20.880
She is a hero to me and everyone else at the hospital.

02:03:24.880 --> 02:03:25.760
Unit 22.

02:03:26.480 --> 02:03:27.120
Word List

02:03:28.320 --> 02:03:28.800
Actual

02:03:29.600 --> 02:03:32.560
Actual means that something is real or true.

02:03:33.920 --> 02:03:37.840
This is the actual sword that the king owned, not a fake one.

02:03:40.080 --> 02:03:40.560
Amaze

02:03:41.760 --> 02:03:44.480
To amaze someone is to surprise them very much.

02:03:45.680 --> 02:03:48.000
The news in the paper, Amaze Jack.

02:03:50.160 --> 02:03:50.560
Charge

02:03:51.680 --> 02:03:53.840
A charge is the price to pay for something.

02:03:54.960 --> 02:03:57.760
The charge for the shirts was $15.

02:03:59.440 --> 02:04:00.400
Comfort

02:04:01.440 --> 02:04:03.840
To comfort someone means to make them feel better.

02:04:04.960 --> 02:04:08.880
I wanted to comfort my friend after I heard the bad news.

02:04:11.040 --> 02:04:11.600
Contact

02:04:12.720 --> 02:04:15.200
To contact someone is to speak or write to them.

02:04:16.320 --> 02:04:18.720
I contacted Sue about my party.

02:04:20.800 --> 02:04:21.280
Customer

02:04:22.400 --> 02:04:25.120
A customer is a person who buys something at a store.

02:04:25.760 --> 02:04:29.040
The customer put a few items in a bag.

02:04:31.280 --> 02:04:31.760
Deliver

02:04:32.880 --> 02:04:35.840
To deliver something is to take it from one place to another.

02:04:37.040 --> 02:04:39.760
The man delivered Chinese food to my house.

02:04:42.000 --> 02:04:42.320
Earn

02:04:43.600 --> 02:04:46.080
To earn means to get money for the work you do.

02:04:47.280 --> 02:04:50.720
He earns his living as a chef in a great restaurant.

02:04:51.360 --> 02:04:53.200
Gate

02:04:54.320 --> 02:04:55.920
A gate is a type of door.

02:04:56.720 --> 02:04:58.800
Gates are usually made of metal or wood.

02:05:00.000 --> 02:05:03.200
We want to put up a wooden gate around our house.

02:05:05.360 --> 02:05:05.920
Include

02:05:07.040 --> 02:05:10.000
To include something means to have it as part of a group.

02:05:11.200 --> 02:05:13.360
Does this meal include a soft drink?

02:05:15.600 --> 02:05:16.080
Manage

02:05:17.200 --> 02:05:20.320
To manage something means to control or be in charge of it.

02:05:21.360 --> 02:05:23.760
I had to manage the meeting myself.

02:05:25.920 --> 02:05:26.400
Mystery

02:05:27.520 --> 02:05:30.960
A mystery is something that is difficult to understand or explain.

02:05:32.160 --> 02:05:35.200
The path on the map was a complete mystery to me.

02:05:37.440 --> 02:05:37.920
Occur

02:05:39.040 --> 02:05:40.640
To occur means to happen.

02:05:41.840 --> 02:05:43.680
When did the thunderstorm occur?

02:05:45.840 --> 02:05:46.400
Opposite

02:05:47.520 --> 02:05:49.440
If A is the opposite of B,

02:05:50.160 --> 02:05:51.920
A is completely different from B.

02:05:53.040 --> 02:05:55.120
The opposite of black is white.

02:05:57.200 --> 02:05:57.520
Plate

02:05:58.720 --> 02:06:01.760
A plate is a flat round thing that you put food on.

02:06:02.880 --> 02:06:06.240
I put my plate down so I could put some food on it.

02:06:08.320 --> 02:06:08.880
Receive

02:06:09.920 --> 02:06:11.840
To receive something is to get it.

02:06:12.880 --> 02:06:15.120
I received a present on my birthday.

02:06:17.360 --> 02:06:17.840
Reward

02:06:18.480 --> 02:06:23.120
A reward is something given in exchange for good behavior or work.

02:06:24.240 --> 02:06:27.440
He was given a reward for his excellent performance.

02:06:29.680 --> 02:06:30.000
Set

02:06:31.120 --> 02:06:33.360
To set something is to put it somewhere.

02:06:34.400 --> 02:06:36.720
Please set the dice down on the table.

02:06:38.880 --> 02:06:39.360
Steel

02:06:40.480 --> 02:06:43.200
To steal is to take something that is not yours.

02:06:44.480 --> 02:06:46.960
The men tried to steal money from the bank.

02:06:48.640 --> 02:06:49.520
Thief

02:06:50.720 --> 02:06:54.400
A thief is someone who quietly takes things that do not belong to them.

02:06:55.520 --> 02:06:59.280
A thief broke into our home and took my mother's jewelry.

02:07:02.720 --> 02:07:03.840
A better reward

02:07:05.280 --> 02:07:07.200
Jenny delivered food for a restaurant.

02:07:07.840 --> 02:07:09.520
She read the newspaper and said,

02:07:10.080 --> 02:07:12.800
Uh-oh, there was a story about a thief.

02:07:13.520 --> 02:07:16.240
He stole food and no one had seen him.

02:07:17.040 --> 02:07:18.560
Even the police couldn't catch him.

02:07:19.440 --> 02:07:20.880
Jenny was a little scared.

02:07:21.600 --> 02:07:23.120
She worked close to that area.

02:07:23.920 --> 02:07:26.320
The newspaper included a message from the police.

02:07:27.040 --> 02:07:29.200
If anything strange occurs, call us.

02:07:30.080 --> 02:07:33.280
If you help us to catch the thief, you'll earn a reward.

02:07:34.080 --> 02:07:35.040
Jenny talked to Jen.

02:07:35.920 --> 02:07:37.200
He managed the restaurant.

02:07:38.080 --> 02:07:39.440
Do you know about the thief?

02:07:40.320 --> 02:07:41.440
Yes, he said.

02:07:42.080 --> 02:07:44.160
But he steals more than one person can eat.

02:07:44.800 --> 02:07:46.560
And why haven't the police stopped him yet?

02:07:47.360 --> 02:07:48.240
It's a mystery.

02:07:48.960 --> 02:07:51.120
If you see him, contact the police.

02:07:51.760 --> 02:07:52.720
Don't run after him.

02:07:53.440 --> 02:07:55.040
Jenny drove to a customer's house.

02:07:55.840 --> 02:07:58.160
She left her car and opened the gate to the house.

02:07:58.720 --> 02:08:00.480
But then she heard a noise by her car.

02:08:01.360 --> 02:08:02.320
She yelled,

02:08:02.320 --> 02:08:02.720
Thief!

02:08:03.600 --> 02:08:04.560
She wasn't scared.

02:08:05.200 --> 02:08:06.320
She wanted the reward.

02:08:07.200 --> 02:08:09.280
She did the opposite of what Jim told her to do.

02:08:10.000 --> 02:08:11.920
Hey, she yelled,

02:08:11.920 --> 02:08:12.720
Get back here.

02:08:13.520 --> 02:08:15.920
She set the food on the ground and ran to her car.

02:08:16.720 --> 02:08:18.560
But the thief had already left with the food.

02:08:19.520 --> 02:08:21.360
Jenny followed a noise around the corner.

02:08:22.160 --> 02:08:23.040
She was amazed.

02:08:24.000 --> 02:08:25.680
She saw a dog and some puppies.

02:08:26.720 --> 02:08:28.000
They were eating her food.

02:08:29.040 --> 02:08:30.480
They looked thin and scared.

02:08:31.360 --> 02:08:33.280
The actual thief is just a dog.

02:08:34.160 --> 02:08:35.760
She's feeding her puppies,

02:08:35.760 --> 02:08:36.240
she said.

02:08:37.040 --> 02:08:38.800
That's why she steals so much food.

02:08:39.520 --> 02:08:40.480
Jenny felt bad.

02:08:41.360 --> 02:08:44.000
She tried to comfort the dogs with another plate of food.

02:08:44.800 --> 02:08:46.320
Then she took them back to the store.

02:08:47.200 --> 02:08:48.880
Everyone there took a puppy home.

02:08:49.920 --> 02:08:50.960
Jenny called the police.

02:08:51.840 --> 02:08:53.840
She told them there was no real thief.

02:08:54.960 --> 02:08:57.360
Jenny didn't do it to receive the reward anymore.

02:08:58.320 --> 02:08:59.280
She said,

02:08:59.280 --> 02:09:00.320
It was just a dog.

02:09:01.040 --> 02:09:03.440
But there's no charge for catching this thief,

02:09:03.440 --> 02:09:03.920
she said.

02:09:04.720 --> 02:09:06.640
My new dog is a better reward.

02:09:10.640 --> 02:09:11.600
Unit 23.

02:09:12.320 --> 02:09:12.880
Word list.

02:09:14.160 --> 02:09:14.720
Advance.

02:09:15.840 --> 02:09:17.440
To advance is to go forward.

02:09:18.560 --> 02:09:20.560
He advanced up the ladder slowly.

02:09:22.640 --> 02:09:23.200
Athlete.

02:09:24.240 --> 02:09:26.560
An athlete is a person who plays sports.

02:09:27.760 --> 02:09:30.880
Some athletes can play many sports very well.

02:09:33.040 --> 02:09:33.600
Average.

02:09:34.640 --> 02:09:37.280
If something is average, it is at a normal level.

02:09:38.400 --> 02:09:40.160
I'm not rich or poor.

02:09:40.160 --> 02:09:40.960
I'm average.

02:09:43.120 --> 02:09:43.680
Behavior.

02:09:44.800 --> 02:09:46.560
Your behavior is the way you act.

02:09:47.760 --> 02:09:50.480
Their behavior was good this semester.

02:09:50.480 --> 02:09:51.760
They didn't cause trouble.

02:09:53.840 --> 02:09:54.400
Behind.

02:09:55.680 --> 02:09:57.760
Behind means to be at the back of something.

02:09:58.960 --> 02:10:01.520
The little girl was hiding behind a tree.

02:10:03.760 --> 02:10:04.160
Course.

02:10:05.280 --> 02:10:07.200
A course is a class in school.

02:10:08.080 --> 02:10:10.800
I took a PE course in school this year.

02:10:13.040 --> 02:10:13.440
Lower.

02:10:14.560 --> 02:10:16.720
To lower something is to make it go down.

02:10:17.840 --> 02:10:21.600
The chart shows how his production has lowered over the year.

02:10:23.840 --> 02:10:24.240
Match.

02:10:25.360 --> 02:10:27.840
To match is to be the same or similar.

02:10:28.880 --> 02:10:30.720
The two shoes matched.

02:10:30.720 --> 02:10:31.760
They look the same.

02:10:34.080 --> 02:10:34.400
Member.

02:10:35.200 --> 02:10:37.760
A member is a person who is part of a group.

02:10:39.040 --> 02:10:41.760
Julie is the newest member of our team.

02:10:44.080 --> 02:10:44.480
Mental.

02:10:45.520 --> 02:10:48.160
If something is mental, it has to do with your mind.

02:10:49.200 --> 02:10:51.360
I made a mental picture of the room.

02:10:53.680 --> 02:10:54.240
Passenger.

02:10:55.360 --> 02:10:59.440
A passenger is a person who rides in a car, train or airplane.

02:11:00.640 --> 02:11:03.680
One passenger was standing in the subway train.

02:11:05.360 --> 02:11:06.560
Personality.

02:11:07.680 --> 02:11:10.880
Your personality is what you are like and how you behave.

02:11:12.160 --> 02:11:14.080
John has a bad personality.

02:11:16.240 --> 02:11:16.640
Poem.

02:11:17.840 --> 02:11:19.680
A poem is a short kind of writing.

02:11:20.800 --> 02:11:23.360
William Shakespeare wrote many poems.

02:11:25.520 --> 02:11:25.920
Poel.

02:11:27.120 --> 02:11:31.680
A pole is a long, thin stick made of wood or metal that supports things.

02:11:32.640 --> 02:11:35.200
The flag was hanging from the flagpole.

02:11:37.360 --> 02:11:37.920
Remove.

02:11:39.040 --> 02:11:41.120
To remove something is to take it away.

02:11:42.240 --> 02:11:44.320
I removed the nail from the board.

02:11:46.480 --> 02:11:46.960
Safety.

02:11:48.160 --> 02:11:52.080
Safety means to be the condition of being safe and free from danger.

02:11:53.200 --> 02:11:56.400
For his own safety, he was placed in a car seat.

02:11:56.640 --> 02:11:57.440
Shoot.

02:11:58.560 --> 02:12:04.080
To shoot is to fire something like a bullet at someone or something.

02:12:05.280 --> 02:12:08.320
The hunter raised his gun to shoot at the target.

02:12:10.560 --> 02:12:10.960
Sound.

02:12:12.080 --> 02:12:13.920
To sound means to make a noise.

02:12:15.040 --> 02:12:18.000
The alarm clock sounded and woke us all up.

02:12:20.240 --> 02:12:20.640
Swim.

02:12:21.760 --> 02:12:23.680
To swim is to move through water.

02:12:24.560 --> 02:12:26.960
I love to swim in the ocean.

02:12:29.120 --> 02:12:29.520
Web.

02:12:30.720 --> 02:12:32.960
A web is a home made by a spider.

02:12:34.080 --> 02:12:37.040
Mom cleaned the spider webs out of the garage.

02:12:40.560 --> 02:12:41.120
The camp.

02:12:42.480 --> 02:12:46.080
Stacy wanted to stay at a nice hotel for vacation,

02:12:46.880 --> 02:12:50.000
but her parents sent her to a terrible camp instead.

02:12:50.800 --> 02:12:54.880
For breakfast, Stacy liked fresh juice and chocolate milk,

02:12:54.880 --> 02:12:56.800
but she got water at the camp.

02:12:57.440 --> 02:13:00.800
In the afternoon, she wanted to write poems,

02:13:00.800 --> 02:13:02.000
but she had to swim.

02:13:02.800 --> 02:13:05.680
The camp was near an airport with loud planes.

02:13:06.240 --> 02:13:08.320
Spider webs hung over her bed.

02:13:08.880 --> 02:13:12.560
To her, the kid's average behavior was very bad.

02:13:13.440 --> 02:13:16.000
No girl matched her personality.

02:13:16.000 --> 02:13:17.360
She hated it.

02:13:17.360 --> 02:13:19.040
One day, they had a class.

02:13:19.680 --> 02:13:22.320
Mental exercise sounded good to Stacy,

02:13:22.880 --> 02:13:25.120
but it was a course on water safety.

02:13:25.680 --> 02:13:28.480
They learned how to be safe passengers on a boat.

02:13:29.040 --> 02:13:31.680
Stacy didn't ever plan to go on a boat.

02:13:32.240 --> 02:13:34.240
The next day, they played a game.

02:13:35.520 --> 02:13:37.680
There were a red team and a blue team.

02:13:38.560 --> 02:13:40.240
Stacy was on the blue team.

02:13:40.880 --> 02:13:45.200
Each team had to try to remove the other team's flag from a pole.

02:13:46.000 --> 02:13:48.080
They also had to use water guns.

02:13:48.800 --> 02:13:53.440
I'm not much of an athlete, she said, but she still had to play.

02:13:54.160 --> 02:13:57.520
Stacy took a water gun and looked for somewhere to hide.

02:13:58.080 --> 02:14:01.680
A boy said, Stacy, you advance to the middle.

02:14:01.680 --> 02:14:02.720
I will go right.

02:14:03.280 --> 02:14:04.800
Those two will go left.

02:14:05.600 --> 02:14:07.840
Stacy still didn't want to play.

02:14:07.840 --> 02:14:11.520
She walked into the forest and saw a red team player coming.

02:14:12.320 --> 02:14:16.480
Stacy hid behind a tree and then jumped out and shot the other player.

02:14:17.280 --> 02:14:19.360
This is fun, Stacy thought.

02:14:20.160 --> 02:14:25.040
Several minutes after advancing further, Stacy saw the red flag.

02:14:25.040 --> 02:14:27.760
A red team member was watching over it.

02:14:27.760 --> 02:14:29.360
She shot him with her water gun.

02:14:30.000 --> 02:14:32.960
Then she lowered the flag and ran back to her team.

02:14:33.520 --> 02:14:35.040
I got it, she yelled.

02:14:35.680 --> 02:14:36.880
The blue team won.

02:14:37.440 --> 02:14:38.800
Stacy was the hero.

02:14:39.280 --> 02:14:42.400
For the rest of the week, Stacy had fun.

02:14:42.400 --> 02:14:44.240
She even made new friends.

02:14:47.360 --> 02:14:51.920
Unit 24, word list, block.

02:14:53.040 --> 02:14:56.400
A block is a solid piece of wood, stone, or ice.

02:14:57.440 --> 02:14:59.840
I saw a block of ice on the floor.

02:15:02.080 --> 02:15:02.480
Chair.

02:15:03.600 --> 02:15:07.120
Two chair is to give a loud shout of approval or encouragement.

02:15:08.240 --> 02:15:11.120
The crowd all cheered when the home team won.

02:15:13.360 --> 02:15:14.000
Complex

02:15:14.960 --> 02:15:17.840
If something is complex, it has many small parts.

02:15:18.560 --> 02:15:19.760
It is hard to understand.

02:15:20.880 --> 02:15:25.200
A jigsaw puzzle can be complex because it has so many pieces.

02:15:27.360 --> 02:15:27.760
Critic

02:15:28.880 --> 02:15:33.760
A critic is someone who gives their opinions about movies, books, plays, etc.

02:15:34.880 --> 02:15:38.800
The wine critic tasted the wine so he could give his opinion.

02:15:40.960 --> 02:15:41.440
Event

02:15:42.400 --> 02:15:46.080
An event is something that happens, especially something important.

02:15:47.120 --> 02:15:50.400
Finishing high school was a major event in his life.

02:15:52.480 --> 02:15:53.120
Exercise

02:15:54.240 --> 02:15:58.000
Two exercises is to run or play sports so that you can be healthy.

02:15:59.120 --> 02:16:01.120
You should exercise every day.

02:16:03.360 --> 02:16:03.600
Fit

02:16:04.720 --> 02:16:08.560
If something fits, it is small enough or the right size to go there.

02:16:09.520 --> 02:16:12.320
The colorful eggs fit into the box.

02:16:14.400 --> 02:16:14.960
Friendship

02:16:16.000 --> 02:16:19.040
Friendship is the relationship between people who are friends.

02:16:20.240 --> 02:16:23.760
Michael and Lisa have a very strong friendship with each other.

02:16:26.080 --> 02:16:26.480
Guide

02:16:27.520 --> 02:16:29.680
A guide is someone who shows you where to go.

02:16:30.880 --> 02:16:32.880
We followed a guide at the park.

02:16:35.040 --> 02:16:35.440
Lack

02:16:36.400 --> 02:16:39.200
If there is a lack of something, there is not enough of it.

02:16:40.320 --> 02:16:42.800
His only problem is a lack of money.

02:16:45.040 --> 02:16:45.520
Passage

02:16:46.640 --> 02:16:50.800
A passage is a long area with walls that goes from one place to another.

02:16:51.920 --> 02:16:55.360
The long passage led us to the other side of the field.

02:16:57.440 --> 02:16:58.000
Perform

02:16:59.120 --> 02:17:02.080
To perform is to do something in front of people who watch.

02:17:03.040 --> 02:17:05.600
He will perform a song for the class.

02:17:07.760 --> 02:17:08.240
Pressure

02:17:09.280 --> 02:17:11.920
Pressure is what you apply to make someone do something.

02:17:12.960 --> 02:17:15.760
They put pressure on him to change his mind.

02:17:17.840 --> 02:17:18.400
Probable

02:17:19.520 --> 02:17:22.000
If something is probable, it is likely to happen.

02:17:23.040 --> 02:17:27.280
It is probable that you will get a good grade if you study for the test.

02:17:29.360 --> 02:17:29.840
Public

02:17:30.800 --> 02:17:33.920
If something is public, it is meant for everyone to use.

02:17:35.120 --> 02:17:38.000
I went to the public park to play with my friends.

02:17:40.160 --> 02:17:40.640
Strike

02:17:41.600 --> 02:17:44.000
To strike someone or something is to hit them.

02:17:45.200 --> 02:17:47.440
She struck the other girl in the face.

02:17:49.680 --> 02:17:50.240
Support

02:17:51.280 --> 02:17:54.720
To support something is to like it and help it be successful.

02:17:55.840 --> 02:17:58.560
Everyone at work supports the new plan.

02:18:00.720 --> 02:18:01.200
Task

02:18:02.320 --> 02:18:04.560
A task is work that someone has to do.

02:18:05.760 --> 02:18:08.320
Who has the task of building the brick wall?

02:18:10.560 --> 02:18:10.880
Term

02:18:12.000 --> 02:18:13.760
A term is a word for something.

02:18:14.800 --> 02:18:18.240
I often use the term oops when I make a mistake.

02:18:20.400 --> 02:18:20.880
Unite

02:18:21.920 --> 02:18:24.400
To unite is to get together to do something.

02:18:25.520 --> 02:18:28.800
If we unite, we can finish our project faster.

02:18:30.800 --> 02:18:33.520
A strong friendship

02:18:34.720 --> 02:18:36.800
Tim was the strongest man in the town.

02:18:37.520 --> 02:18:39.840
When he played sports, he always won.

02:18:40.720 --> 02:18:43.520
He performed and exercised in the public park.

02:18:44.240 --> 02:18:46.640
He did this to show everyone how strong he was.

02:18:47.520 --> 02:18:50.160
Most people liked him, but one man didn't.

02:18:50.880 --> 02:18:51.760
His name was Jack.

02:18:52.560 --> 02:18:53.520
Jack hated Tim.

02:18:54.240 --> 02:18:57.120
Jack was a movie critic and the smartest man in town.

02:18:57.680 --> 02:19:01.200
He could solve complex math problems, but no one cared.

02:19:02.240 --> 02:19:03.920
Jack wanted to be famous like Tim.

02:19:04.960 --> 02:19:07.200
One day, there was an unusual event.

02:19:08.000 --> 02:19:09.520
A big storm came suddenly.

02:19:10.400 --> 02:19:11.600
Snow covered the town.

02:19:12.320 --> 02:19:13.440
No one could get out.

02:19:14.320 --> 02:19:15.200
They needed food.

02:19:15.840 --> 02:19:19.120
The people said, this is a task for a strong man.

02:19:20.400 --> 02:19:22.000
Tim was under pressure to save them.

02:19:22.800 --> 02:19:25.680
But Jack wanted to be the hero, so they both went.

02:19:26.480 --> 02:19:29.840
Tim said, you can't help because of your lack of strength.

02:19:30.560 --> 02:19:33.040
But Jack found some small passages under the snow.

02:19:34.160 --> 02:19:35.760
One of them led toward another town.

02:19:36.720 --> 02:19:37.760
That town had food.

02:19:38.640 --> 02:19:42.400
Because Tim was so big and strong, he almost couldn't fit inside.

02:19:43.200 --> 02:19:45.440
They walked until there was a block of ice in their way.

02:19:46.400 --> 02:19:50.720
Jack said, we can't get past it, but if you strike it, it might break.

02:19:51.600 --> 02:19:52.880
Tim knew that was probable.

02:19:53.680 --> 02:19:54.320
He broke it.

02:19:55.200 --> 02:19:57.760
When there were more ice blocks, Tim broke them.

02:19:58.560 --> 02:19:59.520
That made him tired.

02:20:00.240 --> 02:20:01.360
He couldn't walk anymore.

02:20:02.240 --> 02:20:05.120
Jack said, let's unite and support each other.

02:20:05.920 --> 02:20:07.040
I'll get the food alone.

02:20:07.680 --> 02:20:08.480
You rest here.

02:20:09.440 --> 02:20:10.720
Jack came back with food.

02:20:11.360 --> 02:20:13.520
Tim couldn't remember which passage led home.

02:20:14.320 --> 02:20:15.840
He needed Jack to be his guide.

02:20:16.880 --> 02:20:19.040
The men became friends by working together.

02:20:19.920 --> 02:20:22.880
In town, people saw Jack with the food and cheered.

02:20:23.600 --> 02:20:26.560
They called Jack a hero, but Jack didn't care.

02:20:27.360 --> 02:20:28.720
He was thinking of something else.

02:20:29.600 --> 02:20:34.240
He said to Tim, I thought I was smart, but I learned a new term today.

02:20:35.120 --> 02:20:35.600
Friendship.

02:20:39.600 --> 02:20:41.680
Unit 25, word list.

02:20:42.960 --> 02:20:43.600
Associate

02:20:44.720 --> 02:20:48.000
To associate means to connect something with a person or thing.

02:20:48.800 --> 02:20:52.880
Most people associate birthday parties with having fun.

02:20:55.120 --> 02:20:55.680
Environment.

02:20:56.880 --> 02:20:59.600
The environment is the place where people work or live.

02:21:00.880 --> 02:21:04.320
Keeping our environment clean is important to our health.

02:21:06.560 --> 02:21:07.040
Factory.

02:21:08.240 --> 02:21:11.440
A factory is a building where things are made or put together.

02:21:12.560 --> 02:21:15.440
We have only one factory in our town.

02:21:16.160 --> 02:21:18.800
A feature is an important part of something.

02:21:19.760 --> 02:21:21.760
The cell phone has many features.

02:21:23.760 --> 02:21:24.560
Instance.

02:21:25.600 --> 02:21:27.600
An instance is an example of something.

02:21:28.800 --> 02:21:31.040
I have never experienced an instance of hate.

02:21:32.240 --> 02:21:32.960
Have you?

02:21:34.640 --> 02:21:35.200
Involved.

02:21:36.240 --> 02:21:38.880
To involve means to be actively taking part in something.

02:21:40.000 --> 02:21:42.640
The whole family was involved in providing information.

02:21:43.200 --> 02:21:46.240
The whole family was involved in playing the game.

02:21:48.480 --> 02:21:48.960
Medicine.

02:21:50.240 --> 02:21:53.520
Medicine is something you take to feel better or treat an illness.

02:21:54.640 --> 02:21:57.200
The doctor gave me medicine for my called.

02:21:59.440 --> 02:21:59.760
Mix.

02:22:00.960 --> 02:22:02.960
A mix is different things put together.

02:22:04.080 --> 02:22:08.080
The green mix we made in science class spilled onto the table.

02:22:10.240 --> 02:22:10.800
Organize.

02:22:11.760 --> 02:22:15.200
To organize is to plan or get ready for an event.

02:22:16.400 --> 02:22:19.600
Make a list to help you organize the things you need.

02:22:21.840 --> 02:22:22.320
Period.

02:22:23.440 --> 02:22:26.080
A period is an amount of time when something happens.

02:22:27.200 --> 02:22:30.400
In one period in Europe, there were many nights.

02:22:32.560 --> 02:22:33.200
Populate.

02:22:34.240 --> 02:22:36.800
If people populate an area, they live there.

02:22:38.080 --> 02:22:40.400
Billions of people populate the earth.

02:22:41.600 --> 02:22:43.040
Produce.

02:22:44.160 --> 02:22:46.400
To produce something is to make or grow it.

02:22:47.600 --> 02:22:50.400
This tree produces apples every year.

02:22:52.720 --> 02:22:53.120
Range.

02:22:54.320 --> 02:22:57.120
A range is a number or a set of similar things.

02:22:58.240 --> 02:23:00.720
I saw a range of cars to choose from.

02:23:02.880 --> 02:23:03.600
Recognize.

02:23:04.640 --> 02:23:08.000
To recognize something is to know it because you have seen it before.

02:23:08.960 --> 02:23:12.560
I recognized an old friend from many years ago.

02:23:14.800 --> 02:23:15.280
Regular.

02:23:16.400 --> 02:23:20.560
If something is regular, it happens often and in equal amounts of time.

02:23:21.680 --> 02:23:24.400
Our regular lunch time is around noon.

02:23:26.720 --> 02:23:27.120
Sign.

02:23:28.240 --> 02:23:33.120
A sign is a notice giving information, directions, a warning, etc.

02:23:34.080 --> 02:23:37.680
The sign indicated that today would be a bad day.

02:23:39.840 --> 02:23:40.160
Tip.

02:23:41.200 --> 02:23:42.960
A tip is a pointed end of something.

02:23:44.160 --> 02:23:46.560
The tip of his pen was very sharp.

02:23:48.720 --> 02:23:49.200
Tradition.

02:23:50.320 --> 02:23:53.440
A tradition is something people have been doing for a long time.

02:23:54.800 --> 02:23:57.520
Marriage is a tradition all over the world.

02:23:59.680 --> 02:24:00.160
Trash.

02:24:01.120 --> 02:24:04.800
Trash is waste material or unwanted or worthless things.

02:24:05.920 --> 02:24:08.560
Please take out the trash. It smells bad.

02:24:10.800 --> 02:24:11.200
Wide.

02:24:12.240 --> 02:24:15.440
If something is wide, it is large from side to side.

02:24:16.640 --> 02:24:19.040
The door was as wide as my arms.

02:24:22.560 --> 02:24:23.520
Joe spawned.

02:24:24.800 --> 02:24:27.040
Joe made the world a better place.

02:24:27.680 --> 02:24:30.000
He got the idea to do that at school.

02:24:30.880 --> 02:24:34.320
He watched a video there. It was about a factory.

02:24:35.120 --> 02:24:39.040
This factory produced a lot of trash and put it in a river.

02:24:39.760 --> 02:24:42.160
The trash and water were a bad mix.

02:24:42.800 --> 02:24:46.560
People populated the area by the river and drank its water.

02:24:47.360 --> 02:24:48.480
This made them sick.

02:24:49.120 --> 02:24:53.040
Many of them needed medicine and made regular visits to doctors.

02:24:53.680 --> 02:24:56.320
But the video wasn't all bad news.

02:24:56.320 --> 02:25:00.160
It showed ways to pick up trash and why it's important to do this.

02:25:00.800 --> 02:25:04.240
It said people can make a difference to their environment.

02:25:04.240 --> 02:25:09.120
The video's important features made Joe associate trash with hurting people.

02:25:09.920 --> 02:25:15.280
One day, Joe walked through a park. He recognized some of the problems from the video.

02:25:16.080 --> 02:25:19.920
One instance of these problems was the trash in the pond.

02:25:19.920 --> 02:25:23.520
It was full of plastic cups. There was too much trash.

02:25:24.080 --> 02:25:26.080
Joe didn't want it to hurt anyone.

02:25:26.640 --> 02:25:29.040
He told his grandfather about the park.

02:25:29.600 --> 02:25:31.200
His grandfather said,

02:25:31.200 --> 02:25:34.480
You know, it's a tradition in our family to help people.

02:25:35.280 --> 02:25:37.520
That's why we give food to poor people.

02:25:38.240 --> 02:25:40.960
Maybe you can help people by cleaning the park.

02:25:41.520 --> 02:25:44.080
Cleaning the park would involve hard work.

02:25:44.800 --> 02:25:47.520
Joe decided to organize a group to help him.

02:25:48.080 --> 02:25:50.320
He chose a wide area of the park.

02:25:50.880 --> 02:25:52.320
It had the most trash.

02:25:52.960 --> 02:25:55.120
He asked his family and friends to come.

02:25:55.760 --> 02:25:58.720
On Saturday, he gave everyone a sharp stick.

02:25:59.440 --> 02:26:00.800
They wondered why?

02:26:00.800 --> 02:26:04.800
He said, You used the stick's tip to pick up trash.

02:26:04.800 --> 02:26:06.000
This makes it easier.

02:26:06.640 --> 02:26:08.560
They worked for six weeks.

02:26:08.560 --> 02:26:10.480
Different people helped each time.

02:26:11.040 --> 02:26:12.640
But Joe was always there.

02:26:13.360 --> 02:26:17.520
In that period of time, Joe saw a range of results.

02:26:17.520 --> 02:26:19.360
There was no trash in the water.

02:26:19.920 --> 02:26:21.120
People could swim in it.

02:26:21.680 --> 02:26:23.680
Joe knew that was a good sign.

02:26:24.240 --> 02:26:27.040
He was happy because he helped his environment.

02:26:31.040 --> 02:26:34.800
Unit 26, word list, advice.

02:26:36.000 --> 02:26:38.000
Advice is an opinion about what to do.

02:26:39.200 --> 02:26:42.000
I don't know how to study for my exams.

02:26:42.000 --> 02:26:43.600
Can you give me some advice?

02:26:45.760 --> 02:26:46.240
A long.

02:26:47.440 --> 02:26:52.320
A long means to move from one part of a road, river, etc. to another.

02:26:53.120 --> 02:26:58.080
Walk along this tunnel for 10 minutes and you'll see a door on the left.

02:27:00.320 --> 02:27:00.880
Attention.

02:27:02.000 --> 02:27:05.520
Attention is the notice, thought, or consideration of someone.

02:27:06.640 --> 02:27:10.000
His work got the attention of two of his co-workers.

02:27:12.160 --> 02:27:12.720
Attract.

02:27:13.760 --> 02:27:18.000
To attract means to make a person or thing come closer or be interested.

02:27:19.120 --> 02:27:21.040
The magnet attracted the metal.

02:27:23.200 --> 02:27:23.600
Climb.

02:27:24.800 --> 02:27:28.720
To climb means to use your hands and feet to go up on something.

02:27:29.840 --> 02:27:32.240
The girl's climb to the top of the mountain.

02:27:34.480 --> 02:27:34.880
Drop.

02:27:35.920 --> 02:27:38.800
To drop is to fall or allow something to fall.

02:27:39.920 --> 02:27:42.880
A small amount of water dropped from the bottle.

02:27:45.040 --> 02:27:45.440
Final.

02:27:46.560 --> 02:27:48.960
If something is final, it is the last part.

02:27:49.920 --> 02:27:54.240
In the final part of the film, the man and the woman got married.

02:27:56.400 --> 02:27:56.800
Further.

02:27:57.920 --> 02:28:01.040
Further is used to say something is from a distance or time.

02:28:02.240 --> 02:28:05.280
The escalator is further along than I thought.

02:28:07.440 --> 02:28:08.000
Apply.

02:28:09.120 --> 02:28:11.920
To imply something is to suggest it without saying it.

02:28:12.960 --> 02:28:16.800
The man implied that he wanted the job, but he didn't say so.

02:28:19.040 --> 02:28:19.600
Maintain.

02:28:20.800 --> 02:28:23.280
To maintain means to make something stay the same.

02:28:24.480 --> 02:28:26.800
The balls maintain constant movement.

02:28:29.040 --> 02:28:29.440
Neither.

02:28:30.720 --> 02:28:33.440
You use neither to connect two negative statements.

02:28:34.720 --> 02:28:39.440
Neither the pass on the left nor the pass on the right will lead us home.

02:28:41.680 --> 02:28:42.240
Otherwise.

02:28:43.440 --> 02:28:46.160
Otherwise means different or in another way.

02:28:46.800 --> 02:28:50.800
It's good to stay active, otherwise you'll gain weight.

02:28:52.960 --> 02:28:53.440
Physical.

02:28:54.560 --> 02:28:58.480
If something is physical, it is related to your body and not your mind.

02:28:59.760 --> 02:29:01.920
Biking is good for your physical health.

02:29:04.080 --> 02:29:04.480
Prove.

02:29:05.600 --> 02:29:07.920
To prove something is to show that it is true.

02:29:09.200 --> 02:29:11.760
My teacher proved the answer on the board.

02:29:12.400 --> 02:29:14.400
React.

02:29:15.600 --> 02:29:19.520
To react is to act in a certain way because of something that happened.

02:29:20.880 --> 02:29:22.960
James reacted badly to the news.

02:29:25.280 --> 02:29:25.680
Ride.

02:29:26.880 --> 02:29:29.120
To ride something is to travel on it.

02:29:29.840 --> 02:29:32.720
You can ride an animal, a bike, etc.

02:29:33.760 --> 02:29:36.960
I will ride a roller coaster for the first time today.

02:29:39.120 --> 02:29:39.760
Situated.

02:29:40.720 --> 02:29:43.920
If something is situated somewhere, it is in that place.

02:29:44.960 --> 02:29:47.840
The whiteboard is situated between the two men.

02:29:50.000 --> 02:29:50.640
Society.

02:29:51.840 --> 02:29:54.720
Society is people and the way that they live.

02:29:55.840 --> 02:29:59.040
Society expects people to be good and honest.

02:30:01.200 --> 02:30:01.680
Standard.

02:30:02.720 --> 02:30:05.760
A standard is what people considered normal or good.

02:30:06.560 --> 02:30:10.800
And this older model TV is below our store standards.

02:30:12.960 --> 02:30:13.600
Suggest.

02:30:14.640 --> 02:30:18.160
To suggest something means to give an idea or plan about it.

02:30:19.280 --> 02:30:21.840
He suggested that we go to see his boss.

02:30:25.280 --> 02:30:26.560
Archie and his donkey.

02:30:27.760 --> 02:30:29.360
Old Archie needed some money.

02:30:30.000 --> 02:30:31.600
He decided to sell his donkey.

02:30:32.320 --> 02:30:34.320
So he and his son, Tom, went to town.

02:30:34.960 --> 02:30:36.880
It was situated many miles away.

02:30:38.080 --> 02:30:39.440
Soon they met a woman.

02:30:40.560 --> 02:30:41.760
Where are you going?

02:30:41.760 --> 02:30:42.320
She asked.

02:30:43.120 --> 02:30:44.080
To town.

02:30:44.080 --> 02:30:44.640
Said Archie.

02:30:45.440 --> 02:30:48.000
Any smart person would ride the donkey.

02:30:48.000 --> 02:30:48.480
She said.

02:30:49.520 --> 02:30:50.960
What are you implying?

02:30:50.960 --> 02:30:51.600
Archie asked.

02:30:52.240 --> 02:30:53.280
I'm very smart.

02:30:54.000 --> 02:30:55.360
Archie wanted to look smart.

02:30:56.080 --> 02:30:57.760
So he climbed onto the donkey.

02:30:58.560 --> 02:31:00.640
Then they continued in the direction of the town.

02:31:01.440 --> 02:31:04.240
Further along the road, they met a farmer.

02:31:04.880 --> 02:31:06.080
Hello, said Archie.

02:31:06.720 --> 02:31:08.160
We want to sell this donkey.

02:31:08.720 --> 02:31:09.680
Do you want to buy it?

02:31:10.480 --> 02:31:12.960
I don't need a donkey, said the farmer.

02:31:13.600 --> 02:31:16.240
But if you want my advice, don't ride it.

02:31:16.880 --> 02:31:19.200
The donkey needs to be in good physical condition.

02:31:20.000 --> 02:31:21.600
Good idea, said Archie.

02:31:22.240 --> 02:31:24.240
Tom, I want you to ride it.

02:31:24.240 --> 02:31:24.880
You're lighter.

02:31:26.000 --> 02:31:28.320
Neither you nor your son should ride it.

02:31:28.880 --> 02:31:30.000
It looks very tired.

02:31:30.800 --> 02:31:33.600
You should carry the donkey, suggested the farmer.

02:31:34.560 --> 02:31:35.920
You're right, said Archie.

02:31:36.560 --> 02:31:37.360
Come on, Tom.

02:31:37.920 --> 02:31:39.680
We'll carry it for the final few miles.

02:31:40.480 --> 02:31:41.840
The donkey was very heavy.

02:31:42.560 --> 02:31:44.240
And they couldn't maintain a good speed.

02:31:44.960 --> 02:31:46.880
They didn't arrive until late in the evening.

02:31:47.760 --> 02:31:49.920
At last, they walked into the town.

02:31:50.640 --> 02:31:53.360
But there they attracted the attention of some teenage boys.

02:31:54.160 --> 02:31:55.680
They laughed at Tom and Archie.

02:31:56.240 --> 02:31:57.920
They started to throw stones at them.

02:31:58.560 --> 02:32:00.160
The donkey reacted by kicking.

02:32:00.880 --> 02:32:02.640
Tom and Archie dropped the donkey.

02:32:03.600 --> 02:32:05.760
It fell on the ground, and they ran away.

02:32:06.640 --> 02:32:07.920
Archie lost his donkey.

02:32:08.880 --> 02:32:10.320
He went home with no money.

02:32:11.280 --> 02:32:12.720
What does this story teach us?

02:32:13.760 --> 02:32:16.080
We cannot please everyone in our society.

02:32:17.200 --> 02:32:18.640
Don't take everyone's advice.

02:32:19.280 --> 02:32:20.560
But set your own standards.

02:32:21.440 --> 02:32:24.400
Prove to everyone that you can make decisions by yourself.

02:32:25.120 --> 02:32:28.000
Otherwise, you may end up with nothing at all.

02:32:31.520 --> 02:32:34.160
Unit 27, word list.

02:32:35.440 --> 02:32:39.440
Actually, actually means, in fact, or really.

02:32:40.560 --> 02:32:44.480
My dad looks a little mean, but actually, he's very kind.

02:32:46.720 --> 02:32:47.120
Bite.

02:32:48.400 --> 02:32:52.640
Bite is the act of using your teeth to cut and tear into something.

02:32:53.760 --> 02:32:56.560
The boy took a big bite out of his hamburger.

02:32:57.200 --> 02:33:00.160
The coast is the land by an ocean.

02:33:00.880 --> 02:33:03.440
I stayed on the southern coast of Australia.

02:33:04.880 --> 02:33:05.680
Deal.

02:33:06.320 --> 02:33:08.960
A deal is an agreement that you have with another person.

02:33:09.920 --> 02:33:13.360
I made a deal with the other company to give us some money.

02:33:15.040 --> 02:33:16.000
Desert.

02:33:16.800 --> 02:33:20.400
The desert is an area of land without many plants or water.

02:33:21.360 --> 02:33:22.720
Not many plants.

02:33:22.800 --> 02:33:24.320
Grow in the desert.

02:33:25.760 --> 02:33:26.800
Earthquake.

02:33:27.360 --> 02:33:29.840
An earthquake is a shaking movement of the ground.

02:33:31.040 --> 02:33:33.600
The building shook during the earthquake.

02:33:35.120 --> 02:33:36.320
Effective.

02:33:36.960 --> 02:33:39.520
If something is effective, it works well.

02:33:40.480 --> 02:33:43.280
Swimming is an effective way to stay healthy.

02:33:45.280 --> 02:33:46.080
Examine.

02:33:46.640 --> 02:33:49.280
To examine something is too hard to use.

02:33:49.680 --> 02:33:50.240
Examine.

02:33:51.360 --> 02:33:53.840
To examine something is too look at it carefully.

02:33:54.960 --> 02:33:57.200
The doctor examined my eyes today.

02:33:59.360 --> 02:33:59.760
False.

02:34:00.880 --> 02:34:03.280
If something is false, it is not correct.

02:34:04.400 --> 02:34:07.760
If you think the answer is false, press the red button.

02:34:10.000 --> 02:34:10.400
Gift.

02:34:11.520 --> 02:34:13.280
A gift is something you give someone.

02:34:14.560 --> 02:34:17.040
Dave received many gifts for Christmas.

02:34:19.280 --> 02:34:19.680
Hunger.

02:34:20.800 --> 02:34:23.200
Hunger is the feeling that you get when you need to eat.

02:34:24.400 --> 02:34:27.760
After playing all day long, he was filled with hunger.

02:34:29.920 --> 02:34:30.400
Imagine.

02:34:31.520 --> 02:34:34.240
To imagine something is to think of it in your mind.

02:34:35.520 --> 02:34:38.560
Sally imagined herself winning lots of money.

02:34:40.800 --> 02:34:41.200
Journey.

02:34:42.320 --> 02:34:43.920
A journey is a long trip.

02:34:45.120 --> 02:34:48.400
I went on a journey across the country with my parents.

02:34:50.080 --> 02:34:50.960
Puzzle.

02:34:52.080 --> 02:34:54.640
A puzzle is something that is hard to understand.

02:34:55.840 --> 02:34:57.920
The question was a puzzle to him.

02:35:00.080 --> 02:35:00.400
Quite.

02:35:01.600 --> 02:35:05.120
Quite is used to say that something is complete or very much.

02:35:06.240 --> 02:35:09.040
I think typing on a keyboard is quite easy.

02:35:11.280 --> 02:35:11.680
Rather.

02:35:12.960 --> 02:35:16.160
Rather is used when you want to do one thing but not the other.

02:35:17.120 --> 02:35:20.000
I would rather have the red one than the blue one.

02:35:22.240 --> 02:35:22.800
Specific.

02:35:24.000 --> 02:35:27.120
If something is specific, it is precise or exact.

02:35:28.160 --> 02:35:30.960
Please choose a specific place on the map.

02:35:33.040 --> 02:35:33.360
Tour.

02:35:34.560 --> 02:35:37.440
A tour is a short trip in which you see many sites.

02:35:38.560 --> 02:35:40.960
I took a tour of Asia and Europe.

02:35:41.520 --> 02:35:42.400
A trip.

02:35:43.040 --> 02:35:46.560
A trip is a journey to a certain place.

02:35:47.760 --> 02:35:50.080
Can took a trip to the city yesterday.

02:35:52.240 --> 02:35:52.720
Value.

02:35:53.840 --> 02:35:56.480
If something has value, it is worth a lot of money.

02:35:57.600 --> 02:36:00.480
Matthew found a treasure of very high value.

02:36:03.920 --> 02:36:05.600
The spider and the bird.

02:36:06.800 --> 02:36:09.680
There was once a very big spider.

02:36:09.680 --> 02:36:12.880
If a bug got into his web, he would examine it.

02:36:13.520 --> 02:36:16.320
However, he didn't eat the bug right away.

02:36:17.120 --> 02:36:19.280
He asked the bug a question first.

02:36:19.920 --> 02:36:22.240
It was always quite a difficult puzzle.

02:36:22.800 --> 02:36:25.840
If the bug's answer was correct, he let it go.

02:36:26.400 --> 02:36:27.840
If not, he ate it.

02:36:28.640 --> 02:36:32.800
One day, a small bird on a journey flew into the spider's web.

02:36:33.520 --> 02:36:36.480
The spider couldn't imagine eating a bird.

02:36:36.480 --> 02:36:37.520
It was so big.

02:36:38.160 --> 02:36:40.400
But his hunger was too great.

02:36:40.400 --> 02:36:41.840
He said to the bird,

02:36:41.840 --> 02:36:45.360
If you cannot give me a specific answer, I will eat you.

02:36:46.000 --> 02:36:46.960
The bird laughed.

02:36:47.520 --> 02:36:49.040
I could eat you.

02:36:49.040 --> 02:36:51.600
But the bird was actually scared.

02:36:51.600 --> 02:36:54.960
She had used all her energy trying to get out of the web.

02:36:55.600 --> 02:36:59.680
And her spider's bite can be very effective in killing animals.

02:37:00.240 --> 02:37:01.600
Please don't eat me.

02:37:01.600 --> 02:37:02.800
The bird said,

02:37:02.800 --> 02:37:04.800
I would rather make a deal with you.

02:37:05.520 --> 02:37:07.440
Okay, the spider said.

02:37:07.440 --> 02:37:10.160
If your answer is right, I will let you go.

02:37:10.720 --> 02:37:13.200
If not, you must give me a gift.

02:37:13.200 --> 02:37:15.280
It must be something of great value.

02:37:15.920 --> 02:37:17.120
The bird said,

02:37:17.120 --> 02:37:19.440
You can pick anything you want to eat.

02:37:19.440 --> 02:37:20.800
I will find it for you.

02:37:21.360 --> 02:37:22.480
The spider agreed.

02:37:23.120 --> 02:37:25.520
Where can you take a trip to the coast?

02:37:25.520 --> 02:37:28.560
The desert and the mountains at the same time.

02:37:28.560 --> 02:37:29.600
The spider asked.

02:37:30.160 --> 02:37:31.280
The bird asked,

02:37:31.280 --> 02:37:33.520
Does this place have earthquakes?

02:37:33.520 --> 02:37:35.600
But the spider did not say anything.

02:37:36.160 --> 02:37:38.800
I can see those places when I fly.

02:37:38.800 --> 02:37:40.560
Is the sky the right answer?

02:37:41.440 --> 02:37:43.280
False said the spider.

02:37:43.280 --> 02:37:44.720
The answer is Hawaii.

02:37:45.280 --> 02:37:47.280
Now you must find some bugs for me.

02:37:48.000 --> 02:37:50.240
The spider climbed on the bird's back.

02:37:50.800 --> 02:37:52.800
They flew and ate bugs together.

02:37:53.440 --> 02:37:55.200
They took a tour of the forest.

02:37:55.920 --> 02:37:58.320
Then the bird took the spider home.

02:37:59.040 --> 02:38:00.560
From that day on,

02:38:00.560 --> 02:38:01.840
they were friends,

02:38:01.840 --> 02:38:04.320
and they never tried to eat each other again.

02:38:08.400 --> 02:38:09.760
Unit 28.

02:38:09.760 --> 02:38:10.320
Word list.

02:38:11.520 --> 02:38:11.920
Band.

02:38:13.120 --> 02:38:15.440
A band is a group of people who play music.

02:38:16.560 --> 02:38:18.480
My brother is in a rock band.

02:38:20.640 --> 02:38:21.120
Barely.

02:38:22.320 --> 02:38:24.640
Barely means by the smallest amount.

02:38:24.640 --> 02:38:25.440
Almost not.

02:38:26.560 --> 02:38:29.840
I barely had enough money to pay for my bus ticket.

02:38:31.520 --> 02:38:32.560
Boring.

02:38:33.600 --> 02:38:35.840
If something is boring, it is not fun.

02:38:37.040 --> 02:38:39.040
I think the internet is boring.

02:38:41.200 --> 02:38:41.680
Cancel.

02:38:42.800 --> 02:38:45.920
Do cancel means to decide that an event

02:38:45.920 --> 02:38:47.840
or a request will not happen.

02:38:49.040 --> 02:38:52.320
She canceled the rest of her plans because of the rain.

02:38:54.480 --> 02:38:55.040
Driveway.

02:38:56.240 --> 02:38:59.920
A driveway is a short private road that leads to a person's home.

02:39:01.120 --> 02:39:04.080
The long driveway led us to their new house.

02:39:06.240 --> 02:39:06.800
Garbage.

02:39:07.920 --> 02:39:11.920
Garbage is waste material like unwanted or spoiled food,

02:39:11.920 --> 02:39:13.840
bottles, paper, etc.

02:39:14.880 --> 02:39:17.760
The boy cleaned up the garbage around his house.

02:39:20.000 --> 02:39:20.480
Instrument.

02:39:21.600 --> 02:39:25.520
An instrument is something designed to do a certain task like music.

02:39:26.720 --> 02:39:29.520
My favorite musical instrument is the piano.

02:39:31.520 --> 02:39:32.080
List.

02:39:33.200 --> 02:39:37.040
A list is a record of information printed with an item on each line.

02:39:38.320 --> 02:39:40.880
My mom makes a list of groceries to buy.

02:39:43.200 --> 02:39:43.600
Magic.

02:39:44.800 --> 02:39:47.120
Magic is the power to do impossible things.

02:39:48.240 --> 02:39:51.920
The magician used magic to pull a rabbit out of his hat.

02:39:54.160 --> 02:39:54.640
Message.

02:39:55.760 --> 02:39:58.560
A message is a set of words that you send to someone.

02:39:59.520 --> 02:40:02.240
I left a message for you in the envelope.

02:40:04.640 --> 02:40:05.040
Notice.

02:40:06.160 --> 02:40:08.640
To notice something is to see it for the first time.

02:40:09.840 --> 02:40:11.200
Did you notice the view?

02:40:13.440 --> 02:40:13.760
Own.

02:40:14.960 --> 02:40:16.960
To own something means to have it.

02:40:17.760 --> 02:40:18.960
That thing belongs to you.

02:40:20.080 --> 02:40:22.160
My grandfather owns that house.

02:40:24.320 --> 02:40:24.800
Predict.

02:40:25.840 --> 02:40:28.320
To predict something is to say that it will happen.

02:40:29.520 --> 02:40:32.160
She predicted that I would get married next year.

02:40:34.240 --> 02:40:34.800
Professor.

02:40:35.920 --> 02:40:38.480
A professor is a person who teaches in college.

02:40:39.600 --> 02:40:42.960
Mike Science Professor knows a lot about physics.

02:40:45.120 --> 02:40:45.520
Rush.

02:40:46.640 --> 02:40:50.400
To rush is to go somewhere or do something very quickly.

02:40:51.600 --> 02:40:53.680
Nancy Rush to finish her homework.

02:40:55.840 --> 02:40:56.320
Schedule.

02:40:56.960 --> 02:41:00.240
A schedule is a plan that tells you when to do things.

02:41:01.440 --> 02:41:03.440
What is your class schedule for today?

02:41:05.760 --> 02:41:06.080
Share.

02:41:07.200 --> 02:41:10.160
To share something is to give some of it to another person.

02:41:11.440 --> 02:41:13.200
Jimmy shared his apple with me.

02:41:15.440 --> 02:41:16.000
Stage.

02:41:17.120 --> 02:41:21.200
A stage is a place where actors or musicians act or sing.

02:41:22.320 --> 02:41:24.480
A large screen was on the stage.

02:41:26.800 --> 02:41:27.280
Storm.

02:41:28.480 --> 02:41:30.240
A storm is very bad weather.

02:41:30.960 --> 02:41:32.480
There is a lot of rain or snow.

02:41:33.760 --> 02:41:36.240
Did that storm wake you up last night?

02:41:38.400 --> 02:41:38.880
Within.

02:41:40.080 --> 02:41:43.280
You use within to say that something is inside another thing.

02:41:44.560 --> 02:41:46.800
Within the box there was a pizza.

02:41:50.320 --> 02:41:50.960
The party.

02:41:52.160 --> 02:41:53.920
Cody's family moved to a new house.

02:41:54.640 --> 02:41:56.640
His dad got a new job as a professor.

02:41:57.280 --> 02:41:58.560
Cody liked his new town.

02:41:59.120 --> 02:42:00.560
But he missed his grandparents.

02:42:01.280 --> 02:42:03.920
For his birthday Cody wanted to have a party.

02:42:04.560 --> 02:42:05.360
His dad said.

02:42:06.000 --> 02:42:08.160
Yes, we could even have a band play.

02:42:08.880 --> 02:42:12.400
On the day of the party Cody woke up and rushed to get ready.

02:42:12.960 --> 02:42:15.040
He started to check his list of things to do.

02:42:15.920 --> 02:42:17.120
He was so excited.

02:42:18.000 --> 02:42:19.600
But then he noticed something terrible.

02:42:20.400 --> 02:42:22.960
There was snow on the ground and lots of it.

02:42:24.160 --> 02:42:25.680
Dad yelled.

02:42:26.400 --> 02:42:28.880
How can the band play their instruments outside?

02:42:29.840 --> 02:42:30.400
Dad said.

02:42:31.040 --> 02:42:32.400
We'll move the stage inside.

02:42:33.440 --> 02:42:37.600
It barely fit within the garage because there were some boxes and garbage there.

02:42:38.640 --> 02:42:41.120
But when they finished they got a call from the band.

02:42:41.840 --> 02:42:43.680
They did not want to come in the snowstorm.

02:42:44.560 --> 02:42:47.360
Dad said let's get someone to perform magic.

02:42:48.320 --> 02:42:50.160
But no one would come because of the snow.

02:42:51.040 --> 02:42:52.080
Finally dad said.

02:42:52.720 --> 02:42:54.720
Cody there's too much snow.

02:42:55.360 --> 02:42:56.720
We need to cancel the party.

02:42:57.760 --> 02:42:58.320
Yes sir.

02:42:58.880 --> 02:42:59.920
Cody said sadly.

02:43:00.640 --> 02:43:02.480
It's going to be a boring birthday.

02:43:03.120 --> 02:43:03.760
He predicted.

02:43:04.560 --> 02:43:06.720
Cody wanted to share his birthday with someone.

02:43:07.520 --> 02:43:09.120
He wanted to be at his old home.

02:43:09.920 --> 02:43:11.520
He wanted to see his grandparents.

02:43:12.160 --> 02:43:13.680
But then something got his attention.

02:43:14.560 --> 02:43:16.160
He noticed a car in the driveway.

02:43:17.360 --> 02:43:19.360
His grandparents owned a car like that.

02:43:20.160 --> 02:43:21.040
Cody was right.

02:43:21.840 --> 02:43:23.840
His grandparents came for his birthday.

02:43:24.640 --> 02:43:25.920
Happy birthday Cody.

02:43:26.560 --> 02:43:28.160
We're sorry we are late.

02:43:28.160 --> 02:43:29.360
But there was so much snow.

02:43:30.160 --> 02:43:31.520
It made us go off schedule.

02:43:32.240 --> 02:43:34.080
We tried to leave a message to tell you.

02:43:35.040 --> 02:43:36.400
Cody told them what happened.

02:43:37.200 --> 02:43:39.200
I'm sorry said grandpa.

02:43:39.840 --> 02:43:40.640
I was sad.

02:43:41.200 --> 02:43:41.840
Cody said.

02:43:42.560 --> 02:43:43.600
But I'm not anymore.

02:43:44.320 --> 02:43:45.680
I'm so happy to see you.

02:43:46.720 --> 02:43:48.560
Dad brought out Cody's birthday treat.

02:43:49.200 --> 02:43:50.480
It was his favorite type.

02:43:51.200 --> 02:43:53.120
A Sunday with whipped cream on top.

02:43:53.920 --> 02:43:56.560
Then Cody told his grandparents about the new town.

02:43:57.520 --> 02:43:59.520
It was his best birthday ever.

02:44:03.520 --> 02:44:04.400
Unit 29.

02:44:04.960 --> 02:44:05.520
Word list.

02:44:06.720 --> 02:44:07.440
Advertise.

02:44:08.560 --> 02:44:13.360
To advertise is to tell people about something on TV, radio, etc.

02:44:14.480 --> 02:44:17.680
They used a ramen to help them advertise their product.

02:44:19.840 --> 02:44:20.400
A sign.

02:44:21.680 --> 02:44:24.720
To assign something to someone is to tell them to do it.

02:44:25.840 --> 02:44:28.480
I assigned the worker an important task.

02:44:30.720 --> 02:44:31.200
Audience.

02:44:32.320 --> 02:44:35.760
An audience is a group of people who watch something together.

02:44:36.880 --> 02:44:39.200
There was a large audience at the game.

02:44:41.440 --> 02:44:42.000
Breakfast.

02:44:43.120 --> 02:44:45.040
Breakfast is the first meal of the day.

02:44:46.160 --> 02:44:48.640
I eat breakfast at 8 every morning.

02:44:49.360 --> 02:44:50.400
Competition.

02:44:51.200 --> 02:44:56.000
A competition is a contest to see who is the best at something.

02:44:56.960 --> 02:45:00.000
He won the running competition over the weekend.

02:45:01.920 --> 02:45:02.480
Cool.

02:45:03.440 --> 02:45:06.400
If the weather is cool, it is a little bit cold.

02:45:07.440 --> 02:45:09.600
The weather is cool in the fall.

02:45:11.680 --> 02:45:12.240
Gain.

02:45:13.200 --> 02:45:15.760
If you gain something, you get more of it.

02:45:16.640 --> 02:45:18.800
I gained some weight over the summer.

02:45:20.720 --> 02:45:21.520
Importance.

02:45:22.640 --> 02:45:26.640
Importance means the quality or condition of being needed or valued.

02:45:27.680 --> 02:45:29.680
VIPs are people of great importance.

02:45:33.120 --> 02:45:33.920
Knowledge.

02:45:34.960 --> 02:45:37.360
Knowledge is information that you have about something.

02:45:38.560 --> 02:45:41.360
A music teacher should have good knowledge of music.

02:45:43.360 --> 02:45:44.000
Major.

02:45:44.320 --> 02:45:44.800
Major.

02:45:46.000 --> 02:45:48.720
If something is major, it is big or important.

02:45:49.840 --> 02:45:51.440
I have a major problem.

02:45:51.920 --> 02:45:54.480
My boss wants me to redo my project.

02:45:56.720 --> 02:45:56.960
Mean.

02:45:58.400 --> 02:46:01.200
Mean describes someone who is unkind or cruel.

02:46:02.400 --> 02:46:05.360
My coworker is a very mean person.

02:46:05.360 --> 02:46:07.200
He gets angry very quickly.

02:46:07.840 --> 02:46:09.280
Prefer.

02:46:09.280 --> 02:46:14.000
If you prefer something, you want it more than something else.

02:46:15.120 --> 02:46:19.040
I prefer to take the path that will lead me to a bright future.

02:46:21.200 --> 02:46:21.680
President.

02:46:22.800 --> 02:46:24.720
A president is the leader of a country.

02:46:25.920 --> 02:46:29.440
The president of our country made an important announcement.

02:46:31.600 --> 02:46:32.160
Progress.

02:46:33.360 --> 02:46:37.120
Progress is the act of getting closer to doing or finishing something.

02:46:37.840 --> 02:46:41.200
Our company made financial progress this year.

02:46:43.360 --> 02:46:43.920
Respect.

02:46:45.040 --> 02:46:48.080
Respect is a good opinion of someone because they are good.

02:46:49.200 --> 02:46:51.360
I have great respect for firemen.

02:46:53.600 --> 02:46:54.000
Rich.

02:46:55.120 --> 02:46:57.120
If you are rich, you have a lot of money.

02:46:58.240 --> 02:47:01.200
He is rich. He can buy anything he wants.

02:47:03.440 --> 02:47:03.840
Skill.

02:47:04.480 --> 02:47:08.640
A skill is the knowledge and ability that allows you to do something well.

02:47:09.760 --> 02:47:13.040
A snowboarder must have the right skills to do well.

02:47:15.200 --> 02:47:15.680
Somehow.

02:47:16.880 --> 02:47:20.960
Somehow means in a way or by some means, which is not known.

02:47:22.240 --> 02:47:25.840
He somehow had to find a way to reach the life preserver.

02:47:28.080 --> 02:47:28.560
Strength.

02:47:29.760 --> 02:47:32.080
Strength is the physical power that you have.

02:47:32.880 --> 02:47:36.880
Exercising will increase your strength and give you more power.

02:47:39.040 --> 02:47:39.440
Vote.

02:47:40.560 --> 02:47:44.080
To vote is to officially choose between two or more things.

02:47:45.120 --> 02:47:48.080
I voted for Billy to be our class president.

02:47:51.520 --> 02:47:53.120
How the world got light.

02:47:54.160 --> 02:47:58.320
The president of Darkland was a pig, a very bad pig.

02:47:58.960 --> 02:48:01.760
He was a pig of major importance.

02:48:02.320 --> 02:48:05.040
He was rich and he had a lot of strength.

02:48:05.760 --> 02:48:08.800
But he was mean to all the animals in Darkland.

02:48:09.600 --> 02:48:12.320
He kept all of the world's light in a bag.

02:48:12.960 --> 02:48:15.440
He preferred to keep the world cool and dark.

02:48:16.000 --> 02:48:18.640
He wanted to stop the progress of the city.

02:48:19.280 --> 02:48:21.840
The animals couldn't work in the dark.

02:48:21.840 --> 02:48:23.760
He didn't have any respect for them.

02:48:24.400 --> 02:48:26.240
Light is too good for them.

02:48:26.320 --> 02:48:31.440
He said only I should have light, but the animals needed light,

02:48:31.440 --> 02:48:33.600
so they decided to hold a competition.

02:48:34.480 --> 02:48:37.680
They wanted to find the smartest animal in Darkland.

02:48:38.480 --> 02:48:41.360
That animal had to steal light from the president.

02:48:42.000 --> 02:48:44.720
They advertised the competition everywhere.

02:48:45.280 --> 02:48:46.640
All the animals came.

02:48:47.520 --> 02:48:49.920
The animals all showed off their skills.

02:48:50.800 --> 02:48:55.280
The audience watched and then voted for the animal with the most knowledge.

02:48:56.000 --> 02:48:58.640
The winner was a tall bird named Raven.

02:48:59.280 --> 02:49:01.840
They assigned him the job of getting light.

02:49:02.480 --> 02:49:06.240
The next morning Raven ate breakfast and then left his home.

02:49:06.880 --> 02:49:09.520
How will I gain light from the president?

02:49:09.520 --> 02:49:10.320
Thought Raven.

02:49:10.960 --> 02:49:13.200
He needed to trick the president somehow.

02:49:14.000 --> 02:49:15.920
Then Raven had an idea.

02:49:16.720 --> 02:49:19.280
Raven could make his voice sound like anything.

02:49:20.080 --> 02:49:22.320
Raven walked up to the president's door.

02:49:22.800 --> 02:49:25.120
He made the sound of a crying baby.

02:49:25.760 --> 02:49:27.440
He cried very loudly.

02:49:28.240 --> 02:49:30.080
Soon the president opened the door.

02:49:30.880 --> 02:49:33.280
Be quiet, the president yelled.

02:49:33.840 --> 02:49:36.800
Right then Raven quickly made his move.

02:49:36.800 --> 02:49:39.600
He flew by the pig and found the soft bag.

02:49:40.160 --> 02:49:41.760
He took it outside.

02:49:41.760 --> 02:49:43.600
The sun was inside the bag.

02:49:44.160 --> 02:49:47.040
Raven flew high and put the sun in the sky.

02:49:47.600 --> 02:49:49.840
The president was very mad.

02:49:49.840 --> 02:49:50.880
Raven tricked him.

02:49:51.520 --> 02:49:53.840
But the other animals were very happy.

02:49:54.480 --> 02:49:56.560
At last they had light.

02:49:56.560 --> 02:49:58.960
All because of Raven's smart thinking.

02:50:03.040 --> 02:50:03.760
Unit 30.

02:50:04.480 --> 02:50:05.120
Word list.

02:50:06.240 --> 02:50:06.720
Above.

02:50:07.920 --> 02:50:11.360
If something is above, it is at a higher level than something else.

02:50:12.480 --> 02:50:15.280
He straightened the sign that was above the crowd.

02:50:17.440 --> 02:50:17.920
Ahead.

02:50:18.800 --> 02:50:22.080
If something is ahead of something else, it is in front of it.

02:50:23.120 --> 02:50:25.600
The blue car drove on ahead of us.

02:50:27.840 --> 02:50:28.240
Amount.

02:50:29.360 --> 02:50:31.760
An amount is how much there is of something.

02:50:32.800 --> 02:50:35.840
Can I use my car to pay for the entire amount?

02:50:38.000 --> 02:50:38.480
Belief.

02:50:39.520 --> 02:50:42.880
A belief is a strong feeling that something is correct or true.

02:50:44.080 --> 02:50:47.760
A preacher or priest should have a strong belief in God.

02:50:48.560 --> 02:50:50.480
Center.

02:50:51.600 --> 02:50:53.760
The center of something is the middle of it.

02:50:54.880 --> 02:50:58.320
The center of a dartboard is the most important spot.

02:51:00.480 --> 02:51:00.880
Common.

02:51:02.080 --> 02:51:05.840
If something is common, it happens often or there is much of it.

02:51:06.800 --> 02:51:09.440
It is common for snow to fall in the winter.

02:51:11.600 --> 02:51:12.080
Cost.

02:51:13.280 --> 02:51:16.560
To cost is to require expenditure or payment.

02:51:17.360 --> 02:51:20.640
These designer shoes cost more than the regular ones.

02:51:22.800 --> 02:51:23.440
Demonstrate.

02:51:24.480 --> 02:51:27.200
To demonstrate something is to show how it is done.

02:51:28.400 --> 02:51:31.040
She demonstrated her plan to her coworkers.

02:51:33.200 --> 02:51:33.680
Different.

02:51:34.960 --> 02:51:39.120
Different describes someone or something that is not the same as others.

02:51:40.160 --> 02:51:44.000
Each of my sisters has a different hairstyle from one another.

02:51:44.560 --> 02:51:45.520
Evidence.

02:51:46.080 --> 02:51:51.280
Evidence is a fact or thing that you use to prove something.

02:51:52.400 --> 02:51:56.080
You use the pictures as evidence that UFOs are real.

02:51:58.320 --> 02:51:58.880
Honesty.

02:52:00.000 --> 02:52:03.120
Honesty means the quality of being truthful or honest.

02:52:04.240 --> 02:52:06.800
A courtroom should be a place of honesty.

02:52:08.960 --> 02:52:09.360
Idiom.

02:52:10.240 --> 02:52:14.000
An idiom is a phrase with a meaning different from its words.

02:52:15.200 --> 02:52:19.360
The idiom when pigs fly means that something will never happen.

02:52:21.600 --> 02:52:22.240
Independent.

02:52:23.360 --> 02:52:27.120
If something is independent, it is not controlled by something else.

02:52:28.240 --> 02:52:31.520
She chose to live an independent life in the country.

02:52:33.680 --> 02:52:34.240
Inside.

02:52:35.360 --> 02:52:39.040
Inside means the inner part, space or side of something.

02:52:40.240 --> 02:52:42.480
The inside of the box was empty.

02:52:44.800 --> 02:52:45.280
Master.

02:52:46.480 --> 02:52:49.040
A master is a person who is very good at something.

02:52:50.240 --> 02:52:52.880
My brother is a master of Taekwondo.

02:52:55.040 --> 02:52:55.520
Memory.

02:52:56.640 --> 02:52:58.480
A memory is something you remember.

02:52:59.680 --> 02:53:04.000
The memory of my first time in the city will always be the best.

02:53:06.160 --> 02:53:06.560
Proper.

02:53:07.520 --> 02:53:09.680
If something is proper, it is right.

02:53:10.800 --> 02:53:13.760
It is not proper to throw your garbage on their own.

02:53:15.920 --> 02:53:16.400
Scan.

02:53:17.520 --> 02:53:20.400
To scan something is to look at it very carefully.

02:53:21.600 --> 02:53:23.920
You must scan each person closely.

02:53:26.080 --> 02:53:26.560
Section.

02:53:27.680 --> 02:53:30.080
A section is a part of something larger.

02:53:31.200 --> 02:53:34.560
The green section of the graph is the most important part.

02:53:36.800 --> 02:53:37.280
Surface.

02:53:38.480 --> 02:53:41.920
The surface of something is the top part or outside of it.

02:53:43.040 --> 02:53:45.680
The surface of the moon is very rough.

02:53:49.200 --> 02:53:50.720
Cats and Secrets.

02:53:51.920 --> 02:53:54.080
In English, there is a common idiom.

02:53:54.720 --> 02:53:56.240
Let the cat out of the bag.

02:53:56.960 --> 02:53:58.240
It means to tell a secret.

02:53:59.040 --> 02:54:00.640
But where did this idiom start?

02:54:01.520 --> 02:54:03.120
It came from a section of England.

02:54:03.760 --> 02:54:08.720
Long ago, people there went from town to town to sell things like vegetables,

02:54:08.720 --> 02:54:09.920
clothes and pigs.

02:54:10.480 --> 02:54:12.400
They had strong beliefs about honesty.

02:54:13.200 --> 02:54:14.320
They didn't like lying.

02:54:15.040 --> 02:54:18.320
One day, a man went to the section's center to sell things.

02:54:19.280 --> 02:54:20.960
I have a baby pig for sale.

02:54:21.680 --> 02:54:23.600
It won't cost much, he said.

02:54:24.320 --> 02:54:25.840
He held the animal above his head.

02:54:26.640 --> 02:54:29.120
His style was different from honest people's style.

02:54:29.920 --> 02:54:32.080
He was a master of tricking people in lying.

02:54:33.200 --> 02:54:35.360
A woman named Beth scanned his pig.

02:54:36.400 --> 02:54:38.560
He offered her the pig for one gold coin.

02:54:39.360 --> 02:54:40.880
That was a very small amount.

02:54:41.680 --> 02:54:42.800
Beth gave him the coin.

02:54:43.520 --> 02:54:44.640
He put it in his pocket.

02:54:45.600 --> 02:54:47.520
He walked ahead of Beth to get the pig.

02:54:48.480 --> 02:54:50.240
He gave her a closed bag and said,

02:54:50.800 --> 02:54:51.440
here's your pig.

02:54:52.320 --> 02:54:53.680
He then left very quickly.

02:54:55.040 --> 02:54:56.560
Beth looked at the bag's surface.

02:54:57.360 --> 02:54:58.080
It was moving.

02:54:59.040 --> 02:55:00.560
She opened it to let the pig out.

02:55:01.520 --> 02:55:02.880
A cat was inside.

02:55:03.840 --> 02:55:04.800
He tricked me.

02:55:05.520 --> 02:55:07.520
That isn't proper, she said.

02:55:08.480 --> 02:55:10.560
Later, the man returned to trick more people.

02:55:11.600 --> 02:55:14.240
Beth saw him and the memory of the cat came back.

02:55:15.040 --> 02:55:16.000
She told her friends.

02:55:16.720 --> 02:55:17.440
They stopped him.

02:55:18.320 --> 02:55:19.840
But no one knew what to do next.

02:55:20.720 --> 02:55:21.440
Someone said,

02:55:22.000 --> 02:55:25.040
we need an independent and fair person to decide that.

02:55:25.600 --> 02:55:26.560
They went to the judge.

02:55:27.360 --> 02:55:29.280
Beth told him about the cat in the bag.

02:55:29.920 --> 02:55:30.720
The judge asked,

02:55:31.440 --> 02:55:32.320
is there evidence?

02:55:32.880 --> 02:55:35.040
Can you demonstrate how he did it?

02:55:35.840 --> 02:55:37.760
Look in his bag, said Beth.

02:55:38.720 --> 02:55:41.200
She opened it and let a cat out of the bag.

02:55:41.840 --> 02:55:44.480
They learned the man's secret and he went to jail.

02:55:45.360 --> 02:55:46.800
That's how the idiom,

02:55:46.800 --> 02:55:50.560
let the cat out of the bag came to mean to tell a secret.

